  4   //@ts-check
  5   const Drawer = require('./src/Drawer');
  6   
  7   const Parser = require('./src/Parser');
  8   
  9   const SvgDrawer = require('./src/SvgDrawer'); // Detect SSR (server side rendering)
 10   
 11   
 12   var canUseDOM = !!(typeof window !== 'undefined' && window.document && window.document.createElement);
 13   /**
 14    * The SmilesDrawer namespace.
 15    * @typicalname SmilesDrawer
 16    */
 17   
 18   var SmilesDrawer = {
 19     Version: '1.0.0'
 20   };
 21   SmilesDrawer.Drawer = Drawer;
 22   SmilesDrawer.Parser = Parser;
 23   SmilesDrawer.SvgDrawer = SvgDrawer;
 24   /**
 25   * Cleans a SMILES string (removes non-valid characters)
 26   *
 27   * @static
 28   * @param {String} smiles A SMILES string.
 29   * @returns {String} The clean SMILES string.
 30   */
 31   
 32   SmilesDrawer.clean = function (smiles) {
 33     return smiles.replace(/[^A-Za-z0-9@\.\+\-\?!\(\)\[\]\{\}/\\=#\$:\*]/g, '');
 34   };
 35   /**
 36   * Applies the smiles drawer draw function to each canvas element that has a smiles string in the data-smiles attribute.
 37   *
 38   * @static
 39   * @param {Object} options SmilesDrawer options.
 40   * @param {String} [selector='canvas[data-smiles]'] Selectors for the draw areas (canvas elements).
 41   * @param {String} [themeName='light'] The theme to apply.
 42   * @param {Function} [onError='null'] A callback function providing an error object.
 43   */
 44   
 45   
 46   SmilesDrawer.apply = function (options, selector = 'canvas[data-smiles]', themeName = 'light', onError = null) {
 47     let smilesDrawer = new Drawer(options);
 48     let elements = document.querySelectorAll(selector);
 49   
 50     for (var i = 0; i < elements.length; i++) {
 51       let element = elements[i];
 52       SmilesDrawer.parse(element.getAttribute('data-smiles'), function (tree) {
 53         smilesDrawer.draw(tree, element, themeName, false);
 54       }, function (err) {
 55         if (onError) {
 56           onError(err);
 57         }
 58       });
 59     }
 60   };
 61   /**
 62   * Parses the entered smiles string.
 63   * 
 64   * @static
 65   * @param {String} smiles A SMILES string.
 66   * @param {Function} successCallback A callback that is called on success with the parse tree.
 67   * @param {Function} errorCallback A callback that is called with the error object on error.
 68   */
 69   
 70   
 71   SmilesDrawer.parse = function (smiles, successCallback, errorCallback) {
 72     try {
 73       if (successCallback) {
 74         successCallback(Parser.parse(smiles));
 75       }
 76     } catch (err) {
 77       if (errorCallback) {
 78         errorCallback(err);
 79       }
 80     }
 81   };
 82   
 83   if (canUseDOM) {
 84     window.SmilesDrawer = SmilesDrawer;
 85   } // There be dragons (polyfills)
 86   
 87   
 88   if (!Array.prototype.fill) {
 89     Object.defineProperty(Array.prototype, 'fill', {
 90       value: function (value) {
 91         // Steps 1-2.
 92         if (this == null) {
 93           throw new TypeError('this is null or not defined');
 94         }
 95   
 96         var O = Object(this); // Steps 3-5.
 97   
 98         var len = O.length >>> 0; // Steps 6-7.
 99   
100         var start = arguments[1];
101         var relativeStart = start >> 0; // Step 8.
102   
103         var k = relativeStart < 0 ? Math.max(len + relativeStart, 0) : Math.min(relativeStart, len); // Steps 9-10.
104   
105         var end = arguments[2];
106         var relativeEnd = end === undefined ? len : end >> 0; // Step 11.
107   
108         var final = relativeEnd < 0 ? Math.max(len + relativeEnd, 0) : Math.min(relativeEnd, len); // Step 12.
109   
110         while (k < final) {
111           O[k] = value;
112           k++;
113         } // Step 13.
114   
115   
116         return O;
117       }
118     });
119   }

124   "use strict";
125   
126   //@ts-check
127   
128   /** 
129    * A static class containing helper functions for array-related tasks. 
130    */
131   class ArrayHelper {
132     /**
133      * Clone an array or an object. If an object is passed, a shallow clone will be created.
134      *
135      * @static
136      * @param {*} arr The array or object to be cloned.
137      * @returns {*} A clone of the array or object.
138      */
139     static clone(arr) {
140       let out = Array.isArray(arr) ? Array() : {};
141   
142       for (let key in arr) {
143         let value = arr[key];
144   
145         if (typeof value.clone === 'function') {
146           out[key] = value.clone();
147         } else {
148           out[key] = typeof value === 'object' ? ArrayHelper.clone(value) : value;
149         }
150       }
151   
152       return out;
153     }
154     /**
155      * Returns a boolean indicating whether or not the two arrays contain the same elements.
156      * Only supports 1d, non-nested arrays.
157      *
158      * @static
159      * @param {Array} arrA An array.
160      * @param {Array} arrB An array.
161      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not the two arrays contain the same elements.
162      */
163   
164   
165     static equals(arrA, arrB) {
166       if (arrA.length !== arrB.length) {
167         return false;
168       }
169   
170       let tmpA = arrA.slice().sort();
171       let tmpB = arrB.slice().sort();
172   
173       for (var i = 0; i < tmpA.length; i++) {
174         if (tmpA[i] !== tmpB[i]) {
175           return false;
176         }
177       }
178   
179       return true;
180     }
181     /**
182      * Returns a string representation of an array. If the array contains objects with an id property, the id property is printed for each of the elements.
183      *
184      * @static
185      * @param {Object[]} arr An array.
186      * @param {*} arr[].id If the array contains an object with the property 'id', the properties value is printed. Else, the array elements value is printend.
187      * @returns {String} A string representation of the array.
188      */
189   
190   
191     static print(arr) {
192       if (arr.length == 0) {
193         return '';
194       }
195   
196       let s = '(';
197   
198       for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
199         s += arr[i].id ? arr[i].id + ', ' : arr[i] + ', ';
200       }
201   
202       s = s.substring(0, s.length - 2);
203       return s + ')';
204     }
205     /**
206      * Run a function for each element in the array. The element is supplied as an argument for the callback function
207      *
208      * @static
209      * @param {Array} arr An array.
210      * @param {Function} callback The callback function that is called for each element.
211      */
212   
213   
214     static each(arr, callback) {
215       for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
216         callback(arr[i]);
217       }
218     }
219     /**
220      * Return the array element from an array containing objects, where a property of the object is set to a given value.
221      *
222      * @static
223      * @param {Array} arr An array.
224      * @param {(String|Number)} property A property contained within an object in the array.
225      * @param {(String|Number)} value The value of the property.
226      * @returns {*} The array element matching the value.
227      */
228   
229   
230     static get(arr, property, value) {
231       for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
232         if (arr[i][property] == value) {
233           return arr[i];
234         }
235       }
236     }
237     /**
238      * Checks whether or not an array contains a given value. the options object passed as a second argument can contain three properties. value: The value to be searched for. property: The property that is to be searched for a given value. func: A function that is used as a callback to return either true or false in order to do a custom comparison.
239      *
240      * @static
241      * @param {Array} arr An array.
242      * @param {Object} options See method description.
243      * @param {*} options.value The value for which to check.
244      * @param {String} [options.property=undefined] The property on which to check.
245      * @param {Function} [options.func=undefined] A custom property function.
246      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean whether or not the array contains a value.
247      */
248   
249   
250     static contains(arr, options) {
251       if (!options.property && !options.func) {
252         for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
253           if (arr[i] == options.value) {
254             return true;
255           }
256         }
257       } else if (options.func) {
258         for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
259           if (options.func(arr[i])) {
260             return true;
261           }
262         }
263       } else {
264         for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
265           if (arr[i][options.property] == options.value) {
266             return true;
267           }
268         }
269       }
270   
271       return false;
272     }
273     /**
274      * Returns an array containing the intersection between two arrays. That is, values that are common to both arrays.
275      *
276      * @static
277      * @param {Array} arrA An array.
278      * @param {Array} arrB An array.
279      * @returns {Array} The intersecting vlaues.
280      */
281   
282   
283     static intersection(arrA, arrB) {
284       let intersection = new Array();
285   
286       for (let i = 0; i < arrA.length; i++) {
287         for (let j = 0; j < arrB.length; j++) {
288           if (arrA[i] === arrB[j]) {
289             intersection.push(arrA[i]);
290           }
291         }
292       }
293   
294       return intersection;
295     }
296     /**
297      * Returns an array of unique elements contained in an array.
298      *
299      * @static
300      * @param {Array} arr An array.
301      * @returns {Array} An array of unique elements contained within the array supplied as an argument.
302      */
303   
304   
305     static unique(arr) {
306       let contains = {};
307       return arr.filter(function (i) {
308         // using !== instead of hasOwnProperty (http://andrew.hedges.name/experiments/in/)
309         return contains[i] !== undefined ? false : contains[i] = true;
310       });
311     }
312     /**
313      * Count the number of occurences of a value in an array.
314      *
315      * @static
316      * @param {Array} arr An array.
317      * @param {*} value A value to be counted.
318      * @returns {Number} The number of occurences of a value in the array.
319      */
320   
321   
322     static count(arr, value) {
323       let count = 0;
324   
325       for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
326         if (arr[i] === value) {
327           count++;
328         }
329       }
330   
331       return count;
332     }
333     /**
334      * Toggles the value of an array. If a value is not contained in an array, the array returned will contain all the values of the original array including the value. If a value is contained in an array, the array returned will contain all the values of the original array excluding the value.
335      *
336      * @static
337      * @param {Array} arr An array.
338      * @param {*} value A value to be toggled.
339      * @returns {Array} The toggled array.
340      */
341   
342   
343     static toggle(arr, value) {
344       let newArr = Array();
345       let removed = false;
346   
347       for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
348         // Do not copy value if it exists
349         if (arr[i] !== value) {
350           newArr.push(arr[i]);
351         } else {
352           // The element was not copied to the new array, which
353           // means it was removed
354           removed = true;
355         }
356       } // If the element was not removed, then it was not in the array
357       // so add it
358   
359   
360       if (!removed) {
361         newArr.push(value);
362       }
363   
364       return newArr;
365     }
366     /**
367      * Remove a value from an array.
368      *
369      * @static
370      * @param {Array} arr An array.
371      * @param {*} value A value to be removed.
372      * @returns {Array} A new array with the element with a given value removed.
373      */
374   
375   
376     static remove(arr, value) {
377       let tmp = Array();
378   
379       for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
380         if (arr[i] !== value) {
381           tmp.push(arr[i]);
382         }
383       }
384   
385       return tmp;
386     }
387     /**
388      * Remove a value from an array with unique values.
389      *
390      * @static
391      * @param {Array} arr An array.
392      * @param {*} value A value to be removed.
393      * @returns {Array} An array with the element with a given value removed.
394      */
395   
396   
397     static removeUnique(arr, value) {
398       let index = arr.indexOf(value);
399   
400       if (index > -1) {
401         arr.splice(index, 1);
402       }
403   
404       return arr;
405     }
406     /**
407      * Remove all elements contained in one array from another array.
408      *
409      * @static
410      * @param {Array} arrA The array to be filtered.
411      * @param {Array} arrB The array containing elements that will be removed from the other array.
412      * @returns {Array} The filtered array.
413      */
414   
415   
416     static removeAll(arrA, arrB) {
417       return arrA.filter(function (item) {
418         return arrB.indexOf(item) === -1;
419       });
420     }
421     /**
422      * Merges two arrays and returns the result. The first array will be appended to the second array.
423      *
424      * @static
425      * @param {Array} arrA An array.
426      * @param {Array} arrB An array.
427      * @returns {Array} The merged array.
428      */
429   
430   
431     static merge(arrA, arrB) {
432       let arr = new Array(arrA.length + arrB.length);
433   
434       for (let i = 0; i < arrA.length; i++) {
435         arr[i] = arrA[i];
436       }
437   
438       for (let i = 0; i < arrB.length; i++) {
439         arr[arrA.length + i] = arrB[i];
440       }
441   
442       return arr;
443     }
444     /**
445      * Checks whether or not an array contains all the elements of another array, without regard to the order.
446      *
447      * @static
448      * @param {Array} arrA An array.
449      * @param {Array} arrB An array.
450      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not both array contain the same elements.
451      */
452   
453   
454     static containsAll(arrA, arrB) {
455       let containing = 0;
456   
457       for (let i = 0; i < arrA.length; i++) {
458         for (let j = 0; j < arrB.length; j++) {
459           if (arrA[i] === arrB[j]) {
460             containing++;
461           }
462         }
463       }
464   
465       return containing === arrB.length;
466     }
467     /**
468      * Sort an array of atomic number information. Where the number is indicated as x, x.y, x.y.z, ...
469      *
470      * @param {Object[]} arr An array of vertex ids with their associated atomic numbers.
471      * @param {Number} arr[].vertexId A vertex id.
472      * @param {String} arr[].atomicNumber The atomic number associated with the vertex id.
473      * @returns {Object[]} The array sorted by atomic number. Example of an array entry: { atomicNumber: 2, vertexId: 5 }.
474      */
475   
476   
477     static sortByAtomicNumberDesc(arr) {
478       let map = arr.map(function (e, i) {
479         return {
480           index: i,
481           value: e.atomicNumber.split('.').map(Number)
482         };
483       });
484       map.sort(function (a, b) {
485         let min = Math.min(b.value.length, a.value.length);
486         let i = 0;
487   
488         while (i < min && b.value[i] === a.value[i]) {
489           i++;
490         }
491   
492         return i === min ? b.value.length - a.value.length : b.value[i] - a.value[i];
493       });
494       return map.map(function (e) {
495         return arr[e.index];
496       });
497     }
498     /**
499      * Copies a an n-dimensional array.
500      * 
501      * @param {Array} arr The array to be copied.
502      * @returns {Array} The copy.
503      */
504   
505   
506     static deepCopy(arr) {
507       let newArr = Array();
508   
509       for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
510         let item = arr[i];
511   
512         if (item instanceof Array) {
513           newArr[i] = ArrayHelper.deepCopy(item);
514         } else {
515           newArr[i] = item;
516         }
517       }
518   
519       return newArr;
520     }
521   
522   }

527   "use strict";

529   //@ts-check
530   const ArrayHelper = require('./ArrayHelper');
531   
532   const Vertex = require('./Vertex');

534   const Ring = require('./Ring');
535   /** 
536    * A class representing an atom.
537    * 
538    * @property {String} element The element symbol of this atom. Single-letter symbols are always uppercase. Examples: H, C, F, Br, Si, ...
539    * @property {Boolean} drawExplicit A boolean indicating whether or not this atom is drawn explicitly (for example, a carbon atom). This overrides the default behaviour.
540    * @property {Object[]} ringbonds An array containing the ringbond ids and bond types as specified in the original SMILE.
541    * @property {String} branchBond The branch bond as defined in the SMILES.
542    * @property {Number} ringbonds[].id The ringbond id as defined in the SMILES.
543    * @property {String} ringbonds[].bondType The bond type of the ringbond as defined in the SMILES.
544    * @property {Number[]} rings The ids of rings which contain this atom.
545    * @property {String} bondType The bond type associated with this array. Examples: -, =, #, ...
546    * @property {Boolean} isBridge A boolean indicating whether or not this atom is part of a bridge in a bridged ring (contained by the largest ring).
547    * @property {Boolean} isBridgeNode A boolean indicating whether or not this atom is a bridge node (a member of the largest ring in a bridged ring which is connected to a bridge-atom).
548    * @property {Number[]} originalRings Used to back up rings when they are replaced by a bridged ring.
549    * @property {Number} bridgedRing The id of the bridged ring if the atom is part of a bridged ring.
550    * @property {Number[]} anchoredRings The ids of the rings that are anchored to this atom. The centers of anchored rings are translated when this atom is translated.
551    * @property {Object} bracket If this atom is defined as a bracket atom in the original SMILES, this object contains all the bracket information. Example: { hcount: {Number}, charge: ['--', '-', '+', '++'], isotope: {Number} }.
552    * @property {Number} plane Specifies on which "plane" the atoms is in stereochemical deptictions (-1 back, 0 middle, 1 front).
553    * @property {Object[]} attachedPseudoElements A map with containing information for pseudo elements or concatinated elements. The key is comprised of the element symbol and the hydrogen count.
554    * @property {String} attachedPseudoElement[].element The element symbol.
555    * @property {Number} attachedPseudoElement[].count The number of occurences that match the key.
556    * @property {Number} attachedPseudoElement[].hyrogenCount The number of hydrogens attached to each atom matching the key.
557    * @property {Boolean} hasAttachedPseudoElements A boolean indicating whether or not this attom will be drawn with an attached pseudo element or concatinated elements.
558    * @property {Boolean} isDrawn A boolean indicating whether or not this atom is drawn. In contrast to drawExplicit, the bond is drawn neither.
559    * @property {Boolean} isConnectedToRing A boolean indicating whether or not this atom is directly connected (but not a member of) a ring.
560    * @property {String[]} neighbouringElements An array containing the element symbols of neighbouring atoms.
561    * @property {Boolean} isPartOfAromaticRing A boolean indicating whether or not this atom is part of an explicitly defined aromatic ring. Example: c1ccccc1.
562    * @property {Number} bondCount The number of bonds in which this atom is participating.
563    * @property {String} chirality The chirality of this atom if it is a stereocenter (R or S).
564    * @property {Number} priority The priority of this atom acording to the CIP rules, where 0 is the highest priority.
565    * @property {Boolean} mainChain A boolean indicating whether or not this atom is part of the main chain (used for chirality).
566    * @property {String} hydrogenDirection The direction of the hydrogen, either up or down. Only for stereocenters with and explicit hydrogen.
567    * @property {Number} subtreeDepth The depth of the subtree coming from a stereocenter.
568    */
569   
570   
571   class Atom {
572     /**
573      * The constructor of the class Atom.
574      *
575      * @param {String} element The one-letter code of the element.
576      * @param {String} [bondType='-'] The type of the bond associated with this atom.
577      */
578     constructor(element, bondType = '-') {
579       this.element = element.length === 1 ? element.toUpperCase() : element;
580       this.drawExplicit = false;
581       this.ringbonds = Array();
582       this.rings = Array();
583       this.bondType = bondType;
584       this.branchBond = null;
585       this.isBridge = false;
586       this.isBridgeNode = false;
587       this.originalRings = Array();
588       this.bridgedRing = null;
589       this.anchoredRings = Array();
590       this.bracket = null;
591       this.plane = 0;
592       this.attachedPseudoElements = {};
593       this.hasAttachedPseudoElements = false;
594       this.isDrawn = true;
595       this.isConnectedToRing = false;
596       this.neighbouringElements = Array();
597       this.isPartOfAromaticRing = element !== this.element;
598       this.bondCount = 0;
599       this.chirality = '';
600       this.isStereoCenter = false;
601       this.priority = 0;
602       this.mainChain = false;
603       this.hydrogenDirection = 'down';
604       this.subtreeDepth = 1;
605       this.hasHydrogen = false;
606     }
607     /**
608      * Adds a neighbouring element to this atom.
609      * 
610      * @param {String} element A string representing an element.
611      */
612   
613   
614     addNeighbouringElement(element) {
615       this.neighbouringElements.push(element);
616     }
617     /**
618      * Attaches a pseudo element (e.g. Ac) to the atom.
619      * @param {String} element The element identifier (e.g. Br, C, ...).
620      * @param {String} previousElement The element that is part of the main chain (not the terminals that are converted to the pseudo element or concatinated).
621      * @param {Number} [hydrogenCount=0] The number of hydrogens for the element.
622      * @param {Number} [charge=0] The charge for the element.
623      */
624   
625   
626     attachPseudoElement(element, previousElement, hydrogenCount = 0, charge = 0) {
627       if (hydrogenCount === null) {
628         hydrogenCount = 0;
629       }
630   
631       if (charge === null) {
632         charge = 0;
633       }
634   
635       let key = hydrogenCount + element + charge;
636   
637       if (this.attachedPseudoElements[key]) {
638         this.attachedPseudoElements[key].count += 1;
639       } else {
640         this.attachedPseudoElements[key] = {
641           element: element,
642           count: 1,
643           hydrogenCount: hydrogenCount,
644           previousElement: previousElement,
645           charge: charge
646         };
647       }
648   
649       this.hasAttachedPseudoElements = true;
650     }
651     /**
652      * Returns the attached pseudo elements sorted by hydrogen count (ascending).
653      *
654      * @returns {Object} The sorted attached pseudo elements.
655      */
656   
657   
658     getAttachedPseudoElements() {
659       let ordered = {};
660       let that = this;
661       Object.keys(this.attachedPseudoElements).sort().forEach(function (key) {
662         ordered[key] = that.attachedPseudoElements[key];
663       });
664       return ordered;
665     }
666     /**
667      * Returns the number of attached pseudo elements.
668      *
669      * @returns {Number} The number of attached pseudo elements.
670      */
671   
672   
673     getAttachedPseudoElementsCount() {
674       return Object.keys(this.attachedPseudoElements).length;
675     }
676     /**
677      * Returns whether this atom is a heteroatom (not C and not H).
678      *
679      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether this atom is a heteroatom.
680      */
681   
682   
683     isHeteroAtom() {
684       return this.element !== 'C' && this.element !== 'H';
685     }
686     /**
687      * Defines this atom as the anchor for a ring. When doing repositionings of the vertices and the vertex associated with this atom is moved, the center of this ring is moved as well.
688      *
689      * @param {Number} ringId A ring id.
690      */
691   
692   
693     addAnchoredRing(ringId) {
694       if (!ArrayHelper.contains(this.anchoredRings, {
695         value: ringId
696       })) {
697         this.anchoredRings.push(ringId);
698       }
699     }
700     /**
701      * Returns the number of ringbonds (breaks in rings to generate the MST of the smiles) within this atom is connected to.
702      *
703      * @returns {Number} The number of ringbonds this atom is connected to.
704      */
705   
706   
707     getRingbondCount() {
708       return this.ringbonds.length;
709     }
710     /**
711      * Backs up the current rings.
712      */
713   
714   
715     backupRings() {
716       this.originalRings = Array(this.rings.length);
717   
718       for (let i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
719         this.originalRings[i] = this.rings[i];
720       }
721     }
722     /**
723      * Restores the most recent backed up rings.
724      */
725   
726   
727     restoreRings() {
728       this.rings = Array(this.originalRings.length);
729   
730       for (let i = 0; i < this.originalRings.length; i++) {
731         this.rings[i] = this.originalRings[i];
732       }
733     }
734     /**
735      * Checks whether or not two atoms share a common ringbond id. A ringbond is a break in a ring created when generating the spanning tree of a structure.
736      *
737      * @param {Atom} atomA An atom.
738      * @param {Atom} atomB An atom.
739      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not two atoms share a common ringbond.
740      */
741   
742   
743     haveCommonRingbond(atomA, atomB) {
744       for (let i = 0; i < atomA.ringbonds.length; i++) {
745         for (let j = 0; j < atomB.ringbonds.length; j++) {
746           if (atomA.ringbonds[i].id == atomB.ringbonds[j].id) {
747             return true;
748           }
749         }
750       }
751   
752       return false;
753     }
754     /**
755      * Check whether or not the neighbouring elements of this atom equal the supplied array.
756      * 
757      * @param {String[]} arr An array containing all the elements that are neighbouring this atom. E.g. ['C', 'O', 'O', 'N']
758      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not the neighbours match the supplied array of elements.
759      */
760   
761   
762     neighbouringElementsEqual(arr) {
763       if (arr.length !== this.neighbouringElements.length) {
764         return false;
765       }
766   
767       arr.sort();
768       this.neighbouringElements.sort();
769   
770       for (var i = 0; i < this.neighbouringElements.length; i++) {
771         if (arr[i] !== this.neighbouringElements[i]) {
772           return false;
773         }
774       }
775   
776       return true;
777     }
778     /**
779      * Get the atomic number of this atom.
780      * 
781      * @returns {Number} The atomic number of this atom.
782      */
783   
784   
785     getAtomicNumber() {
786       return Atom.atomicNumbers[this.element];
787     }
788     /**
789      * Get the maximum number of bonds for this atom.
790      * 
791      * @returns {Number} The maximum number of bonds of this atom.
792      */
793   
794   
795     getMaxBonds() {
796       return Atom.maxBonds[this.element];
797     }

1090   "use strict";
1091   
1092   //@ts-check
1093   const MathHelper = require('./MathHelper');
1094   
1095   const Vector2 = require('./Vector2');
1096   
1097   const Line = require('./Line');

1099   const Vertex = require('./Vertex');
1100   
1101   const Ring = require('./Ring');
1102   
1103   const {
1104     getChargeText
1105   } = require('./UtilityFunctions');
1106   /** 
1107    * A class wrapping a canvas element.
1108    * 
1109    * @property {HTMLElement} canvas The HTML element for the canvas associated with this CanvasWrapper instance.
1110    * @property {CanvasRenderingContext2D} ctx The CanvasRenderingContext2D of the canvas associated with this CanvasWrapper instance.
1111    * @property {Object} colors The colors object as defined in the SmilesDrawer options.
1112    * @property {Object} opts The SmilesDrawer options.
1113    * @property {Number} drawingWidth The width of the canvas.
1114    * @property {Number} drawingHeight The height of the canvas.
1115    * @property {Number} offsetX The horizontal offset required for centering the drawing.
1116    * @property {Number} offsetY The vertical offset required for centering the drawing.
1117    * @property {Number} fontLarge The large font size in pt.
1118    * @property {Number} fontSmall The small font size in pt.
1119    */
1120   
1121   
1122   class CanvasWrapper {
1123     /**
1124      * The constructor for the class CanvasWrapper.
1125      *
1126      * @param {(String|HTMLElement)} target The canvas id or the canvas HTMLElement.
1127      * @param {ThemeManager} themeManager Theme manager for setting proper colors.
1128      * @param {Object} options The smiles drawer options object.
1129      */
1130     constructor(target, themeManager, options) {
1131       if (typeof target === 'string' || target instanceof String) {
1132         this.canvas = document.getElementById(target);
1133       } else {
1134         this.canvas = target;
1135       }
1136   
1137       this.ctx = this.canvas.getContext('2d');
1138       this.themeManager = themeManager;
1139       this.opts = options;
1140       this.drawingWidth = 0.0;
1141       this.drawingHeight = 0.0;
1142       this.offsetX = 0.0;
1143       this.offsetY = 0.0;
1144       this.fontLarge = this.opts.fontSizeLarge + 'pt Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif';
1145       this.fontSmall = this.opts.fontSizeSmall + 'pt Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif';
1146       this.updateSize(this.opts.width, this.opts.height);
1147       this.ctx.font = this.fontLarge;
1148       this.hydrogenWidth = this.ctx.measureText('H').width;
1149       this.halfHydrogenWidth = this.hydrogenWidth / 2.0;
1150       this.halfBondThickness = this.opts.bondThickness / 2.0; // TODO: Find out why clear was here.
1151       // this.clear();
1152     }
1153     /**
1154      * Update the width and height of the canvas
1155      * 
1156      * @param {Number} width 
1157      * @param {Number} height 
1158      */
1159   
1160   
1161     updateSize(width, height) {
1162       this.devicePixelRatio = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;
1163       this.backingStoreRatio = this.ctx.webkitBackingStorePixelRatio || this.ctx.mozBackingStorePixelRatio || this.ctx.msBackingStorePixelRatio || this.ctx.oBackingStorePixelRatio || this.ctx.backingStorePixelRatio || 1;
1164       this.ratio = this.devicePixelRatio / this.backingStoreRatio;
1165   
1166       if (this.ratio !== 1) {
1167         this.canvas.width = width * this.ratio;
1168         this.canvas.height = height * this.ratio;
1169         this.canvas.style.width = width + 'px';
1170         this.canvas.style.height = height + 'px';
1171         this.ctx.setTransform(this.ratio, 0, 0, this.ratio, 0, 0);
1172       } else {
1173         this.canvas.width = width * this.ratio;
1174         this.canvas.height = height * this.ratio;
1175       }
1176     }
1177     /**
1178      * Sets a provided theme.
1179      *
1180      * @param {Object} theme A theme from the smiles drawer options.
1181      */
1182   
1183   
1184     setTheme(theme) {
1185       this.colors = theme;
1186     }
1187     /**
1188      * Scale the canvas based on vertex positions.
1189      *
1190      * @param {Vertex[]} vertices An array of vertices containing the vertices associated with the current molecule.
1191      */
1192   
1193   
1194     scale(vertices) {
1195       // Figure out the final size of the image
1196       let maxX = -Number.MAX_VALUE;
1197       let maxY = -Number.MAX_VALUE;
1198       let minX = Number.MAX_VALUE;
1199       let minY = Number.MAX_VALUE;
1200   
1201       for (var i = 0; i < vertices.length; i++) {
1202         if (!vertices[i].value.isDrawn) {
1203           continue;
1204         }
1205   
1206         let p = vertices[i].position;
1207         if (maxX < p.x) maxX = p.x;
1208         if (maxY < p.y) maxY = p.y;
1209         if (minX > p.x) minX = p.x;
1210         if (minY > p.y) minY = p.y;
1211       } // Add padding
1212   
1213   
1214       var padding = this.opts.padding;
1215       maxX += padding;
1216       maxY += padding;
1217       minX -= padding;
1218       minY -= padding;
1219       this.drawingWidth = maxX - minX;
1220       this.drawingHeight = maxY - minY;
1221       var scaleX = this.canvas.offsetWidth / this.drawingWidth;
1222       var scaleY = this.canvas.offsetHeight / this.drawingHeight;
1223       var scale = scaleX < scaleY ? scaleX : scaleY;
1224       this.ctx.scale(scale, scale);
1225       this.offsetX = -minX;
1226       this.offsetY = -minY; // Center
1227   
1228       if (scaleX < scaleY) {
1229         this.offsetY += this.canvas.offsetHeight / (2.0 * scale) - this.drawingHeight / 2.0;
1230       } else {
1231         this.offsetX += this.canvas.offsetWidth / (2.0 * scale) - this.drawingWidth / 2.0;
1232       }
1233     }
1234     /**
1235      * Resets the transform of the canvas.
1236      */
1237   
1238   
1239     reset() {
1240       this.ctx.setTransform(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0);
1241     }
1242     /**
1243      * Returns the hex code of a color associated with a key from the current theme.
1244      *
1245      * @param {String} key The color key in the theme (e.g. C, N, BACKGROUND, ...).
1246      * @returns {String} A color hex value.
1247      */
1248   
1249   
1250     getColor(key) {
1251       key = key.toUpperCase();
1252   
1253       if (key in this.colors) {
1254         return this.colors[key];
1255       }
1256   
1257       return this.colors['C'];
1258     }
1259     /**
1260      * Draws a circle to a canvas context.
1261      * @param {Number} x The x coordinate of the circles center.
1262      * @param {Number} y The y coordinate of the circles center.
1263      * @param {Number} radius The radius of the circle
1264      * @param {String} color A hex encoded color.
1265      * @param {Boolean} [fill=true] Whether to fill or stroke the circle.
1266      * @param {Boolean} [debug=false] Draw in debug mode.
1267      * @param {String} [debugText=''] A debug message.
1268      */
1269   
1270   
1271     drawCircle(x, y, radius, color, fill = true, debug = false, debugText = '') {
1272       let ctx = this.ctx;
1273       let offsetX = this.offsetX;
1274       let offsetY = this.offsetY;
1275       ctx.save();
1276       ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;
1277       ctx.beginPath();
1278       ctx.arc(x + offsetX, y + offsetY, radius, 0, MathHelper.twoPI, true);
1279       ctx.closePath();
1280   
1281       if (debug) {
1282         if (fill) {
1283           ctx.fillStyle = '#f00';
1284           ctx.fill();
1285         } else {
1286           ctx.strokeStyle = '#f00';
1287           ctx.stroke();
1288         }
1289   
1290         this.drawDebugText(x, y, debugText);
1291       } else {
1292         if (fill) {
1293           ctx.fillStyle = color;
1294           ctx.fill();
1295         } else {
1296           ctx.strokeStyle = color;
1297           ctx.stroke();
1298         }
1299       }
1300   
1301       ctx.restore();
1302     }
1303     /**
1304      * Draw a line to a canvas.
1305      *
1306      * @param {Line} line A line.
1307      * @param {Boolean} [dashed=false] Whether or not the line is dashed.
1308      * @param {Number} [alpha=1.0] The alpha value of the color.
1309      */
1310   
1311   
1312     drawLine(line, dashed = false, alpha = 1.0) {
1313       let ctx = this.ctx;
1314       let offsetX = this.offsetX;
1315       let offsetY = this.offsetY; // Add a shadow behind the line
1316   
1317       let shortLine = line.clone().shorten(4.0);
1318       let l = shortLine.getLeftVector().clone();
1319       let r = shortLine.getRightVector().clone();
1320       l.x += offsetX;
1321       l.y += offsetY;
1322       r.x += offsetX;
1323       r.y += offsetY; // Draw the "shadow"
1324   
1325       if (!dashed) {
1326         ctx.save();
1327         ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'destination-out';
1328         ctx.beginPath();
1329         ctx.moveTo(l.x, l.y);
1330         ctx.lineTo(r.x, r.y);
1331         ctx.lineCap = 'round';
1332         ctx.lineWidth = this.opts.bondThickness + 1.2;
1333         ctx.strokeStyle = this.themeManager.getColor('BACKGROUND');
1334         ctx.stroke();
1335         ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'source-over';
1336         ctx.restore();
1337       }
1338   
1339       l = line.getLeftVector().clone();
1340       r = line.getRightVector().clone();
1341       l.x += offsetX;
1342       l.y += offsetY;
1343       r.x += offsetX;
1344       r.y += offsetY;
1345       ctx.save();
1346       ctx.beginPath();
1347       ctx.moveTo(l.x, l.y);
1348       ctx.lineTo(r.x, r.y);
1349       ctx.lineCap = 'round';
1350       ctx.lineWidth = this.opts.bondThickness;
1351       let gradient = this.ctx.createLinearGradient(l.x, l.y, r.x, r.y);
1352       gradient.addColorStop(0.4, this.themeManager.getColor(line.getLeftElement()) || this.themeManager.getColor('C'));
1353       gradient.addColorStop(0.6, this.themeManager.getColor(line.getRightElement()) || this.themeManager.getColor('C'));
1354   
1355       if (dashed) {
1356         ctx.setLineDash([1, 1.5]);
1357         ctx.lineWidth = this.opts.bondThickness / 1.5;
1358       }
1359   
1360       if (alpha < 1.0) {
1361         ctx.globalAlpha = alpha;
1362       }
1363   
1364       ctx.strokeStyle = gradient;
1365       ctx.stroke();
1366       ctx.restore();
1367     }
1368     /**
1369      * Draw a wedge on the canvas.
1370      *
1371      * @param {Line} line A line.
1372      * @param {Number} width The wedge width.
1373      */
1374   
1375   
1376     drawWedge(line, width = 1.0) {
1377       if (isNaN(line.from.x) || isNaN(line.from.y) || isNaN(line.to.x) || isNaN(line.to.y)) {
1378         return;
1379       }
1380   
1381       let ctx = this.ctx;
1382       let offsetX = this.offsetX;
1383       let offsetY = this.offsetY; // Add a shadow behind the line
1384   
1385       let shortLine = line.clone().shorten(5.0);
1386       let l = shortLine.getLeftVector().clone();
1387       let r = shortLine.getRightVector().clone();
1388       l.x += offsetX;
1389       l.y += offsetY;
1390       r.x += offsetX;
1391       r.y += offsetY;
1392       l = line.getLeftVector().clone();
1393       r = line.getRightVector().clone();
1394       l.x += offsetX;
1395       l.y += offsetY;
1396       r.x += offsetX;
1397       r.y += offsetY;
1398       ctx.save();
1399       let normals = Vector2.normals(l, r);
1400       normals[0].normalize();
1401       normals[1].normalize();
1402       let isRightChiralCenter = line.getRightChiral();
1403       let start = l;
1404       let end = r;
1405   
1406       if (isRightChiralCenter) {
1407         start = r;
1408         end = l;
1409       }
1410   
1411       let t = Vector2.add(start, Vector2.multiplyScalar(normals[0], this.halfBondThickness));
1412       let u = Vector2.add(end, Vector2.multiplyScalar(normals[0], 1.5 + this.halfBondThickness));
1413       let v = Vector2.add(end, Vector2.multiplyScalar(normals[1], 1.5 + this.halfBondThickness));
1414       let w = Vector2.add(start, Vector2.multiplyScalar(normals[1], this.halfBondThickness));
1415       ctx.beginPath();
1416       ctx.moveTo(t.x, t.y);
1417       ctx.lineTo(u.x, u.y);
1418       ctx.lineTo(v.x, v.y);
1419       ctx.lineTo(w.x, w.y);
1420       let gradient = this.ctx.createRadialGradient(r.x, r.y, this.opts.bondLength, r.x, r.y, 0);
1421       gradient.addColorStop(0.4, this.themeManager.getColor(line.getLeftElement()) || this.themeManager.getColor('C'));
1422       gradient.addColorStop(0.6, this.themeManager.getColor(line.getRightElement()) || this.themeManager.getColor('C'));
1423       ctx.fillStyle = gradient;
1424       ctx.fill();
1425       ctx.restore();
1426     }
1427     /**
1428      * Draw a dashed wedge on the canvas.
1429      *
1430      * @param {Line} line A line.
1431      */
1432   
1433   
1434     drawDashedWedge(line) {
1435       if (isNaN(line.from.x) || isNaN(line.from.y) || isNaN(line.to.x) || isNaN(line.to.y)) {
1436         return;
1437       }
1438   
1439       let ctx = this.ctx;
1440       let offsetX = this.offsetX;
1441       let offsetY = this.offsetY;
1442       let l = line.getLeftVector().clone();
1443       let r = line.getRightVector().clone();
1444       l.x += offsetX;
1445       l.y += offsetY;
1446       r.x += offsetX;
1447       r.y += offsetY;
1448       ctx.save();
1449       let normals = Vector2.normals(l, r);
1450       normals[0].normalize();
1451       normals[1].normalize();
1452       let isRightChiralCenter = line.getRightChiral();
1453       let start;
1454       let end;
1455       let sStart;
1456       let sEnd;
1457       let shortLine = line.clone();
1458   
1459       if (isRightChiralCenter) {
1460         start = r;
1461         end = l;
1462         shortLine.shortenRight(1.0);
1463         sStart = shortLine.getRightVector().clone();
1464         sEnd = shortLine.getLeftVector().clone();
1465       } else {
1466         start = l;
1467         end = r;
1468         shortLine.shortenLeft(1.0);
1469         sStart = shortLine.getLeftVector().clone();
1470         sEnd = shortLine.getRightVector().clone();
1471       }
1472   
1473       sStart.x += offsetX;
1474       sStart.y += offsetY;
1475       sEnd.x += offsetX;
1476       sEnd.y += offsetY;
1477       let dir = Vector2.subtract(end, start).normalize();
1478       ctx.strokeStyle = this.themeManager.getColor('C');
1479       ctx.lineCap = 'round';
1480       ctx.lineWidth = this.opts.bondThickness;
1481       ctx.beginPath();
1482       let length = line.getLength();
1483       let step = 1.25 / (length / (this.opts.bondThickness * 3.0));
1484       let changed = false;
1485   
1486       for (var t = 0.0; t < 1.0; t += step) {
1487         let to = Vector2.multiplyScalar(dir, t * length);
1488         let startDash = Vector2.add(start, to);
1489         let width = 1.5 * t;
1490         let dashOffset = Vector2.multiplyScalar(normals[0], width);
1491   
1492         if (!changed && t > 0.5) {
1493           ctx.stroke();
1494           ctx.beginPath();
1495           ctx.strokeStyle = this.themeManager.getColor(line.getRightElement()) || this.themeManager.getColor('C');
1496           changed = true;
1497         }
1498   
1499         startDash.subtract(dashOffset);
1500         ctx.moveTo(startDash.x, startDash.y);
1501         startDash.add(Vector2.multiplyScalar(dashOffset, 2.0));
1502         ctx.lineTo(startDash.x, startDash.y);
1503       }
1504   
1505       ctx.stroke();
1506       ctx.restore();
1507     }
1508     /**
1509      * Draws a debug text message at a given position
1510      *
1511      * @param {Number} x The x coordinate.
1512      * @param {Number} y The y coordinate.
1513      * @param {String} text The debug text.
1514      */
1515   
1516   
1517     drawDebugText(x, y, text) {
1518       let ctx = this.ctx;
1519       ctx.save();
1520       ctx.font = '5px Droid Sans, sans-serif';
1521       ctx.textAlign = 'start';
1522       ctx.textBaseline = 'top';
1523       ctx.fillStyle = '#ff0000';
1524       ctx.fillText(text, x + this.offsetX, y + this.offsetY);
1525       ctx.restore();
1526     }
1527     /**
1528      * Draw a ball to the canvas.
1529      *
1530      * @param {Number} x The x position of the text.
1531      * @param {Number} y The y position of the text.
1532      * @param {String} elementName The name of the element (single-letter).
1533      */
1534   
1535   
1536     drawBall(x, y, elementName) {
1537       let ctx = this.ctx;
1538       ctx.save();
1539       ctx.beginPath();
1540       ctx.arc(x + this.offsetX, y + this.offsetY, this.opts.bondLength / 4.5, 0, MathHelper.twoPI, false);
1541       ctx.fillStyle = this.themeManager.getColor(elementName);
1542       ctx.fill();
1543       ctx.restore();
1544     }
1545     /**
1546      * Draw a point to the canvas.
1547      *
1548      * @param {Number} x The x position of the point.
1549      * @param {Number} y The y position of the point.
1550      * @param {String} elementName The name of the element (single-letter).
1551      */
1552   
1553   
1554     drawPoint(x, y, elementName) {
1555       let ctx = this.ctx;
1556       let offsetX = this.offsetX;
1557       let offsetY = this.offsetY;
1558       ctx.save();
1559       ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'destination-out';
1560       ctx.beginPath();
1561       ctx.arc(x + offsetX, y + offsetY, 1.5, 0, MathHelper.twoPI, true);
1562       ctx.closePath();
1563       ctx.fill();
1564       ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'source-over';
1565       ctx.beginPath();
1566       ctx.arc(x + this.offsetX, y + this.offsetY, 0.75, 0, MathHelper.twoPI, false);
1567       ctx.fillStyle = this.themeManager.getColor(elementName);
1568       ctx.fill();
1569       ctx.restore();
1570     }
1571     /**
1572      * Draw a text to the canvas.
1573      *
1574      * @param {Number} x The x position of the text.
1575      * @param {Number} y The y position of the text.
1576      * @param {String} elementName The name of the element (single-letter).
1577      * @param {Number} hydrogens The number of hydrogen atoms.
1578      * @param {String} direction The direction of the text in relation to the associated vertex.
1579      * @param {Boolean} isTerminal A boolean indicating whether or not the vertex is terminal.
1580      * @param {Number} charge The charge of the atom.
1581      * @param {Number} isotope The isotope number.
1582      * @param {Object} attachedPseudoElement A map with containing information for pseudo elements or concatinated elements. The key is comprised of the element symbol and the hydrogen count.
1583      * @param {String} attachedPseudoElement.element The element symbol.
1584      * @param {Number} attachedPseudoElement.count The number of occurences that match the key.
1585      * @param {Number} attachedPseudoElement.hyrogenCount The number of hydrogens attached to each atom matching the key.
1586      */
1587   
1588   
1589     drawText(x, y, elementName, hydrogens, direction, isTerminal, charge, isotope, attachedPseudoElement = {}) {
1590       let ctx = this.ctx;
1591       let offsetX = this.offsetX;
1592       let offsetY = this.offsetY;
1593       ctx.save();
1594       ctx.textAlign = 'start';
1595       ctx.textBaseline = 'alphabetic';
1596       let pseudoElementHandled = false; // Charge
1597   
1598       let chargeText = '';
1599       let chargeWidth = 0;
1600   
1601       if (charge) {
1602         chargeText = getChargeText(charge);
1603         ctx.font = this.fontSmall;
1604         chargeWidth = ctx.measureText(chargeText).width;
1605       }
1606   
1607       let isotopeText = '0';
1608       let isotopeWidth = 0;
1609   
1610       if (isotope > 0) {
1611         isotopeText = isotope.toString();
1612         ctx.font = this.fontSmall;
1613         isotopeWidth = ctx.measureText(isotopeText).width;
1614       } // TODO: Better handle exceptions
1615       // Exception for nitro (draw nitro as NO2 instead of N+O-O)
1616   
1617   
1618       if (charge === 1 && elementName === 'N' && attachedPseudoElement.hasOwnProperty('0O') && attachedPseudoElement.hasOwnProperty('0O-1')) {
1619         attachedPseudoElement = {
1620           '0O': {
1621             element: 'O',
1622             count: 2,
1623             hydrogenCount: 0,
1624             previousElement: 'C',
1625             charge: ''
1626           }
1627         };
1628         charge = 0;
1629       }
1630   
1631       ctx.font = this.fontLarge;
1632       ctx.fillStyle = this.themeManager.getColor('BACKGROUND');
1633       let dim = ctx.measureText(elementName);
1634       dim.totalWidth = dim.width + chargeWidth;
1635       dim.height = parseInt(this.fontLarge, 10);
1636       let r = dim.width > this.opts.fontSizeLarge ? dim.width : this.opts.fontSizeLarge;
1637       r /= 1.5;
1638       ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'destination-out';
1639       ctx.beginPath();
1640       ctx.arc(x + offsetX, y + offsetY, r, 0, MathHelper.twoPI, true);
1641       ctx.closePath();
1642       ctx.fill();
1643       ctx.globalCompositeOperation = 'source-over';
1644       let cursorPos = -dim.width / 2.0;
1645       let cursorPosLeft = -dim.width / 2.0;
1646       ctx.fillStyle = this.themeManager.getColor(elementName);
1647       ctx.fillText(elementName, x + offsetX + cursorPos, y + this.opts.halfFontSizeLarge + offsetY);
1648       cursorPos += dim.width;
1649   
1650       if (charge) {
1651         ctx.font = this.fontSmall;
1652         ctx.fillText(chargeText, x + offsetX + cursorPos, y - this.opts.fifthFontSizeSmall + offsetY);
1653         cursorPos += chargeWidth;
1654       }
1655   
1656       if (isotope > 0) {
1657         ctx.font = this.fontSmall;
1658         ctx.fillText(isotopeText, x + offsetX + cursorPosLeft - isotopeWidth, y - this.opts.fifthFontSizeSmall + offsetY);
1659         cursorPosLeft -= isotopeWidth;
1660       }
1661   
1662       ctx.font = this.fontLarge;
1663       let hydrogenWidth = 0;
1664       let hydrogenCountWidth = 0;
1665   
1666       if (hydrogens === 1) {
1667         let hx = x + offsetX;
1668         let hy = y + offsetY + this.opts.halfFontSizeLarge;
1669         hydrogenWidth = this.hydrogenWidth;
1670         cursorPosLeft -= hydrogenWidth;
1671   
1672         if (direction === 'left') {
1673           hx += cursorPosLeft;
1674         } else if (direction === 'right') {
1675           hx += cursorPos;
1676         } else if (direction === 'up' && isTerminal) {
1677           hx += cursorPos;
1678         } else if (direction === 'down' && isTerminal) {
1679           hx += cursorPos;
1680         } else if (direction === 'up' && !isTerminal) {
1681           hy -= this.opts.fontSizeLarge + this.opts.quarterFontSizeLarge;
1682           hx -= this.halfHydrogenWidth;
1683         } else if (direction === 'down' && !isTerminal) {
1684           hy += this.opts.fontSizeLarge + this.opts.quarterFontSizeLarge;
1685           hx -= this.halfHydrogenWidth;
1686         }
1687   
1688         ctx.fillText('H', hx, hy);
1689         cursorPos += hydrogenWidth;
1690       } else if (hydrogens > 1) {
1691         let hx = x + offsetX;
1692         let hy = y + offsetY + this.opts.halfFontSizeLarge;
1693         hydrogenWidth = this.hydrogenWidth;
1694         ctx.font = this.fontSmall;
1695         hydrogenCountWidth = ctx.measureText(hydrogens).width;
1696         cursorPosLeft -= hydrogenWidth + hydrogenCountWidth;
1697   
1698         if (direction === 'left') {
1699           hx += cursorPosLeft;
1700         } else if (direction === 'right') {
1701           hx += cursorPos;
1702         } else if (direction === 'up' && isTerminal) {
1703           hx += cursorPos;
1704         } else if (direction === 'down' && isTerminal) {
1705           hx += cursorPos;
1706         } else if (direction === 'up' && !isTerminal) {
1707           hy -= this.opts.fontSizeLarge + this.opts.quarterFontSizeLarge;
1708           hx -= this.halfHydrogenWidth;
1709         } else if (direction === 'down' && !isTerminal) {
1710           hy += this.opts.fontSizeLarge + this.opts.quarterFontSizeLarge;
1711           hx -= this.halfHydrogenWidth;
1712         }
1713   
1714         ctx.font = this.fontLarge;
1715         ctx.fillText('H', hx, hy);
1716         ctx.font = this.fontSmall;
1717         ctx.fillText(hydrogens, hx + this.halfHydrogenWidth + hydrogenCountWidth, hy + this.opts.fifthFontSizeSmall);
1718         cursorPos += hydrogenWidth + this.halfHydrogenWidth + hydrogenCountWidth;
1719       }
1720   
1721       if (pseudoElementHandled) {
1722         ctx.restore();
1723         return;
1724       }
1725   
1726       for (let key in attachedPseudoElement) {
1727         if (!attachedPseudoElement.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
1728           continue;
1729         }
1730   
1731         let openParenthesisWidth = 0;
1732         let closeParenthesisWidth = 0;
1733         let element = attachedPseudoElement[key].element;
1734         let elementCount = attachedPseudoElement[key].count;
1735         let hydrogenCount = attachedPseudoElement[key].hydrogenCount;
1736         let elementCharge = attachedPseudoElement[key].charge;
1737         ctx.font = this.fontLarge;
1738   
1739         if (elementCount > 1 && hydrogenCount > 0) {
1740           openParenthesisWidth = ctx.measureText('(').width;
1741           closeParenthesisWidth = ctx.measureText(')').width;
1742         }
1743   
1744         let elementWidth = ctx.measureText(element).width;
1745         let elementCountWidth = 0;
1746         let elementChargeText = '';
1747         let elementChargeWidth = 0;
1748         hydrogenWidth = 0;
1749   
1750         if (hydrogenCount > 0) {
1751           hydrogenWidth = this.hydrogenWidth;
1752         }
1753   
1754         ctx.font = this.fontSmall;
1755   
1756         if (elementCount > 1) {
1757           elementCountWidth = ctx.measureText(elementCount).width;
1758         }
1759   
1760         if (elementCharge !== 0) {
1761           elementChargeText = getChargeText(elementCharge);
1762           elementChargeWidth = ctx.measureText(elementChargeText).width;
1763         }
1764   
1765         hydrogenCountWidth = 0;
1766   
1767         if (hydrogenCount > 1) {
1768           hydrogenCountWidth = ctx.measureText(hydrogenCount).width;
1769         }
1770   
1771         ctx.font = this.fontLarge;
1772         let hx = x + offsetX;
1773         let hy = y + offsetY + this.opts.halfFontSizeLarge;
1774         ctx.fillStyle = this.themeManager.getColor(element);
1775   
1776         if (elementCount > 0) {
1777           cursorPosLeft -= elementCountWidth;
1778         }
1779   
1780         if (elementCount > 1 && hydrogenCount > 0) {
1781           if (direction === 'left') {
1782             cursorPosLeft -= closeParenthesisWidth;
1783             ctx.fillText(')', hx + cursorPosLeft, hy);
1784           } else {
1785             ctx.fillText('(', hx + cursorPos, hy);
1786             cursorPos += openParenthesisWidth;
1787           }
1788         }
1789   
1790         if (direction === 'left') {
1791           cursorPosLeft -= elementWidth;
1792           ctx.fillText(element, hx + cursorPosLeft, hy);
1793         } else {
1794           ctx.fillText(element, hx + cursorPos, hy);
1795           cursorPos += elementWidth;
1796         }
1797   
1798         if (hydrogenCount > 0) {
1799           if (direction === 'left') {
1800             cursorPosLeft -= hydrogenWidth + hydrogenCountWidth;
1801             ctx.fillText('H', hx + cursorPosLeft, hy);
1802   
1803             if (hydrogenCount > 1) {
1804               ctx.font = this.fontSmall;
1805               ctx.fillText(hydrogenCount, hx + cursorPosLeft + hydrogenWidth, hy + this.opts.fifthFontSizeSmall);
1806             }
1807           } else {
1808             ctx.fillText('H', hx + cursorPos, hy);
1809             cursorPos += hydrogenWidth;
1810   
1811             if (hydrogenCount > 1) {
1812               ctx.font = this.fontSmall;
1813               ctx.fillText(hydrogenCount, hx + cursorPos, hy + this.opts.fifthFontSizeSmall);
1814               cursorPos += hydrogenCountWidth;
1815             }
1816           }
1817         }
1818   
1819         ctx.font = this.fontLarge;
1820   
1821         if (elementCount > 1 && hydrogenCount > 0) {
1822           if (direction === 'left') {
1823             cursorPosLeft -= openParenthesisWidth;
1824             ctx.fillText('(', hx + cursorPosLeft, hy);
1825           } else {
1826             ctx.fillText(')', hx + cursorPos, hy);
1827             cursorPos += closeParenthesisWidth;
1828           }
1829         }
1830   
1831         ctx.font = this.fontSmall;
1832   
1833         if (elementCount > 1) {
1834           if (direction === 'left') {
1835             ctx.fillText(elementCount, hx + cursorPosLeft + openParenthesisWidth + closeParenthesisWidth + hydrogenWidth + hydrogenCountWidth + elementWidth, hy + this.opts.fifthFontSizeSmall);
1836           } else {
1837             ctx.fillText(elementCount, hx + cursorPos, hy + this.opts.fifthFontSizeSmall);
1838             cursorPos += elementCountWidth;
1839           }
1840         }
1841   
1842         if (elementCharge !== 0) {
1843           if (direction === 'left') {
1844             ctx.fillText(elementChargeText, hx + cursorPosLeft + openParenthesisWidth + closeParenthesisWidth + hydrogenWidth + hydrogenCountWidth + elementWidth, y - this.opts.fifthFontSizeSmall + offsetY);
1845           } else {
1846             ctx.fillText(elementChargeText, hx + cursorPos, y - this.opts.fifthFontSizeSmall + offsetY);
1847             cursorPos += elementChargeWidth;
1848           }
1849         }
1850       }
1851   
1852       ctx.restore();
1853     }
1854     /**
1855      * Translate the integer indicating the charge to the appropriate text.
1856      * @param {Number} charge The integer indicating the charge.
1857      * @returns {String} A string representing a charge.
1858      */
1859   
1860   
1861     getChargeText(charge) {
1862       if (charge === 1) {
1863         return '+';
1864       } else if (charge === 2) {
1865         return '2+';
1866       } else if (charge === -1) {
1867         return '-';
1868       } else if (charge === -2) {
1869         return '2-';
1870       } else {
1871         return '';
1872       }
1873     }
1874     /**
1875      * Draws a dubug dot at a given coordinate and adds text.
1876      *
1877      * @param {Number} x The x coordinate.
1878      * @param {Number} y The y coordindate.
1879      * @param {String} [debugText=''] A string.
1880      * @param {String} [color='#f00'] A color in hex form.
1881      */
1882   
1883   
1884     drawDebugPoint(x, y, debugText = '', color = '#f00') {
1885       this.drawCircle(x, y, 2, color, true, true, debugText);
1886     }
1887     /**
1888      * Draws a ring inside a provided ring, indicating aromaticity.
1889      *
1890      * @param {Ring} ring A ring.
1891      */
1892   
1893   
1894     drawAromaticityRing(ring) {
1895       let ctx = this.ctx;
1896       let radius = MathHelper.apothemFromSideLength(this.opts.bondLength, ring.getSize());
1897       ctx.save();
1898       ctx.strokeStyle = this.themeManager.getColor('C');
1899       ctx.lineWidth = this.opts.bondThickness;
1900       ctx.beginPath();
1901       ctx.arc(ring.center.x + this.offsetX, ring.center.y + this.offsetY, radius - this.opts.bondSpacing, 0, Math.PI * 2, true);
1902       ctx.closePath();
1903       ctx.stroke();
1904       ctx.restore();
1905     }
1906     /**
1907      * Clear the canvas.
1908      *
1909      */
1910   
1911   
1912     clear() {
1913       this.ctx.clearRect(0, 0, this.canvas.offsetWidth, this.canvas.offsetHeight);
1914     }
1915   
1916   }

2023             BR: '#d35400',
2024             I: '#8e44ad',
2025             P: '#d35400',
2026             S: '#f1c40f',
2027             B: '#e67e22',
2028             SI: '#e67e22',
2029             H: '#222',
2030             BACKGROUND: '#fff'
2031           }
2032         }
2033       };
2034       this.opts = this.extend(true, this.defaultOptions, options);
2035       this.opts.halfBondSpacing = this.opts.bondSpacing / 2.0;
2036       this.opts.bondLengthSq = this.opts.bondLength * this.opts.bondLength;
2037       this.opts.halfFontSizeLarge = this.opts.fontSizeLarge / 2.0;
2038       this.opts.quarterFontSizeLarge = this.opts.fontSizeLarge / 4.0;
2039       this.opts.fifthFontSizeSmall = this.opts.fontSizeSmall / 5.0; // Set the default theme.
2040   
2041       this.theme = this.opts.themes.dark;
2042     }
2043     /**
2044      * A helper method to extend the default options with user supplied ones.
2045      */
2046   
2047   
2048     extend() {
2049       let that = this;
2050       let extended = {};
2051       let deep = false;
2052       let i = 0;
2053       let length = arguments.length;
2054   
2055       if (Object.prototype.toString.call(arguments[0]) === '[object Boolean]') {
2056         deep = arguments[0];
2057         i++;
2058       }
2059   
2060       let merge = function (obj) {
2061         for (var prop in obj) {
2062           if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(obj, prop)) {
2063             if (deep && Object.prototype.toString.call(obj[prop]) === '[object Object]') {
2064               extended[prop] = that.extend(true, extended[prop], obj[prop]);
2065             } else {
2066               extended[prop] = obj[prop];
2067             }
2068           }
2069         }
2070       };
2071   
2072       for (; i < length; i++) {
2073         let obj = arguments[i];
2074         merge(obj);
2075       }
2076   
2077       return extended;
2078     }

2080     /**
2081      * Draws the parsed smiles data to a canvas element.
2082      *
2083      * @param {Object} data The tree returned by the smiles parser.
2084      * @param {(String|HTMLElement)} target The id of the HTML canvas element the structure is drawn to - or the element itself.
2085      * @param {String} themeName='dark' The name of the theme to use. Built-in themes are 'light' and 'dark'.
2086      * @param {Boolean} infoOnly=false Only output info on the molecule without drawing anything to the canvas.
2087      */
2088     draw(data, target, themeName = 'light', infoOnly = false) {
2089       this.initDraw(data, themeName, infoOnly);
2090   
2091       if (!this.infoOnly) {
2092         this.themeManager = new ThemeManager(this.opts.themes, themeName);
2093         this.canvasWrapper = new CanvasWrapper(target, this.themeManager, this.opts);
2094       }
2095   
2096       if (!infoOnly) {
2097         this.processGraph(); // Set the canvas to the appropriate size
2098   
2099         this.canvasWrapper.scale(this.graph.vertices); // Do the actual drawing
2100   
2101         this.drawEdges(this.opts.debug);
2102         this.drawVertices(this.opts.debug);
2103         this.canvasWrapper.reset();
2104   
2105         if (this.opts.debug) {
2106           console.log(this.graph);
2107           console.log(this.rings);
2108           console.log(this.ringConnections);
2109         }
2110       }
2111     }
2112     /**
2113      * Returns the number of rings this edge is a part of.
2114      *
2115      * @param {Number} edgeId The id of an edge.
2116      * @returns {Number} The number of rings the provided edge is part of.
2117      */
2118   
2119   
2120     edgeRingCount(edgeId) {
2121       let edge = this.graph.edges[edgeId];
2122       let a = this.graph.vertices[edge.sourceId];
2123       let b = this.graph.vertices[edge.targetId];
2124       return Math.min(a.value.rings.length, b.value.rings.length);
2125     }

2180     /**
2181      * Returns a string containing a semicolon and new-line separated list of ring properties: Id; Members Count; Neighbours Count; IsSpiro; IsFused; IsBridged; Ring Count (subrings of bridged rings)
2182      *
2183      * @returns {String} A string as described in the method description.
2184      */
2185   
2186   
2187     printRingInfo() {
2188       let result = '';
2189   
2190       for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
2191         const ring = this.rings[i];
2192         result += ring.id + ';';
2193         result += ring.members.length + ';';
2194         result += ring.neighbours.length + ';';
2195         result += ring.isSpiro ? 'true;' : 'false;';
2196         result += ring.isFused ? 'true;' : 'false;';
2197         result += ring.isBridged ? 'true;' : 'false;';
2198         result += ring.rings.length + ';';
2199         result += '\n';
2200       }
2201   
2202       return result;
2203     }
2204     /**
2205      * Rotates the drawing to make the widest dimension horizontal.
2206      */
2207   
2208   
2209     rotateDrawing() {
2210       // Rotate the vertices to make the molecule align horizontally
2211       // Find the longest distance
2212       let a = 0;
2213       let b = 0;
2214       let maxDist = 0;
2215   
2216       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
2217         let vertexA = this.graph.vertices[i];
2218   
2219         if (!vertexA.value.isDrawn) {
2220           continue;
2221         }
2222   
2223         for (var j = i + 1; j < this.graph.vertices.length; j++) {
2224           let vertexB = this.graph.vertices[j];
2225   
2226           if (!vertexB.value.isDrawn) {
2227             continue;
2228           }
2229   
2230           let dist = vertexA.position.distanceSq(vertexB.position);
2231   
2232           if (dist > maxDist) {
2233             maxDist = dist;
2234             a = i;
2235             b = j;
2236           }
2237         }
2238       }
2239   
2240       let angle = -Vector2.subtract(this.graph.vertices[a].position, this.graph.vertices[b].position).angle();
2241   
2242       if (!isNaN(angle)) {
2243         // Round to 30 degrees
2244         let remainder = angle % 0.523599; // Round either up or down in 30 degree steps
2245   
2246         if (remainder < 0.2617995) {
2247           angle = angle - remainder;
2248         } else {
2249           angle += 0.523599 - remainder;
2250         } // Finally, rotate everything
2251   
2252   
2253         for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
2254           if (i === b) {
2255             continue;
2256           }
2257   
2258           this.graph.vertices[i].position.rotateAround(angle, this.graph.vertices[b].position);
2259         }
2260   
2261         for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
2262           this.rings[i].center.rotateAround(angle, this.graph.vertices[b].position);
2263         }
2264       }
2265     }

2270      */

2272

2274       return this.totalOverlapScore;
2275     }
