2296     /**
2297      * Returns the number of heavy atoms (non-hydrogen) in the current molecule.
2298      *
2299      * @returns {Number} The heavy atom count.
2300      */
2301   
2302   
2303     getHeavyAtomCount() {
2304       let hac = 0;
2305   
2306       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
2307         if (this.graph.vertices[i].value.element !== 'H') {
2308           hac++;
2309         }
2310       }
2311   
2312       return hac;
2313     }
2314     /**
2315      * Returns the molecular formula of the loaded molecule as a string.
2316      * 
2317      * @returns {String} The molecular formula.
2318      */
2319   
2320   
2321     getMolecularFormula() {
2322       let molecularFormula = '';
2323       let counts = new Map(); // Initialize element count
2324   
2325       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
2326         let atom = this.graph.vertices[i].value;
2327   
2328         if (counts.has(atom.element)) {
2329           counts.set(atom.element, counts.get(atom.element) + 1);
2330         } else {
2331           counts.set(atom.element, 1);
2332         } // Hydrogens attached to a chiral center were added as vertices,
2333         // those in non chiral brackets are added here
2334   
2335   
2336         if (atom.bracket && !atom.bracket.chirality) {
2337           if (counts.has('H')) {
2338             counts.set('H', counts.get('H') + atom.bracket.hcount);
2339           } else {
2340             counts.set('H', atom.bracket.hcount);
2341           }
2342         } // Add the implicit hydrogens according to valency, exclude
2343         // bracket atoms as they were handled and always have the number
2344         // of hydrogens specified explicitly
2345   
2346   
2347         if (!atom.bracket) {
2348           let nHydrogens = Atom.maxBonds[atom.element] - atom.bondCount;
2349   
2350           if (atom.isPartOfAromaticRing) {
2351             nHydrogens--;
2352           }
2353   
2354           if (counts.has('H')) {
2355             counts.set('H', counts.get('H') + nHydrogens);
2356           } else {
2357             counts.set('H', nHydrogens);
2358           }
2359         }
2360       }
2361   
2362       if (counts.has('C')) {
2363         let count = counts.get('C');
2364         molecularFormula += 'C' + (count > 1 ? count : '');
2365         counts.delete('C');
2366       }
2367   
2368       if (counts.has('H')) {
2369         let count = counts.get('H');
2370         molecularFormula += 'H' + (count > 1 ? count : '');
2371         counts.delete('H');
2372       }
2373   
2374       let elements = Object.keys(Atom.atomicNumbers).sort();
2375       elements.map(e => {
2376         if (counts.has(e)) {
2377           let count = counts.get(e);
2378           molecularFormula += e + (count > 1 ? count : '');
2379         }
2380       });
2381       return molecularFormula;
2382     }
2383     /**
2384      * Returns the type of the ringbond (e.g. '=' for a double bond). The ringbond represents the break in a ring introduced when creating the MST. If the two vertices supplied as arguments are not part of a common ringbond, the method returns null.
2385      *
2386      * @param {Vertex} vertexA A vertex.
2387      * @param {Vertex} vertexB A vertex.
2388      * @returns {(String|null)} Returns the ringbond type or null, if the two supplied vertices are not connected by a ringbond.
2389      */
2390   
2391   
2392     getRingbondType(vertexA, vertexB) {
2393       // Checks whether the two vertices are the ones connecting the ring
2394       // and what the bond type should be.
2395       if (vertexA.value.getRingbondCount() < 1 || vertexB.value.getRingbondCount() < 1) {
2396         return null;
2397       }
2398   
2399       for (var i = 0; i < vertexA.value.ringbonds.length; i++) {
2400         for (var j = 0; j < vertexB.value.ringbonds.length; j++) {
2401           // if(i != j) continue;
2402           if (vertexA.value.ringbonds[i].id === vertexB.value.ringbonds[j].id) {
2403             // If the bonds are equal, it doesn't matter which bond is returned.
2404             // if they are not equal, return the one that is not the default ("-")
2405             if (vertexA.value.ringbonds[i].bondType === '-') {
2406               return vertexB.value.ringbonds[j].bond;
2407             } else {
2408               return vertexA.value.ringbonds[i].bond;
2409             }
2410           }
2411         }
2412       }
2413   
2414       return null;
2415     }
2416   
2417     initDraw(data, themeName, infoOnly) {
2418       this.data = data;
2419       this.infoOnly = infoOnly;
2420       this.ringIdCounter = 0;
2421       this.ringConnectionIdCounter = 0;
2422       this.graph = new Graph(data, this.opts.isomeric);
2423       this.rings = Array();
2424       this.ringConnections = Array();
2425       this.originalRings = Array();
2426       this.originalRingConnections = Array();
2427       this.bridgedRing = false; // Reset those, in case the previous drawn SMILES had a dangling \ or /
2428   
2429       this.doubleBondConfigCount = null;
2430       this.doubleBondConfig = null;
2431       this.initRings();
2432       this.initHydrogens();
2433     }
2434   
2435     processGraph() {
2436       this.position(); // Restore the ring information (removes bridged rings and replaces them with the original, multiple, rings)
2437   
2438       this.restoreRingInformation(); // Atoms bonded to the same ring atom
2439   
2440       this.resolvePrimaryOverlaps();
2441       let overlapScore = this.getOverlapScore();
2442       this.totalOverlapScore = this.getOverlapScore().total;
2443   
2444       for (var o = 0; o < this.opts.overlapResolutionIterations; o++) {
2445         for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.edges.length; i++) {
2446           let edge = this.graph.edges[i];
2447   
2448           if (this.isEdgeRotatable(edge)) {
2449             let subTreeDepthA = this.graph.getTreeDepth(edge.sourceId, edge.targetId);
2450             let subTreeDepthB = this.graph.getTreeDepth(edge.targetId, edge.sourceId); // Only rotate the shorter subtree
2451   
2452             let a = edge.targetId;
2453             let b = edge.sourceId;
2454   
2455             if (subTreeDepthA > subTreeDepthB) {
2456               a = edge.sourceId;
2457               b = edge.targetId;
2458             }
2459   
2460             let subTreeOverlap = this.getSubtreeOverlapScore(b, a, overlapScore.vertexScores);
2461   
2462             if (subTreeOverlap.value > this.opts.overlapSensitivity) {
2463               let vertexA = this.graph.vertices[a];
2464               let vertexB = this.graph.vertices[b];
2465               let neighboursB = vertexB.getNeighbours(a);
2466   
2467               if (neighboursB.length === 1) {
2468                 let neighbour = this.graph.vertices[neighboursB[0]];
2469                 let angle = neighbour.position.getRotateAwayFromAngle(vertexA.position, vertexB.position, MathHelper.toRad(120));
2470                 this.rotateSubtree(neighbour.id, vertexB.id, angle, vertexB.position); // If the new overlap is bigger, undo change
2471   
2472                 let newTotalOverlapScore = this.getOverlapScore().total;
2473   
2474                 if (newTotalOverlapScore > this.totalOverlapScore) {
2475                   this.rotateSubtree(neighbour.id, vertexB.id, -angle, vertexB.position);
2476                 } else {
2477                   this.totalOverlapScore = newTotalOverlapScore;
2478                 }
2479               } else if (neighboursB.length === 2) {
2480                 // Switch places / sides
2481                 // If vertex a is in a ring, do nothing
2482                 if (vertexB.value.rings.length !== 0 && vertexA.value.rings.length !== 0) {
2483                   continue;
2484                 }
2485   
2486                 let neighbourA = this.graph.vertices[neighboursB[0]];
2487                 let neighbourB = this.graph.vertices[neighboursB[1]];
2488   
2489                 if (neighbourA.value.rings.length === 1 && neighbourB.value.rings.length === 1) {
2490                   // Both neighbours in same ring. TODO: does this create problems with wedges? (up = down and vice versa?)
2491                   if (neighbourA.value.rings[0] !== neighbourB.value.rings[0]) {
2492                     continue;
2493                   } // TODO: Rotate circle
2494   
2495                 } else if (neighbourA.value.rings.length !== 0 || neighbourB.value.rings.length !== 0) {
2496                   continue;
2497                 } else {
2498                   let angleA = neighbourA.position.getRotateAwayFromAngle(vertexA.position, vertexB.position, MathHelper.toRad(120));
2499                   let angleB = neighbourB.position.getRotateAwayFromAngle(vertexA.position, vertexB.position, MathHelper.toRad(120));
2500                   this.rotateSubtree(neighbourA.id, vertexB.id, angleA, vertexB.position);
2501                   this.rotateSubtree(neighbourB.id, vertexB.id, angleB, vertexB.position);
2502                   let newTotalOverlapScore = this.getOverlapScore().total;
2503   
2504                   if (newTotalOverlapScore > this.totalOverlapScore) {
2505                     this.rotateSubtree(neighbourA.id, vertexB.id, -angleA, vertexB.position);
2506                     this.rotateSubtree(neighbourB.id, vertexB.id, -angleB, vertexB.position);
2507                   } else {
2508                     this.totalOverlapScore = newTotalOverlapScore;
2509                   }
2510                 }
2511               }
2512   
2513               overlapScore = this.getOverlapScore();
2514             }
2515           }
2516         }
2517       }
2518   
2519       this.resolveSecondaryOverlaps(overlapScore.scores);
2520   
2521       if (this.opts.isomeric) {
2522         this.annotateStereochemistry();
2523       } // Initialize pseudo elements or shortcuts
2524   
2525   
2526       if (this.opts.compactDrawing && this.opts.atomVisualization === 'default') {
2527         this.initPseudoElements();
2528       }
2529   
2530       this.rotateDrawing();
2531     }
2532     /**
2533      * Initializes rings and ringbonds for the current molecule.
2534      */
2535   
2536   
2537     initRings() {
2538       let openBonds = new Map(); // Close the open ring bonds (spanning tree -> graph)
2539   
2540       for (var i = this.graph.vertices.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
2541         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[i];
2542   
2543         if (vertex.value.ringbonds.length === 0) {
2544           continue;
2545         }
2546   
2547         for (var j = 0; j < vertex.value.ringbonds.length; j++) {
2548           let ringbondId = vertex.value.ringbonds[j].id;
2549           let ringbondBond = vertex.value.ringbonds[j].bond; // If the other ringbond id has not been discovered,
2550           // add it to the open bonds map and continue.
2551           // if the other ringbond id has already been discovered,
2552           // create a bond between the two atoms.
2553   
2554           if (!openBonds.has(ringbondId)) {
2555             openBonds.set(ringbondId, [vertex.id, ringbondBond]);
2556           } else {
2557             let sourceVertexId = vertex.id;
2558             let targetVertexId = openBonds.get(ringbondId)[0];
2559             let targetRingbondBond = openBonds.get(ringbondId)[1];
2560             let edge = new Edge(sourceVertexId, targetVertexId, 1);
2561             edge.setBondType(targetRingbondBond || ringbondBond || '-');
2562             let edgeId = this.graph.addEdge(edge);
2563             let targetVertex = this.graph.vertices[targetVertexId];
2564             vertex.addRingbondChild(targetVertexId, j);
2565             vertex.value.addNeighbouringElement(targetVertex.value.element);
2566             targetVertex.addRingbondChild(sourceVertexId, j);
2567             targetVertex.value.addNeighbouringElement(vertex.value.element);
2568             vertex.edges.push(edgeId);
2569             targetVertex.edges.push(edgeId);
2570             openBonds.delete(ringbondId);
2571           }
2572         }
2573       } // Get the rings in the graph (the SSSR)
2574   
2575   
2576       let rings = SSSR.getRings(this.graph, this.opts.experimentalSSSR);
2577   
2578       if (rings === null) {
2579         return;
2580       }
2581   
2582       for (var i = 0; i < rings.length; i++) {
2583         let ringVertices = [...rings[i]];
2584         let ringId = this.addRing(new Ring(ringVertices)); // Add the ring to the atoms
2585   
2586         for (var j = 0; j < ringVertices.length; j++) {
2587           this.graph.vertices[ringVertices[j]].value.rings.push(ringId);
2588         }
2589       } // Find connection between rings
2590       // Check for common vertices and create ring connections. This is a bit
2591       // ugly, but the ringcount is always fairly low (< 100)
2592   
2593   
2594       for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length - 1; i++) {
2595         for (var j = i + 1; j < this.rings.length; j++) {
2596           let a = this.rings[i];
2597           let b = this.rings[j];
2598           let ringConnection = new RingConnection(a, b); // If there are no vertices in the ring connection, then there
2599           // is no ring connection
2600   
2601           if (ringConnection.vertices.size > 0) {
2602             this.addRingConnection(ringConnection);
2603           }
2604         }
2605       } // Add neighbours to the rings
2606   
2607   
2608       for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
2609         let ring = this.rings[i];
2610         ring.neighbours = RingConnection.getNeighbours(this.ringConnections, ring.id);
2611       } // Anchor the ring to one of it's members, so that the ring center will always
2612       // be tied to a single vertex when doing repositionings
2613   
2614   
2615       for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
2616         let ring = this.rings[i];
2617         this.graph.vertices[ring.members[0]].value.addAnchoredRing(ring.id);
2618       } // Backup the ring information to restore after placing the bridged ring.
2619       // This is needed in order to identify aromatic rings and stuff like this in
2620       // rings that are member of the superring.
2621   
2622   
2623       this.backupRingInformation(); // Replace rings contained by a larger bridged ring with a bridged ring
2624   
2625       while (this.rings.length > 0) {
2626         let id = -1;
2627   
2628         for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
2629           let ring = this.rings[i];
2630   
2631           if (this.isPartOfBridgedRing(ring.id) && !ring.isBridged) {
2632             id = ring.id;
2633           }
2634         }
2635   
2636         if (id === -1) {
2637           break;
2638         }
2639   
2640         let ring = this.getRing(id);
2641         let involvedRings = this.getBridgedRingRings(ring.id);
2642         this.bridgedRing = true;
2643         this.createBridgedRing(involvedRings, ring.members[0]); // Remove the rings
2644   
2645         for (var i = 0; i < involvedRings.length; i++) {
2646           this.removeRing(involvedRings[i]);
2647         }
2648       }
2649     }
2650   
2651     initHydrogens() {
2652       // Do not draw hydrogens except when they are connected to a stereocenter connected to two or more rings.
2653       if (!this.opts.explicitHydrogens) {
2654         for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
2655           let vertex = this.graph.vertices[i];
2656   
2657           if (vertex.value.element !== 'H') {
2658             continue;
2659           } // Hydrogens should have only one neighbour, so just take the first
2660           // Also set hasHydrogen true on connected atom
2661   
2662   
2663           let neighbour = this.graph.vertices[vertex.neighbours[0]];
2664           neighbour.value.hasHydrogen = true;
2665   
2666           if (!neighbour.value.isStereoCenter || neighbour.value.rings.length < 2 && !neighbour.value.bridgedRing || neighbour.value.bridgedRing && neighbour.value.originalRings.length < 2) {
2667             vertex.value.isDrawn = false;
2668           }
2669         }
2670       }
2671     }
2672     /**
2673      * Returns all rings connected by bridged bonds starting from the ring with the supplied ring id.
2674      *
2675      * @param {Number} ringId A ring id.
2676      * @returns {Number[]} An array containing all ring ids of rings part of a bridged ring system.
2677      */
2678   
2679   
2680     getBridgedRingRings(ringId) {
2681       let involvedRings = Array();
2682       let that = this;
2683   
2684       let recurse = function (r) {
2685         let ring = that.getRing(r);
2686         involvedRings.push(r);
2687   
2688         for (var i = 0; i < ring.neighbours.length; i++) {
2689           let n = ring.neighbours[i];
2690   
2691           if (involvedRings.indexOf(n) === -1 && n !== r && RingConnection.isBridge(that.ringConnections, that.graph.vertices, r, n)) {
2692             recurse(n);
2693           }
2694         }
2695       };
2696   
2697       recurse(ringId);
2698       return ArrayHelper.unique(involvedRings);
2699     }
2700     /**
2701      * Checks whether or not a ring is part of a bridged ring.
2702      *
2703      * @param {Number} ringId A ring id.
2704      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not the supplied ring (by id) is part of a bridged ring system.
2705      */
2706   
2707   
2708     isPartOfBridgedRing(ringId) {
2709       for (var i = 0; i < this.ringConnections.length; i++) {
2710         if (this.ringConnections[i].containsRing(ringId) && this.ringConnections[i].isBridge(this.graph.vertices)) {
2711           return true;
2712         }
2713       }
2714   
2715       return false;
2716     }
2717     /**
2718      * Creates a bridged ring.
2719      *
2720      * @param {Number[]} ringIds An array of ids of rings involved in the bridged ring.
2721      * @param {Number} sourceVertexId The vertex id to start the bridged ring discovery from.
2722      * @returns {Ring} The bridged ring.
2723      */
2724   
2725   
2726     createBridgedRing(ringIds, sourceVertexId) {
2727       let ringMembers = new Set();
2728       let vertices = new Set();
2729       let neighbours = new Set();
2730   
2731       for (var i = 0; i < ringIds.length; i++) {
2732         let ring = this.getRing(ringIds[i]);
2733         ring.isPartOfBridged = true;
2734   
2735         for (var j = 0; j < ring.members.length; j++) {
2736           vertices.add(ring.members[j]);
2737         }
2738   
2739         for (var j = 0; j < ring.neighbours.length; j++) {
2740           let id = ring.neighbours[j];
2741   
2742           if (ringIds.indexOf(id) === -1) {
2743             neighbours.add(ring.neighbours[j]);
2744           }
2745         }
2746       } // A vertex is part of the bridged ring if it only belongs to
2747       // one of the rings (or to another ring
2748       // which is not part of the bridged ring).
2749   
2750   
2751       let leftovers = new Set();
2752   
2753       for (let id of vertices) {
2754         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[id];
2755         let intersection = ArrayHelper.intersection(ringIds, vertex.value.rings);
2756   
2757         if (vertex.value.rings.length === 1 || intersection.length === 1) {
2758           ringMembers.add(vertex.id);
2759         } else {
2760           leftovers.add(vertex.id);
2761         }
2762       } // Vertices can also be part of multiple rings and lay on the bridged ring,
2763       // however, they have to have at least two neighbours that are not part of
2764       // two rings
2765   
2766   
2767       let tmp = Array();
2768       let insideRing = Array();
2769   
2770       for (let id of leftovers) {
2771         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[id];
2772         let onRing = false;
2773   
2774         for (let j = 0; j < vertex.edges.length; j++) {
2775           if (this.edgeRingCount(vertex.edges[j]) === 1) {
2776             onRing = true;
2777           }
2778         }
2779   
2780         if (onRing) {
2781           vertex.value.isBridgeNode = true;
2782           ringMembers.add(vertex.id);
2783         } else {
2784           vertex.value.isBridge = true;
2785           ringMembers.add(vertex.id);
2786         }
2787       } // Create the ring
2788   
2789   
2790       let ring = new Ring([...ringMembers]);
2791       this.addRing(ring);
2792       ring.isBridged = true;
2793       ring.neighbours = [...neighbours];
2794   
2795       for (var i = 0; i < ringIds.length; i++) {
2796         ring.rings.push(this.getRing(ringIds[i]).clone());
2797       }
2798   
2799       for (var i = 0; i < ring.members.length; i++) {
2800         this.graph.vertices[ring.members[i]].value.bridgedRing = ring.id;
2801       } // Atoms inside the ring are no longer part of a ring but are now
2802       // associated with the bridged ring
2803   
2804   
2805       for (var i = 0; i < insideRing.length; i++) {
2806         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[insideRing[i]];
2807         vertex.value.rings = Array();
2808       } // Remove former rings from members of the bridged ring and add the bridged ring
2809   
2810   
2811       for (let id of ringMembers) {
2812         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[id];
2813         vertex.value.rings = ArrayHelper.removeAll(vertex.value.rings, ringIds);
2814         vertex.value.rings.push(ring.id);
2815       } // Remove all the ring connections no longer used
2816   
2817   
2818       for (var i = 0; i < ringIds.length; i++) {
2819         for (var j = i + 1; j < ringIds.length; j++) {
2820           this.removeRingConnectionsBetween(ringIds[i], ringIds[j]);
2821         }
2822       } // Update the ring connections and add this ring to the neighbours neighbours
2823   
2824   
2825       for (let id of neighbours) {
2826         let connections = this.getRingConnections(id, ringIds);
2827   
2828         for (var j = 0; j < connections.length; j++) {
2829           this.getRingConnection(connections[j]).updateOther(ring.id, id);
2830         }
2831   
2832         this.getRing(id).neighbours.push(ring.id);
2833       }
2834   
2835       return ring;
2836     }
2837     /**
2838      * Checks whether or not two vertices are in the same ring.
2839      *
2840      * @param {Vertex} vertexA A vertex.
2841      * @param {Vertex} vertexB A vertex.
2842      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not the two vertices are in the same ring.
2843      */
2844   
2845   
2846     areVerticesInSameRing(vertexA, vertexB) {
2847       // This is a little bit lighter (without the array and push) than
2848       // getCommonRings().length > 0
2849       for (var i = 0; i < vertexA.value.rings.length; i++) {
2850         for (var j = 0; j < vertexB.value.rings.length; j++) {
2851           if (vertexA.value.rings[i] === vertexB.value.rings[j]) {
2852             return true;
2853           }
2854         }
2855       }
2856   
2857       return false;
2858     }
2859     /**
2860      * Returns an array of ring ids shared by both vertices.
2861      *
2862      * @param {Vertex} vertexA A vertex.
2863      * @param {Vertex} vertexB A vertex.
2864      * @returns {Number[]} An array of ids of rings shared by the two vertices.
2865      */
2866   
2867   
2868     getCommonRings(vertexA, vertexB) {
2869       let commonRings = Array();
2870   
2871       for (var i = 0; i < vertexA.value.rings.length; i++) {
2872         for (var j = 0; j < vertexB.value.rings.length; j++) {
2873           if (vertexA.value.rings[i] == vertexB.value.rings[j]) {
2874             commonRings.push(vertexA.value.rings[i]);
2875           }
2876         }
2877       }
2878   
2879       return commonRings;
2880     }
2881     /**
2882      * Returns the aromatic or largest ring shared by the two vertices.
2883      *
2884      * @param {Vertex} vertexA A vertex.
2885      * @param {Vertex} vertexB A vertex.
2886      * @returns {(Ring|null)} If an aromatic common ring exists, that ring, else the largest (non-aromatic) ring, else null.
2887      */
2888   
2889   
2890     getLargestOrAromaticCommonRing(vertexA, vertexB) {
2891       let commonRings = this.getCommonRings(vertexA, vertexB);
2892       let maxSize = 0;
2893       let largestCommonRing = null;
2894   
2895       for (var i = 0; i < commonRings.length; i++) {
2896         let ring = this.getRing(commonRings[i]);
2897         let size = ring.getSize();
2898   
2899         if (ring.isBenzeneLike(this.graph.vertices)) {
2900           return ring;
2901         } else if (size > maxSize) {
2902           maxSize = size;
2903           largestCommonRing = ring;
2904         }
2905       }
2906   
2907       return largestCommonRing;
2908     }
2909     /**
2910      * Returns an array of vertices positioned at a specified location.
2911      *
2912      * @param {Vector2} position The position to search for vertices.
2913      * @param {Number} radius The radius within to search.
2914      * @param {Number} excludeVertexId A vertex id to be excluded from the search results.
2915      * @returns {Number[]} An array containing vertex ids in a given location.
2916      */
2917   
2918   
2919     getVerticesAt(position, radius, excludeVertexId) {
2920       let locals = Array();
2921   
2922       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
2923         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[i];
2924   
2925         if (vertex.id === excludeVertexId || !vertex.positioned) {
2926           continue;
2927         }
2928   
2929         let distance = position.distanceSq(vertex.position);
2930   
2931         if (distance <= radius * radius) {
2932           locals.push(vertex.id);
2933         }
2934       }
2935   
2936       return locals;
2937     }
2938     /**
2939      * Returns the closest vertex (connected as well as unconnected).
2940      *
2941      * @param {Vertex} vertex The vertex of which to find the closest other vertex.
2942      * @returns {Vertex} The closest vertex.
2943      */
2944   
2945   
2946     getClosestVertex(vertex) {
2947       let minDist = 99999;
2948       let minVertex = null;
2949   
2950       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
2951         let v = this.graph.vertices[i];
2952   
2953         if (v.id === vertex.id) {
2954           continue;
2955         }
2956   
2957         let distSq = vertex.position.distanceSq(v.position);
2958   
2959         if (distSq < minDist) {
2960           minDist = distSq;
2961           minVertex = v;
2962         }
2963       }
2964   
2965       return minVertex;
2966     }
2967     /**

2972      */

2980     /**
2981      * Removes a ring from the array of rings associated with the current molecule.
2982      *
2983      * @param {Number} ringId A ring id.
2984      */
2985   
2986   
2987     removeRing(ringId) {
2988       this.rings = this.rings.filter(function (item) {
2989         return item.id !== ringId;
2990       }); // Also remove ring connections involving this ring
2991   
2992       this.ringConnections = this.ringConnections.filter(function (item) {
2993         return item.firstRingId !== ringId && item.secondRingId !== ringId;
2994       }); // Remove the ring as neighbour of other rings
2995   
2996       for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
2997         let r = this.rings[i];
2998         r.neighbours = r.neighbours.filter(function (item) {
2999           return item !== ringId;
3000         });
3001       }
3002     }
3003     /**

3007      * @returns {Ring} A ring associated with the current molecule.

3009

3014           return this.rings[i];

3043     /**
3044      * Removes all ring connections between two vertices.
3045      *
3046      * @param {Number} vertexIdA A vertex id.
3047      * @param {Number} vertexIdB A vertex id.
3048      */
3049   
3050   
3051     removeRingConnectionsBetween(vertexIdA, vertexIdB) {
3052       let toRemove = Array();
3053

3055         let ringConnection = this.ringConnections[i];
3056   
3057         if (ringConnection.firstRingId === vertexIdA && ringConnection.secondRingId === vertexIdB || ringConnection.firstRingId === vertexIdB && ringConnection.secondRingId === vertexIdA) {
3058           toRemove.push(ringConnection.id);
3059         }
3060       }
3061   
3062       for (var i = 0; i < toRemove.length; i++) {
3063         this.removeRingConnection(toRemove[i]);
3064       }
3065     }

3081     /**
3082      * Get the ring connections between a ring and a set of rings.

3097           let id = ringIds[j];
3098   
3099           if (rc.firstRingId === ringId && rc.secondRingId === id || rc.firstRingId === id && rc.secondRingId === ringId) {
3100             ringConnections.push(rc.id);
3101           }
3102         }
3103       }
