3107     /**
3108      * Returns the overlap score of the current molecule based on its positioned vertices. The higher the score, the more overlaps occur in the structure drawing.
3109      *
3110      * @returns {Object} Returns the total overlap score and the overlap score of each vertex sorted by score (higher to lower). Example: { total: 99, scores: [ { id: 0, score: 22 }, ... ]  }
3111      */
3112   
3113   
3114     getOverlapScore() {
3115       let total = 0.0;
3116       let overlapScores = new Float32Array(this.graph.vertices.length);
3117   
3118       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
3119         overlapScores[i] = 0;
3120       }
3121   
3122       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
3123         var j = this.graph.vertices.length;
3124   
3125         while (--j > i) {
3126           let a = this.graph.vertices[i];
3127           let b = this.graph.vertices[j];
3128   
3129           if (!a.value.isDrawn || !b.value.isDrawn) {
3130             continue;
3131           }
3132   
3133           let dist = Vector2.subtract(a.position, b.position).lengthSq();
3134   
3135           if (dist < this.opts.bondLengthSq) {
3136             let weighted = (this.opts.bondLength - Math.sqrt(dist)) / this.opts.bondLength;
3137             total += weighted;
3138             overlapScores[i] += weighted;
3139             overlapScores[j] += weighted;
3140           }
3141         }
3142       }
3143   
3144       let sortable = Array();
3145   
3146       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
3147         sortable.push({
3148           id: i,
3149           score: overlapScores[i]
3150         });
3151       }
3152   
3153       sortable.sort(function (a, b) {
3154         return b.score - a.score;
3155       });
3156       return {
3157         total: total,
3158         scores: sortable,
3159         vertexScores: overlapScores
3160       };
3161     }
3162     /**
3163      * When drawing a double bond, choose the side to place the double bond. E.g. a double bond should always been drawn inside a ring.
3164      *
3165      * @param {Vertex} vertexA A vertex.
3166      * @param {Vertex} vertexB A vertex.
3167      * @param {Vector2[]} sides An array containing the two normals of the line spanned by the two provided vertices.
3168      * @returns {Object} Returns an object containing the following information: {
3169             totalSideCount: Counts the sides of each vertex in the molecule, is an array [ a, b ],
3170             totalPosition: Same as position, but based on entire molecule,
3171             sideCount: Counts the sides of each neighbour, is an array [ a, b ],
3172             position: which side to position the second bond, is 0 or 1, represents the index in the normal array. This is based on only the neighbours
3173             anCount: the number of neighbours of vertexA,
3174             bnCount: the number of neighbours of vertexB
3175         }
3176      */
3177   
3178   
3179     chooseSide(vertexA, vertexB, sides) {
3180       // Check which side has more vertices
3181       // Get all the vertices connected to the both ends
3182       let an = vertexA.getNeighbours(vertexB.id);
3183       let bn = vertexB.getNeighbours(vertexA.id);
3184       let anCount = an.length;
3185       let bnCount = bn.length; // All vertices connected to the edge vertexA to vertexB
3186   
3187       let tn = ArrayHelper.merge(an, bn); // Only considering the connected vertices
3188   
3189       let sideCount = [0, 0];
3190   
3191       for (var i = 0; i < tn.length; i++) {
3192         let v = this.graph.vertices[tn[i]].position;
3193   
3194         if (v.sameSideAs(vertexA.position, vertexB.position, sides[0])) {
3195           sideCount[0]++;
3196         } else {
3197           sideCount[1]++;
3198         }
3199       } // Considering all vertices in the graph, this is to resolve ties
3200       // from the above side counts
3201   
3202   
3203       let totalSideCount = [0, 0];
3204   
3205       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
3206         let v = this.graph.vertices[i].position;
3207   
3208         if (v.sameSideAs(vertexA.position, vertexB.position, sides[0])) {
3209           totalSideCount[0]++;
3210         } else {
3211           totalSideCount[1]++;
3212         }
3213       }
3214   
3215       return {
3216         totalSideCount: totalSideCount,
3217         totalPosition: totalSideCount[0] > totalSideCount[1] ? 0 : 1,
3218         sideCount: sideCount,
3219         position: sideCount[0] > sideCount[1] ? 0 : 1,
3220         anCount: anCount,
3221         bnCount: bnCount
3222       };
3223     }
3224     /**
3225      * Sets the center for a ring.
3226      *
3227      * @param {Ring} ring A ring.
3228      */
3229   
3230   
3231     setRingCenter(ring) {
3232       let ringSize = ring.getSize();
3233       let total = new Vector2(0, 0);
3234   
3235       for (var i = 0; i < ringSize; i++) {
3236         total.add(this.graph.vertices[ring.members[i]].position);
3237       }
3238   
3239       ring.center = total.divide(ringSize);
3240     }
3241     /**
3242      * Gets the center of a ring contained within a bridged ring and containing a given vertex.
3243      *
3244      * @param {Ring} ring A bridged ring.
3245      * @param {Vertex} vertex A vertex.
3246      * @returns {Vector2} The center of the subring that containing the vertex.
3247      */
3248   
3249   
3250     getSubringCenter(ring, vertex) {
3251       let rings = vertex.value.originalRings;
3252       let center = ring.center;
3253       let smallest = Number.MAX_VALUE; // Always get the smallest ring.
3254   
3255       for (var i = 0; i < rings.length; i++) {
3256         for (var j = 0; j < ring.rings.length; j++) {
3257           if (rings[i] === ring.rings[j].id) {
3258             if (ring.rings[j].getSize() < smallest) {
3259               center = ring.rings[j].center;
3260               smallest = ring.rings[j].getSize();
3261             }
3262           }
3263         }
3264       }
3265   
3266       return center;
3267     }
3268     /**
3269      * Draw the actual edges as bonds to the canvas.
3270      *
3271      * @param {Boolean} debug A boolean indicating whether or not to draw debug helpers.
3272      */
3273   
3274   
3275     drawEdges(debug) {
3276       let that = this;
3277       let drawn = Array(this.graph.edges.length);
3278       drawn.fill(false);
3279       this.graph.traverseBF(0, function (vertex) {
3280         let edges = that.graph.getEdges(vertex.id);
3281   
3282         for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
3283           let edgeId = edges[i];
3284   
3285           if (!drawn[edgeId]) {
3286             drawn[edgeId] = true;
3287             that.drawEdge(edgeId, debug);
3288           }
3289         }
3290       }); // Draw ring for implicitly defined aromatic rings
3291   
3292       if (!this.bridgedRing) {
3293         for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
3294           let ring = this.rings[i];
3295   
3296           if (this.isRingAromatic(ring)) {
3297             this.canvasWrapper.drawAromaticityRing(ring);
3298           }
3299         }
3300       }
3301     }
3302     /**
3303      * Draw the an edge as a bonds to the canvas.
3304      *
3305      * @param {Number} edgeId An edge id.
3306      * @param {Boolean} debug A boolean indicating whether or not to draw debug helpers.
3307      */
3308   
3309   
3310     drawEdge(edgeId, debug) {
3311       let that = this;
3312       let edge = this.graph.edges[edgeId];
3313       let vertexA = this.graph.vertices[edge.sourceId];
3314       let vertexB = this.graph.vertices[edge.targetId];
3315       let elementA = vertexA.value.element;
3316       let elementB = vertexB.value.element;
3317   
3318       if ((!vertexA.value.isDrawn || !vertexB.value.isDrawn) && this.opts.atomVisualization === 'default') {
3319         return;
3320       }
3321   
3322       let a = vertexA.position;
3323       let b = vertexB.position;
3324       let normals = this.getEdgeNormals(edge); // Create a point on each side of the line
3325   
3326       let sides = ArrayHelper.clone(normals);
3327       sides[0].multiplyScalar(10).add(a);
3328       sides[1].multiplyScalar(10).add(a);
3329   
3330       if (edge.bondType === '=' || this.getRingbondType(vertexA, vertexB) === '=' || edge.isPartOfAromaticRing && this.bridgedRing) {
3331         // Always draw double bonds inside the ring
3332         let inRing = this.areVerticesInSameRing(vertexA, vertexB);
3333         let s = this.chooseSide(vertexA, vertexB, sides);
3334   
3335         if (inRing) {
3336           // Always draw double bonds inside a ring
3337           // if the bond is shared by two rings, it is drawn in the larger
3338           // problem: smaller ring is aromatic, bond is still drawn in larger -> fix this
3339           let lcr = this.getLargestOrAromaticCommonRing(vertexA, vertexB);
3340           let center = lcr.center;
3341           normals[0].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing);
3342           normals[1].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing); // Choose the normal that is on the same side as the center
3343   
3344           let line = null;
3345   
3346           if (center.sameSideAs(vertexA.position, vertexB.position, Vector2.add(a, normals[0]))) {
3347             line = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[0]), Vector2.add(b, normals[0]), elementA, elementB);
3348           } else {
3349             line = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[1]), Vector2.add(b, normals[1]), elementA, elementB);
3350           }
3351   
3352           line.shorten(this.opts.bondLength - this.opts.shortBondLength * this.opts.bondLength); // The shortened edge
3353   
3354           if (edge.isPartOfAromaticRing) {
3355             this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(line, true);
3356           } else {
3357             this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(line);
3358           } // The normal edge
3359   
3360   
3361           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(new Line(a, b, elementA, elementB));
3362         } else if (edge.center || vertexA.isTerminal() && vertexB.isTerminal()) {
3363           normals[0].multiplyScalar(that.opts.halfBondSpacing);
3364           normals[1].multiplyScalar(that.opts.halfBondSpacing);
3365           let lineA = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[0]), Vector2.add(b, normals[0]), elementA, elementB);
3366           let lineB = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[1]), Vector2.add(b, normals[1]), elementA, elementB);
3367           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(lineA);
3368           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(lineB);
3369         } else if (s.anCount == 0 && s.bnCount > 1 || s.bnCount == 0 && s.anCount > 1) {
3370           // Both lines are the same length here
3371           // Add the spacing to the edges (which are of unit length)
3372           normals[0].multiplyScalar(that.opts.halfBondSpacing);
3373           normals[1].multiplyScalar(that.opts.halfBondSpacing);
3374           let lineA = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[0]), Vector2.add(b, normals[0]), elementA, elementB);
3375           let lineB = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[1]), Vector2.add(b, normals[1]), elementA, elementB);
3376           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(lineA);
3377           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(lineB);
3378         } else if (s.sideCount[0] > s.sideCount[1]) {
3379           normals[0].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing);
3380           normals[1].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing);
3381           let line = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[0]), Vector2.add(b, normals[0]), elementA, elementB);
3382           line.shorten(this.opts.bondLength - this.opts.shortBondLength * this.opts.bondLength);
3383           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(line);
3384           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(new Line(a, b, elementA, elementB));
3385         } else if (s.sideCount[0] < s.sideCount[1]) {
3386           normals[0].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing);
3387           normals[1].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing);
3388           let line = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[1]), Vector2.add(b, normals[1]), elementA, elementB);
3389           line.shorten(this.opts.bondLength - this.opts.shortBondLength * this.opts.bondLength);
3390           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(line);
3391           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(new Line(a, b, elementA, elementB));
3392         } else if (s.totalSideCount[0] > s.totalSideCount[1]) {
3393           normals[0].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing);
3394           normals[1].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing);
3395           let line = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[0]), Vector2.add(b, normals[0]), elementA, elementB);
3396           line.shorten(this.opts.bondLength - this.opts.shortBondLength * this.opts.bondLength);
3397           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(line);
3398           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(new Line(a, b, elementA, elementB));
3399         } else if (s.totalSideCount[0] <= s.totalSideCount[1]) {
3400           normals[0].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing);
3401           normals[1].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing);
3402           let line = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[1]), Vector2.add(b, normals[1]), elementA, elementB);
3403           line.shorten(this.opts.bondLength - this.opts.shortBondLength * this.opts.bondLength);
3404           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(line);
3405           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(new Line(a, b, elementA, elementB));
3406         } else {}
3407       } else if (edge.bondType === '#') {
3408         normals[0].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing / 1.5);
3409         normals[1].multiplyScalar(that.opts.bondSpacing / 1.5);
3410         let lineA = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[0]), Vector2.add(b, normals[0]), elementA, elementB);
3411         let lineB = new Line(Vector2.add(a, normals[1]), Vector2.add(b, normals[1]), elementA, elementB);
3412         this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(lineA);
3413         this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(lineB);
3414         this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(new Line(a, b, elementA, elementB));
3415       } else if (edge.bondType === '.') {// TODO: Something... maybe... version 2?
3416       } else {
3417         let isChiralCenterA = vertexA.value.isStereoCenter;
3418         let isChiralCenterB = vertexB.value.isStereoCenter;
3419   
3420         if (edge.wedge === 'up') {
3421           this.canvasWrapper.drawWedge(new Line(a, b, elementA, elementB, isChiralCenterA, isChiralCenterB));
3422         } else if (edge.wedge === 'down') {
3423           this.canvasWrapper.drawDashedWedge(new Line(a, b, elementA, elementB, isChiralCenterA, isChiralCenterB));
3424         } else {
3425           this.canvasWrapper.drawLine(new Line(a, b, elementA, elementB, isChiralCenterA, isChiralCenterB));
3426         }
3427       }
3428   
3429       if (debug) {
3430         let midpoint = Vector2.midpoint(a, b);
3431         this.canvasWrapper.drawDebugText(midpoint.x, midpoint.y, 'e: ' + edgeId);
3432       }
3433     }
3434     /**
3435      * Draws the vertices representing atoms to the canvas.
3436      *
3437      * @param {Boolean} debug A boolean indicating whether or not to draw debug messages to the canvas.
3438      */
3439   
3440   
3441     drawVertices(debug) {
3442       var i = this.graph.vertices.length;
3443   
3444       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
3445         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[i];
3446         let atom = vertex.value;
3447         let charge = 0;
3448         let isotope = 0;
3449         let bondCount = vertex.value.bondCount;
3450         let element = atom.element;
3451         let hydrogens = Atom.maxBonds[element] - bondCount;
3452         let dir = vertex.getTextDirection(this.graph.vertices);
3453         let isTerminal = this.opts.terminalCarbons || element !== 'C' || atom.hasAttachedPseudoElements ? vertex.isTerminal() : false;
3454         let isCarbon = atom.element === 'C'; // This is a HACK to remove all hydrogens from nitrogens in aromatic rings, as this
3455         // should be the most common state. This has to be fixed by kekulization
3456   
3457         if (atom.element === 'N' && atom.isPartOfAromaticRing) {
3458           hydrogens = 0;
3459         }
3460   
3461         if (atom.bracket) {
3462           hydrogens = atom.bracket.hcount;
3463           charge = atom.bracket.charge;
3464           isotope = atom.bracket.isotope;
3465         }
3466   
3467         if (this.opts.atomVisualization === 'allballs') {
3468           this.canvasWrapper.drawBall(vertex.position.x, vertex.position.y, element);
3469         } else if (atom.isDrawn && (!isCarbon || atom.drawExplicit || isTerminal || atom.hasAttachedPseudoElements) || this.graph.vertices.length === 1) {
3470           if (this.opts.atomVisualization === 'default') {
3471             this.canvasWrapper.drawText(vertex.position.x, vertex.position.y, element, hydrogens, dir, isTerminal, charge, isotope, atom.getAttachedPseudoElements());
3472           } else if (this.opts.atomVisualization === 'balls') {
3473             this.canvasWrapper.drawBall(vertex.position.x, vertex.position.y, element);
3474           }
3475         } else if (vertex.getNeighbourCount() === 2 && vertex.forcePositioned == true) {
3476           // If there is a carbon which bonds are in a straight line, draw a dot
3477           let a = this.graph.vertices[vertex.neighbours[0]].position;
3478           let b = this.graph.vertices[vertex.neighbours[1]].position;
3479           let angle = Vector2.threePointangle(vertex.position, a, b);
3480   
3481           if (Math.abs(Math.PI - angle) < 0.1) {
3482             this.canvasWrapper.drawPoint(vertex.position.x, vertex.position.y, element);
3483           }
3484         }
3485   
3486         if (debug) {
3487           let value = 'v: ' + vertex.id + ' ' + ArrayHelper.print(atom.ringbonds);
3488           this.canvasWrapper.drawDebugText(vertex.position.x, vertex.position.y, value);
3489         } else {// this.canvasWrapper.drawDebugText(vertex.position.x, vertex.position.y, vertex.value.chirality);
3490         }
3491       } // Draw the ring centers for debug purposes
3492   
3493   
3494       if (this.opts.debug) {
3495         for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
3496           let center = this.rings[i].center;
3497           this.canvasWrapper.drawDebugPoint(center.x, center.y, 'r: ' + this.rings[i].id);
3498         }
3499       }
3500     }
3501     /**
3502      * Position the vertices according to their bonds and properties.
3503      */
3504   
3505   
3506     position() {
3507       let startVertex = null; // Always start drawing at a bridged ring if there is one
3508       // If not, start with a ring
3509       // else, start with 0
3510   
3511       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
3512         if (this.graph.vertices[i].value.bridgedRing !== null) {
3513           startVertex = this.graph.vertices[i];
3514           break;
3515         }
3516       }
3517   
3518       for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
3519         if (this.rings[i].isBridged) {
3520           startVertex = this.graph.vertices[this.rings[i].members[0]];
3521         }
3522       }
3523   
3524       if (this.rings.length > 0 && startVertex === null) {
3525         startVertex = this.graph.vertices[this.rings[0].members[0]];
3526       }
3527   
3528       if (startVertex === null) {
3529         startVertex = this.graph.vertices[0];
3530       }
3531   
3532       this.createNextBond(startVertex, null, 0.0);
3533     }
3534     /**
3535      * Stores the current information associated with rings.
3536      */
3537   
3538   
3539     backupRingInformation() {
3540       this.originalRings = Array();
3541       this.originalRingConnections = Array();
3542   
3543       for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
3544         this.originalRings.push(this.rings[i]);
3545       }
3546   
3547       for (var i = 0; i < this.ringConnections.length; i++) {
3548         this.originalRingConnections.push(this.ringConnections[i]);
3549       }
3550   
3551       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
3552         this.graph.vertices[i].value.backupRings();
3553       }
3554     }
3555     /**
3556      * Restores the most recently backed up information associated with rings.
3557      */
3558   
3559   
3560     restoreRingInformation() {
3561       // Get the subring centers from the bridged rings
3562       let bridgedRings = this.getBridgedRings();
3563       this.rings = Array();
3564       this.ringConnections = Array();
3565   
3566       for (var i = 0; i < bridgedRings.length; i++) {
3567         let bridgedRing = bridgedRings[i];
3568   
3569         for (var j = 0; j < bridgedRing.rings.length; j++) {
3570           let ring = bridgedRing.rings[j];
3571           this.originalRings[ring.id].center = ring.center;
3572         }
3573       }
3574   
3575       for (var i = 0; i < this.originalRings.length; i++) {
3576         this.rings.push(this.originalRings[i]);
3577       }
3578   
3579       for (var i = 0; i < this.originalRingConnections.length; i++) {
3580         this.ringConnections.push(this.originalRingConnections[i]);
3581       }
3582   
3583       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
3584         this.graph.vertices[i].value.restoreRings();
3585       }
3586     } // TODO: This needs some cleaning up
3587   
3588     /**
3589      * Creates a new ring, that is, positiones all the vertices inside a ring.
3590      *
3591      * @param {Ring} ring The ring to position.
3592      * @param {(Vector2|null)} [center=null] The center of the ring to be created.
3593      * @param {(Vertex|null)} [startVertex=null] The first vertex to be positioned inside the ring.
3594      * @param {(Vertex|null)} [previousVertex=null] The last vertex that was positioned.
3595      * @param {Boolean} [previousVertex=false] A boolean indicating whether or not this ring was force positioned already - this is needed after force layouting a ring, in order to draw rings connected to it.
3596      */
3597   
3598   
3599     createRing(ring, center = null, startVertex = null, previousVertex = null) {
3600       if (ring.positioned) {
3601         return;
3602       }
3603   
3604       center = center ? center : new Vector2(0, 0);
3605       let orderedNeighbours = ring.getOrderedNeighbours(this.ringConnections);
3606       let startingAngle = startVertex ? Vector2.subtract(startVertex.position, center).angle() : 0;
3607       let radius = MathHelper.polyCircumradius(this.opts.bondLength, ring.getSize());
3608       let angle = MathHelper.centralAngle(ring.getSize());
3609       ring.centralAngle = angle;
3610       let a = startingAngle;
3611       let that = this;
3612       let startVertexId = startVertex ? startVertex.id : null;
3613   
3614       if (ring.members.indexOf(startVertexId) === -1) {
3615         if (startVertex) {
3616           startVertex.positioned = false;
3617         }
3618   
3619         startVertexId = ring.members[0];
3620       } // If the ring is bridged, then draw the vertices inside the ring
3621       // using a force based approach
3622   
3623   
3624       if (ring.isBridged) {
3625         this.graph.kkLayout(ring.members.slice(), center, startVertex.id, ring, this.opts.bondLength, this.opts.kkThreshold, this.opts.kkInnerThreshold, this.opts.kkMaxIteration, this.opts.kkMaxInnerIteration, this.opts.kkMaxEnergy);
3626         ring.positioned = true; // Update the center of the bridged ring
3627   
3628         this.setRingCenter(ring);
3629         center = ring.center; // Setting the centers for the subrings
3630   
3631         for (var i = 0; i < ring.rings.length; i++) {
3632           this.setRingCenter(ring.rings[i]);
3633         }
3634       } else {
3635         ring.eachMember(this.graph.vertices, function (v) {
3636           let vertex = that.graph.vertices[v];
3637   
3638           if (!vertex.positioned) {
3639             vertex.setPosition(center.x + Math.cos(a) * radius, center.y + Math.sin(a) * radius);
3640           }
3641   
3642           a += angle;
3643   
3644           if (!ring.isBridged || ring.rings.length < 3) {
3645             vertex.angle = a;
3646             vertex.positioned = true;
3647           }
3648         }, startVertexId, previousVertex ? previousVertex.id : null);
3649       }
3650   
3651       ring.positioned = true;
3652       ring.center = center; // Draw neighbours in decreasing order of connectivity
3653   
3654       for (var i = 0; i < orderedNeighbours.length; i++) {
3655         let neighbour = this.getRing(orderedNeighbours[i].neighbour);
3656   
3657         if (neighbour.positioned) {
3658           continue;
3659         }
3660   
3661         let vertices = RingConnection.getVertices(this.ringConnections, ring.id, neighbour.id);
3662   
3663         if (vertices.length === 2) {
3664           // This ring is a fused ring
3665           ring.isFused = true;
3666           neighbour.isFused = true;
3667           let vertexA = this.graph.vertices[vertices[0]];
3668           let vertexB = this.graph.vertices[vertices[1]]; // Get middle between vertex A and B
3669   
3670           let midpoint = Vector2.midpoint(vertexA.position, vertexB.position); // Get the normals to the line between A and B
3671   
3672           let normals = Vector2.normals(vertexA.position, vertexB.position); // Normalize the normals
3673   
3674           normals[0].normalize();
3675           normals[1].normalize(); // Set length from middle of side to center (the apothem)
3676   
3677           let r = MathHelper.polyCircumradius(this.opts.bondLength, neighbour.getSize());
3678           let apothem = MathHelper.apothem(r, neighbour.getSize());
3679           normals[0].multiplyScalar(apothem).add(midpoint);
3680           normals[1].multiplyScalar(apothem).add(midpoint); // Pick the normal which results in a larger distance to the previous center
3681           // Also check whether it's inside another ring
3682   
3683           let nextCenter = normals[0];
3684   
3685           if (Vector2.subtract(center, normals[1]).lengthSq() > Vector2.subtract(center, normals[0]).lengthSq()) {
3686             nextCenter = normals[1];
3687           } // Get the vertex (A or B) which is in clock-wise direction of the other
3688   
3689   
3690           let posA = Vector2.subtract(vertexA.position, nextCenter);
3691           let posB = Vector2.subtract(vertexB.position, nextCenter);
3692   
3693           if (posA.clockwise(posB) === -1) {
3694             if (!neighbour.positioned) {
3695               this.createRing(neighbour, nextCenter, vertexA, vertexB);
3696             }
3697           } else {
3698             if (!neighbour.positioned) {
3699               this.createRing(neighbour, nextCenter, vertexB, vertexA);
3700             }
3701           }
3702         } else if (vertices.length === 1) {
3703           // This ring is a spiro
3704           ring.isSpiro = true;
3705           neighbour.isSpiro = true;
3706           let vertexA = this.graph.vertices[vertices[0]]; // Get the vector pointing from the shared vertex to the new centpositioner
3707   
3708           let nextCenter = Vector2.subtract(center, vertexA.position);
3709           nextCenter.invert();
3710           nextCenter.normalize(); // Get the distance from the vertex to the center
3711   
3712           let r = MathHelper.polyCircumradius(this.opts.bondLength, neighbour.getSize());
3713           nextCenter.multiplyScalar(r);
3714           nextCenter.add(vertexA.position);
3715   
3716           if (!neighbour.positioned) {
3717             this.createRing(neighbour, nextCenter, vertexA);
3718           }
3719         }
3720       } // Next, draw atoms that are not part of a ring that are directly attached to this ring
3721   
3722   
3723       for (var i = 0; i < ring.members.length; i++) {
3724         let ringMember = this.graph.vertices[ring.members[i]];
3725         let ringMemberNeighbours = ringMember.neighbours; // If there are multiple, the ovlerap will be resolved in the appropriate step
3726   
3727         for (var j = 0; j < ringMemberNeighbours.length; j++) {
3728           let v = this.graph.vertices[ringMemberNeighbours[j]];
3729   
3730           if (v.positioned) {
3731             continue;
3732           }
3733   
3734           v.value.isConnectedToRing = true;
3735           this.createNextBond(v, ringMember, 0.0);
3736         }
3737       }
3738     }
3739     /**
3740      * Rotate an entire subtree by an angle around a center.
3741      *
3742      * @param {Number} vertexId A vertex id (the root of the sub-tree).
3743      * @param {Number} parentVertexId A vertex id in the previous direction of the subtree that is to rotate.
3744      * @param {Number} angle An angle in randians.
3745      * @param {Vector2} center The rotational center.
3746      */
3747   
3748   
3749     rotateSubtree(vertexId, parentVertexId, angle, center) {
3750       let that = this;
3751       this.graph.traverseTree(vertexId, parentVertexId, function (vertex) {
3752         vertex.position.rotateAround(angle, center);
3753   
3754         for (var i = 0; i < vertex.value.anchoredRings.length; i++) {
3755           let ring = that.rings[vertex.value.anchoredRings[i]];
3756   
3757           if (ring) {
3758             ring.center.rotateAround(angle, center);
3759           }
3760         }
3761       });
3762     }
3763     /**
3764      * Gets the overlap score of a subtree.
3765      *
3766      * @param {Number} vertexId A vertex id (the root of the sub-tree).
3767      * @param {Number} parentVertexId A vertex id in the previous direction of the subtree.
3768      * @param {Number[]} vertexOverlapScores An array containing the vertex overlap scores indexed by vertex id.
3769      * @returns {Object} An object containing the total overlap score and the center of mass of the subtree weighted by overlap score { value: 0.2, center: new Vector2() }.
3770      */
3771   
3772   
3773     getSubtreeOverlapScore(vertexId, parentVertexId, vertexOverlapScores) {
3774       let that = this;
3775       let score = 0;
3776       let center = new Vector2(0, 0);
3777       let count = 0;
3778       this.graph.traverseTree(vertexId, parentVertexId, function (vertex) {
3779         if (!vertex.value.isDrawn) {
3780           return;
3781         }
3782   
3783         let s = vertexOverlapScores[vertex.id];
3784   
3785         if (s > that.opts.overlapSensitivity) {
3786           score += s;
3787           count++;
3788         }
3789   
3790         let position = that.graph.vertices[vertex.id].position.clone();
3791         position.multiplyScalar(s);
3792         center.add(position);
3793       });
3794       center.divide(score);
3795       return {
3796         value: score / count,
3797         center: center
3798       };
3799     }
3800     /**
3801      * Returns the current (positioned vertices so far) center of mass.
3802      * 
3803      * @returns {Vector2} The current center of mass.
3804      */
3805   
3806   
3807     getCurrentCenterOfMass() {
3808       let total = new Vector2(0, 0);
3809       let count = 0;
3810   
3811       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
3812         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[i];
3813   
3814         if (vertex.positioned) {
3815           total.add(vertex.position);
3816           count++;
3817         }
3818       }
3819   
3820       return total.divide(count);
3821     }
3822     /**
3823      * Returns the current (positioned vertices so far) center of mass in the neighbourhood of a given position.
3824      *
3825      * @param {Vector2} vec The point at which to look for neighbours.
3826      * @param {Number} [r=currentBondLength*2.0] The radius of vertices to include.
3827      * @returns {Vector2} The current center of mass.
3828      */
3829   
3830   
3831     getCurrentCenterOfMassInNeigbourhood(vec, r = this.opts.bondLength * 2.0) {
3832       let total = new Vector2(0, 0);
3833       let count = 0;
3834       let rSq = r * r;
3835   
3836       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
3837         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[i];
3838   
3839         if (vertex.positioned && vec.distanceSq(vertex.position) < rSq) {
3840           total.add(vertex.position);
3841           count++;
3842         }
3843       }
3844   
3845       return total.divide(count);
3846     }
3847     /**
3848      * Resolve primary (exact) overlaps, such as two vertices that are connected to the same ring vertex.
3849      */
3850   
3851   
3852     resolvePrimaryOverlaps() {
3853       let overlaps = Array();
3854       let done = Array(this.graph.vertices.length); // Looking for overlaps created by two bonds coming out of a ring atom, which both point straight
3855       // away from the ring and are thus perfectly overlapping.
3856   
3857       for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
3858         let ring = this.rings[i];
3859   
3860         for (var j = 0; j < ring.members.length; j++) {
3861           let vertex = this.graph.vertices[ring.members[j]];
3862   
3863           if (done[vertex.id]) {
3864             continue;
3865           }
3866   
3867           done[vertex.id] = true;
3868           let nonRingNeighbours = this.getNonRingNeighbours(vertex.id);
3869   
3870           if (nonRingNeighbours.length > 1) {
3871             // Look for rings where there are atoms with two bonds outside the ring (overlaps)
3872             let rings = Array();
3873   
3874             for (var k = 0; k < vertex.value.rings.length; k++) {
3875               rings.push(vertex.value.rings[k]);
3876             }
3877   
3878             overlaps.push({
3879               common: vertex,
3880               rings: rings,
3881               vertices: nonRingNeighbours
3882             });
3883           } else if (nonRingNeighbours.length === 1 && vertex.value.rings.length === 2) {
3884             // Look for bonds coming out of joined rings to adjust the angle, an example is: C1=CC(=CC=C1)[C@]12SCCN1CC1=CC=CC=C21
3885             // where the angle has to be adjusted to account for fused ring
3886             let rings = Array();
3887   
3888             for (var k = 0; k < vertex.value.rings.length; k++) {
3889               rings.push(vertex.value.rings[k]);
3890             }
3891   
3892             overlaps.push({
3893               common: vertex,
3894               rings: rings,
3895               vertices: nonRingNeighbours
3896             });
3897           }
3898         }
3899       }
3900   
3901       for (var i = 0; i < overlaps.length; i++) {
3902         let overlap = overlaps[i];
3903   
3904         if (overlap.vertices.length === 2) {
3905           let a = overlap.vertices[0];
3906           let b = overlap.vertices[1];
3907   
3908           if (!a.value.isDrawn || !b.value.isDrawn) {
3909             continue;
3910           }
3911   
3912           let angle = (2 * Math.PI - this.getRing(overlap.rings[0]).getAngle()) / 6.0;
3913           this.rotateSubtree(a.id, overlap.common.id, angle, overlap.common.position);
3914           this.rotateSubtree(b.id, overlap.common.id, -angle, overlap.common.position); // Decide which way to rotate the vertices depending on the effect it has on the overlap score
3915   
3916           let overlapScore = this.getOverlapScore();
3917           let subTreeOverlapA = this.getSubtreeOverlapScore(a.id, overlap.common.id, overlapScore.vertexScores);
3918           let subTreeOverlapB = this.getSubtreeOverlapScore(b.id, overlap.common.id, overlapScore.vertexScores);
3919           let total = subTreeOverlapA.value + subTreeOverlapB.value;
3920           this.rotateSubtree(a.id, overlap.common.id, -2.0 * angle, overlap.common.position);
3921           this.rotateSubtree(b.id, overlap.common.id, 2.0 * angle, overlap.common.position);
3922           overlapScore = this.getOverlapScore();
3923           subTreeOverlapA = this.getSubtreeOverlapScore(a.id, overlap.common.id, overlapScore.vertexScores);
3924           subTreeOverlapB = this.getSubtreeOverlapScore(b.id, overlap.common.id, overlapScore.vertexScores);
3925   
3926           if (subTreeOverlapA.value + subTreeOverlapB.value > total) {
3927             this.rotateSubtree(a.id, overlap.common.id, 2.0 * angle, overlap.common.position);
3928             this.rotateSubtree(b.id, overlap.common.id, -2.0 * angle, overlap.common.position);
3929           }
3930         } else if (overlap.vertices.length === 1) {
3931           if (overlap.rings.length === 2) {// TODO: Implement for more overlap resolution
3932             // console.log(overlap);
3933           }
3934         }
3935       }
3936     }
3937     /**
3938      * Resolve secondary overlaps. Those overlaps are due to the structure turning back on itself.
3939      *
3940      * @param {Object[]} scores An array of objects sorted descending by score.
3941      * @param {Number} scores[].id A vertex id.
3942      * @param {Number} scores[].score The overlap score associated with the vertex id.
3943      */
3944   
3945   
3946     resolveSecondaryOverlaps(scores) {
3947       for (var i = 0; i < scores.length; i++) {
3948         if (scores[i].score > this.opts.overlapSensitivity) {
3949           let vertex = this.graph.vertices[scores[i].id];
3950   
3951           if (vertex.isTerminal()) {
3952             let closest = this.getClosestVertex(vertex);
3953   
3954             if (closest) {
3955               // If one of the vertices is the first one, the previous vertex is not the central vertex but the dummy
3956               // so take the next rather than the previous, which is vertex 1
3957               let closestPosition = null;
3958   
3959               if (closest.isTerminal()) {
3960                 closestPosition = closest.id === 0 ? this.graph.vertices[1].position : closest.previousPosition;
3961               } else {
3962                 closestPosition = closest.id === 0 ? this.graph.vertices[1].position : closest.position;
3963               }
3964   
3965               let vertexPreviousPosition = vertex.id === 0 ? this.graph.vertices[1].position : vertex.previousPosition;
3966               vertex.position.rotateAwayFrom(closestPosition, vertexPreviousPosition, MathHelper.toRad(20));
3967             }
3968           }
3969         }
3970       }
3971     }
3972     /**
3973      * Get the last non-null or 0 angle vertex.
3974      * @param {Number} vertexId A vertex id.
3975      * @returns {Vertex} The last vertex with an angle that was not 0 or null.
3976      */
3977   
3978   
3979     getLastVertexWithAngle(vertexId) {
3980       let angle = 0;
3981       let vertex = null;
3982   
3983       while (!angle && vertexId) {
3984         vertex = this.graph.vertices[vertexId];
3985         angle = vertex.angle;
3986         vertexId = vertex.parentVertexId;
3987       }
3988   
3989       return vertex;
3990     }
3991     /**
3992      * Positiones the next vertex thus creating a bond.
3993      *
3994      * @param {Vertex} vertex A vertex.
3995      * @param {Vertex} [previousVertex=null] The previous vertex which has been positioned.
3996      * @param {Number} [angle=0.0] The (global) angle of the vertex.
3997      * @param {Boolean} [originShortest=false] Whether the origin is the shortest subtree in the branch.
3998      * @param {Boolean} [skipPositioning=false] Whether or not to skip positioning and just check the neighbours.
3999      */
4000   
4001   
4002     createNextBond(vertex, previousVertex = null, angle = 0.0, originShortest = false, skipPositioning = false) {
4003       if (vertex.positioned && !skipPositioning) {
4004         return;
4005       } // If the double bond config was set on this vertex, do not check later
4006   
4007   
4008       let doubleBondConfigSet = false; // Keeping track of configurations around double bonds
4009   
4010       if (previousVertex) {
4011         let edge = this.graph.getEdge(vertex.id, previousVertex.id);
4012   
4013         if ((edge.bondType === '/' || edge.bondType === '\\') && ++this.doubleBondConfigCount % 2 === 1) {
4014           if (this.doubleBondConfig === null) {
4015             this.doubleBondConfig = edge.bondType;
4016             doubleBondConfigSet = true; // Switch if the bond is a branch bond and previous vertex is the first
4017             // TODO: Why is it different with the first vertex?
4018   
4019             if (previousVertex.parentVertexId === null && vertex.value.branchBond) {
4020               if (this.doubleBondConfig === '/') {
4021                 this.doubleBondConfig = '\\';
4022               } else if (this.doubleBondConfig === '\\') {
4023                 this.doubleBondConfig = '/';
4024               }
4025             }
4026           }
4027         }
4028       } // If the current node is the member of one ring, then point straight away
4029       // from the center of the ring. However, if the current node is a member of
4030       // two rings, point away from the middle of the centers of the two rings
4031   
4032   
4033       if (!skipPositioning) {
4034         if (!previousVertex) {
4035           // Add a (dummy) previous position if there is no previous vertex defined
4036           // Since the first vertex is at (0, 0), create a vector at (bondLength, 0)
4037           // and rotate it by 90
4038           let dummy = new Vector2(this.opts.bondLength, 0);
4039           dummy.rotate(MathHelper.toRad(-60));
4040           vertex.previousPosition = dummy;
4041           vertex.setPosition(this.opts.bondLength, 0);
4042           vertex.angle = MathHelper.toRad(-60); // Do not position the vertex if it belongs to a bridged ring that is positioned using a layout algorithm.
4043   
4044           if (vertex.value.bridgedRing === null) {
4045             vertex.positioned = true;
4046           }
4047         } else if (previousVertex.value.rings.length > 0) {
4048           let neighbours = previousVertex.neighbours;
4049           let joinedVertex = null;
4050           let pos = new Vector2(0.0, 0.0);
4051   
4052           if (previousVertex.value.bridgedRing === null && previousVertex.value.rings.length > 1) {
4053             for (var i = 0; i < neighbours.length; i++) {
4054               let neighbour = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[i]];
4055   
4056               if (ArrayHelper.containsAll(neighbour.value.rings, previousVertex.value.rings)) {
4057                 joinedVertex = neighbour;
4058                 break;
4059               }
4060             }
4061           }
4062   
4063           if (joinedVertex === null) {
4064             for (var i = 0; i < neighbours.length; i++) {
4065               let v = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[i]];
4066   
4067               if (v.positioned && this.areVerticesInSameRing(v, previousVertex)) {
4068                 pos.add(Vector2.subtract(v.position, previousVertex.position));
4069               }
4070             }
4071   
4072             pos.invert().normalize().multiplyScalar(this.opts.bondLength).add(previousVertex.position);
4073           } else {
4074             pos = joinedVertex.position.clone().rotateAround(Math.PI, previousVertex.position);
4075           }
4076   
4077           vertex.previousPosition = previousVertex.position;
4078           vertex.setPositionFromVector(pos);
4079           vertex.positioned = true;
4080         } else {
4081           // If the previous vertex was not part of a ring, draw a bond based
4082           // on the global angle of the previous bond
4083           let v = new Vector2(this.opts.bondLength, 0);
4084           v.rotate(angle);
4085           v.add(previousVertex.position);
4086           vertex.setPositionFromVector(v);
4087           vertex.previousPosition = previousVertex.position;
4088           vertex.positioned = true;
4089         }
4090       } // Go to next vertex
4091       // If two rings are connected by a bond ...
4092   
4093   
4094       if (vertex.value.bridgedRing !== null) {
4095         let nextRing = this.getRing(vertex.value.bridgedRing);
4096   
4097         if (!nextRing.positioned) {
4098           let nextCenter = Vector2.subtract(vertex.previousPosition, vertex.position);
4099           nextCenter.invert();
4100           nextCenter.normalize();
4101           let r = MathHelper.polyCircumradius(this.opts.bondLength, nextRing.members.length);
4102           nextCenter.multiplyScalar(r);
4103           nextCenter.add(vertex.position);
4104           this.createRing(nextRing, nextCenter, vertex);
4105         }
4106       } else if (vertex.value.rings.length > 0) {
4107         let nextRing = this.getRing(vertex.value.rings[0]);
4108   
4109         if (!nextRing.positioned) {
4110           let nextCenter = Vector2.subtract(vertex.previousPosition, vertex.position);
4111           nextCenter.invert();
4112           nextCenter.normalize();
4113           let r = MathHelper.polyCircumradius(this.opts.bondLength, nextRing.getSize());
4114           nextCenter.multiplyScalar(r);
4115           nextCenter.add(vertex.position);
4116           this.createRing(nextRing, nextCenter, vertex);
4117         }
4118       } else {
4119         // Draw the non-ring vertices connected to this one  
4120         let isStereoCenter = vertex.value.isStereoCenter;
4121         let tmpNeighbours = vertex.getNeighbours();
4122         let neighbours = Array(); // Remove neighbours that are not drawn
4123   
4124         for (var i = 0; i < tmpNeighbours.length; i++) {
4125           if (this.graph.vertices[tmpNeighbours[i]].value.isDrawn) {
4126             neighbours.push(tmpNeighbours[i]);
4127           }
4128         } // Remove the previous vertex (which has already been drawn)
4129   
4130   
4131         if (previousVertex) {
4132           neighbours = ArrayHelper.remove(neighbours, previousVertex.id);
4133         }
4134   
4135         let previousAngle = vertex.getAngle();
4136   
4137         if (neighbours.length === 1) {
4138           let nextVertex = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[0]]; // Make a single chain always cis except when there's a tribble (yes, this is a Star Trek reference) bond
4139           // or if there are successive double bonds. Added a ring check because if there is an aromatic ring the ring bond inside the ring counts as a double bond and leads to =-= being straight.
4140   
4141           if (vertex.value.bondType === '#' || previousVertex && previousVertex.value.bondType === '#' || vertex.value.bondType === '=' && previousVertex && previousVertex.value.rings.length === 0 && previousVertex.value.bondType === '=' && vertex.value.branchBond !== '-') {
4142             vertex.value.drawExplicit = false;
4143   
4144             if (previousVertex) {
4145               let straightEdge1 = this.graph.getEdge(vertex.id, previousVertex.id);
4146               straightEdge1.center = true;
4147             }
4148   
4149             let straightEdge2 = this.graph.getEdge(vertex.id, nextVertex.id);
4150             straightEdge2.center = true;
4151   
4152             if (vertex.value.bondType === '#' || previousVertex && previousVertex.value.bondType === '#') {
4153               nextVertex.angle = 0.0;
4154             }
4155   
4156             nextVertex.drawExplicit = true;
4157             this.createNextBond(nextVertex, vertex, previousAngle + nextVertex.angle);
4158           } else if (previousVertex && previousVertex.value.rings.length > 0) {
4159             // If coming out of a ring, always draw away from the center of mass
4160             let proposedAngleA = MathHelper.toRad(60);
4161             let proposedAngleB = -proposedAngleA;
4162             let proposedVectorA = new Vector2(this.opts.bondLength, 0);
4163             let proposedVectorB = new Vector2(this.opts.bondLength, 0);
4164             proposedVectorA.rotate(proposedAngleA).add(vertex.position);
4165             proposedVectorB.rotate(proposedAngleB).add(vertex.position); // let centerOfMass = this.getCurrentCenterOfMassInNeigbourhood(vertex.position, 100);
4166   
4167             let centerOfMass = this.getCurrentCenterOfMass();
4168             let distanceA = proposedVectorA.distanceSq(centerOfMass);
4169             let distanceB = proposedVectorB.distanceSq(centerOfMass);
4170             nextVertex.angle = distanceA < distanceB ? proposedAngleB : proposedAngleA;
4171             this.createNextBond(nextVertex, vertex, previousAngle + nextVertex.angle);
4172           } else {
4173             let a = vertex.angle; // Take the min and max if the previous angle was in a 4-neighbourhood (90 angles)
4174             // TODO: If a is null or zero, it should be checked whether or not this one should go cis or trans, that is,
4175             //       it should go into the oposite direction of the last non-null or 0 previous vertex / angle.
4176   
4177             if (previousVertex && previousVertex.neighbours.length > 3) {
4178               if (a > 0) {
4179                 a = Math.min(1.0472, a);
4180               } else if (a < 0) {
4181                 a = Math.max(-1.0472, a);
4182               } else {
4183                 a = 1.0472;
4184               }
4185             } else if (!a) {
4186               let v = this.getLastVertexWithAngle(vertex.id);
4187               a = v.angle;
4188   
4189               if (!a) {
4190                 a = 1.0472;
4191               }
4192             } // Handle configuration around double bonds
4193   
4194   
4195             if (previousVertex && !doubleBondConfigSet) {
4196               let bondType = this.graph.getEdge(vertex.id, nextVertex.id).bondType;
4197   
4198               if (bondType === '/') {
4199                 if (this.doubleBondConfig === '/') {// Nothing to do since it will be trans per default
4200                 } else if (this.doubleBondConfig === '\\') {
4201                   a = -a;
4202                 }
4203   
4204                 this.doubleBondConfig = null;
4205               } else if (bondType === '\\') {
4206                 if (this.doubleBondConfig === '/') {
4207                   a = -a;
4208                 } else if (this.doubleBondConfig === '\\') {// Nothing to do since it will be trans per default
4209                 }
4210   
4211                 this.doubleBondConfig = null;
4212               }
4213             }
4214   
4215             if (originShortest) {
4216               nextVertex.angle = a;
4217             } else {
4218               nextVertex.angle = -a;
4219             }
4220   
4221             this.createNextBond(nextVertex, vertex, previousAngle + nextVertex.angle);
4222           }
4223         } else if (neighbours.length === 2) {
4224           // If the previous vertex comes out of a ring, it doesn't have an angle set
4225           let a = vertex.angle;
4226   
4227           if (!a) {
4228             a = 1.0472;
4229           } // Check for the longer subtree - always go with cis for the longer subtree
4230   
4231   
4232           let subTreeDepthA = this.graph.getTreeDepth(neighbours[0], vertex.id);
4233           let subTreeDepthB = this.graph.getTreeDepth(neighbours[1], vertex.id);
4234           let l = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[0]];
4235           let r = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[1]];
4236           l.value.subtreeDepth = subTreeDepthA;
4237           r.value.subtreeDepth = subTreeDepthB; // Also get the subtree for the previous direction (this is important when
4238           // the previous vertex is the shortest path)
4239   
4240           let subTreeDepthC = this.graph.getTreeDepth(previousVertex ? previousVertex.id : null, vertex.id);
4241   
4242           if (previousVertex) {
4243             previousVertex.value.subtreeDepth = subTreeDepthC;
4244           }
4245   
4246           let cis = 0;
4247           let trans = 1; // Carbons go always cis
4248   
4249           if (r.value.element === 'C' && l.value.element !== 'C' && subTreeDepthB > 1 && subTreeDepthA < 5) {
4250             cis = 1;
4251             trans = 0;
4252           } else if (r.value.element !== 'C' && l.value.element === 'C' && subTreeDepthA > 1 && subTreeDepthB < 5) {
4253             cis = 0;
4254             trans = 1;
4255           } else if (subTreeDepthB > subTreeDepthA) {
4256             cis = 1;
4257             trans = 0;
4258           }
4259   
4260           let cisVertex = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[cis]];
4261           let transVertex = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[trans]];
4262           let edgeCis = this.graph.getEdge(vertex.id, cisVertex.id);
4263           let edgeTrans = this.graph.getEdge(vertex.id, transVertex.id); // If the origin tree is the shortest, make them the main chain
4264   
4265           let originShortest = false;
4266   
4267           if (subTreeDepthC < subTreeDepthA && subTreeDepthC < subTreeDepthB) {
4268             originShortest = true;
4269           }
4270   
4271           transVertex.angle = a;
4272           cisVertex.angle = -a;
4273   
4274           if (this.doubleBondConfig === '\\') {
4275             if (transVertex.value.branchBond === '\\') {
4276               transVertex.angle = -a;
4277               cisVertex.angle = a;
4278             }
4279           } else if (this.doubleBondConfig === '/') {
4280             if (transVertex.value.branchBond === '/') {
4281               transVertex.angle = -a;
4282               cisVertex.angle = a;
4283             }
4284           }
4285   
4286           this.createNextBond(transVertex, vertex, previousAngle + transVertex.angle, originShortest);
4287           this.createNextBond(cisVertex, vertex, previousAngle + cisVertex.angle, originShortest);
4288         } else if (neighbours.length === 3) {
4289           // The vertex with the longest sub-tree should always go straight
4290           let d1 = this.graph.getTreeDepth(neighbours[0], vertex.id);
4291           let d2 = this.graph.getTreeDepth(neighbours[1], vertex.id);
4292           let d3 = this.graph.getTreeDepth(neighbours[2], vertex.id);
4293           let s = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[0]];
4294           let l = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[1]];
4295           let r = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[2]];
4296           s.value.subtreeDepth = d1;
4297           l.value.subtreeDepth = d2;
4298           r.value.subtreeDepth = d3;
4299   
4300           if (d2 > d1 && d2 > d3) {
4301             s = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[1]];
4302             l = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[0]];
4303             r = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[2]];
4304           } else if (d3 > d1 && d3 > d2) {
4305             s = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[2]];
4306             l = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[0]];
4307             r = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[1]];
4308           } // Create a cross if more than one subtree is of length > 1
4309           // or the vertex is connected to a ring
4310   
4311   
4312           if (previousVertex && previousVertex.value.rings.length < 1 && s.value.rings.length < 1 && l.value.rings.length < 1 && r.value.rings.length < 1 && this.graph.getTreeDepth(l.id, vertex.id) === 1 && this.graph.getTreeDepth(r.id, vertex.id) === 1 && this.graph.getTreeDepth(s.id, vertex.id) > 1) {
4313             s.angle = -vertex.angle;
4314   
4315             if (vertex.angle >= 0) {
4316               l.angle = MathHelper.toRad(30);
4317               r.angle = MathHelper.toRad(90);
4318             } else {
4319               l.angle = -MathHelper.toRad(30);
4320               r.angle = -MathHelper.toRad(90);
4321             }
4322   
4323             this.createNextBond(s, vertex, previousAngle + s.angle);
4324             this.createNextBond(l, vertex, previousAngle + l.angle);
4325             this.createNextBond(r, vertex, previousAngle + r.angle);
4326           } else {
4327             s.angle = 0.0;
4328             l.angle = MathHelper.toRad(90);
4329             r.angle = -MathHelper.toRad(90);
4330             this.createNextBond(s, vertex, previousAngle + s.angle);
4331             this.createNextBond(l, vertex, previousAngle + l.angle);
4332             this.createNextBond(r, vertex, previousAngle + r.angle);
4333           }
4334         } else if (neighbours.length === 4) {
4335           // The vertex with the longest sub-tree should always go to the reflected opposide direction
4336           let d1 = this.graph.getTreeDepth(neighbours[0], vertex.id);
4337           let d2 = this.graph.getTreeDepth(neighbours[1], vertex.id);
4338           let d3 = this.graph.getTreeDepth(neighbours[2], vertex.id);
4339           let d4 = this.graph.getTreeDepth(neighbours[3], vertex.id);
4340           let w = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[0]];
4341           let x = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[1]];
4342           let y = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[2]];
4343           let z = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[3]];
4344           w.value.subtreeDepth = d1;
4345           x.value.subtreeDepth = d2;
4346           y.value.subtreeDepth = d3;
4347           z.value.subtreeDepth = d4;
4348   
4349           if (d2 > d1 && d2 > d3 && d2 > d4) {
4350             w = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[1]];
4351             x = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[0]];
4352             y = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[2]];
4353             z = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[3]];
4354           } else if (d3 > d1 && d3 > d2 && d3 > d4) {
4355             w = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[2]];
4356             x = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[0]];
4357             y = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[1]];
4358             z = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[3]];
4359           } else if (d4 > d1 && d4 > d2 && d4 > d3) {
4360             w = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[3]];
4361             x = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[0]];
4362             y = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[1]];
4363             z = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[2]];
4364           }
4365   
4366           w.angle = -MathHelper.toRad(36);
4367           x.angle = MathHelper.toRad(36);
4368           y.angle = -MathHelper.toRad(108);
4369           z.angle = MathHelper.toRad(108);
4370           this.createNextBond(w, vertex, previousAngle + w.angle);
4371           this.createNextBond(x, vertex, previousAngle + x.angle);
4372           this.createNextBond(y, vertex, previousAngle + y.angle);
4373           this.createNextBond(z, vertex, previousAngle + z.angle);
4374         }
4375       }
4376     }
4377     /**
4378      * Gets the vetex sharing the edge that is the common bond of two rings.
4379      *
4380      * @param {Vertex} vertex A vertex.
4381      * @returns {(Number|null)} The id of a vertex sharing the edge that is the common bond of two rings with the vertex provided or null, if none.
4382      */
4383   
4384   
4385     getCommonRingbondNeighbour(vertex) {
4386       let neighbours = vertex.neighbours;
4387   
4388       for (var i = 0; i < neighbours.length; i++) {
4389         let neighbour = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[i]];
4390   
4391         if (ArrayHelper.containsAll(neighbour.value.rings, vertex.value.rings)) {
4392           return neighbour;
4393         }
4394       }
4395   
4396       return null;
4397     }
4398     /**
4399      * Check if a vector is inside any ring.
4400      *
4401      * @param {Vector2} vec A vector.
4402      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not the point (vector) is inside any of the rings associated with the current molecule.
4403      */
4404   
4405   
4406     isPointInRing(vec) {
4407       for (var i = 0; i < this.rings.length; i++) {
4408         let ring = this.rings[i];
4409   
4410         if (!ring.positioned) {
4411           continue;
4412         }
4413   
4414         let radius = MathHelper.polyCircumradius(this.opts.bondLength, ring.getSize());
4415         let radiusSq = radius * radius;
4416   
4417         if (vec.distanceSq(ring.center) < radiusSq) {
4418           return true;
4419         }
4420       }
4421   
4422       return false;
4423     }
4424     /**
4425      * Check whether or not an edge is part of a ring.
4426      *
4427      * @param {Edge} edge An edge.
4428      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not the edge is part of a ring.
4429      */
4430   
4431   
4432     isEdgeInRing(edge) {
4433       let source = this.graph.vertices[edge.sourceId];
4434       let target = this.graph.vertices[edge.targetId];
4435       return this.areVerticesInSameRing(source, target);
4436     }
4437     /**
4438      * Check whether or not an edge is rotatable.
4439      *
4440      * @param {Edge} edge An edge.
4441      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not the edge is rotatable.
4442      */
4443   
4444   
4445     isEdgeRotatable(edge) {
4446       let vertexA = this.graph.vertices[edge.sourceId];
4447       let vertexB = this.graph.vertices[edge.targetId]; // Only single bonds are rotatable
4448   
4449       if (edge.bondType !== '-') {
4450         return false;
4451       } // Do not rotate edges that have a further single bond to each side - do that!
4452       // If the bond is terminal, it doesn't make sense to rotate it
4453       // if (vertexA.getNeighbourCount() + vertexB.getNeighbourCount() < 5) {
4454       //   return false;
4455       // }
4456   
4457   
4458       if (vertexA.isTerminal() || vertexB.isTerminal()) {
4459         return false;
4460       } // Ringbonds are not rotatable
4461   
4462   
4463       if (vertexA.value.rings.length > 0 && vertexB.value.rings.length > 0 && this.areVerticesInSameRing(vertexA, vertexB)) {
4464         return false;
4465       }
4466   
4467       return true;
4468     }
4469     /**
4470      * Check whether or not a ring is an implicitly defined aromatic ring (lower case smiles).
4471      *
4472      * @param {Ring} ring A ring.
4473      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not a ring is implicitly defined as aromatic.
4474      */
4475   
4476   
4477     isRingAromatic(ring) {
4478       for (var i = 0; i < ring.members.length; i++) {
4479         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[ring.members[i]];
4480   
4481         if (!vertex.value.isPartOfAromaticRing) {
4482           return false;
4483         }
4484       }
4485   
4486       return true;
4487     }
4488     /**
4489      * Get the normals of an edge.

4494

4497       let v1 = this.graph.vertices[edge.sourceId].position;
4498       let v2 = this.graph.vertices[edge.targetId].position; // Get the normalized normals for the edge
4499   
4500       let normals = Vector2.units(v1, v2);
4501       return normals;
4502     }
4503     /**
4504      * Returns an array of vertices that are neighbouring a vertix but are not members of a ring (including bridges).
4505      *
4506      * @param {Number} vertexId A vertex id.
4507      * @returns {Vertex[]} An array of vertices.
4508      */
4509   
4510   
4511     getNonRingNeighbours(vertexId) {
4512       let nrneighbours = Array();
4513       let vertex = this.graph.vertices[vertexId];
4514       let neighbours = vertex.neighbours;
4515   
4516       for (var i = 0; i < neighbours.length; i++) {
4517         let neighbour = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[i]];
4518         let nIntersections = ArrayHelper.intersection(vertex.value.rings, neighbour.value.rings).length;
4519   
4520         if (nIntersections === 0 && neighbour.value.isBridge == false) {
4521           nrneighbours.push(neighbour);
4522         }
4523       }
4524   
4525       return nrneighbours;
4526     }
4527     /**
4528      * Annotaed stereochemistry information for visualization.
4529      */
4530   
4531   
4532     annotateStereochemistry() {
4533       let maxDepth = 10; // For each stereo-center
4534   
4535       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
4536         let vertex = this.graph.vertices[i];
4537   
4538         if (!vertex.value.isStereoCenter) {
4539           continue;
4540         }
4541   
4542         let neighbours = vertex.getNeighbours();
4543         let nNeighbours = neighbours.length;
4544         let priorities = Array(nNeighbours);
4545   
4546         for (var j = 0; j < nNeighbours; j++) {
4547           let visited = new Uint8Array(this.graph.vertices.length);
4548           let priority = Array(Array());
4549           visited[vertex.id] = 1;
4550           this.visitStereochemistry(neighbours[j], vertex.id, visited, priority, maxDepth, 0); // Sort each level according to atomic number
4551   
4552           for (var k = 0; k < priority.length; k++) {
4553             priority[k].sort(function (a, b) {
4554               return b - a;
4555             });
4556           }
4557   
4558           priorities[j] = [j, priority];
4559         }
4560   
4561         let maxLevels = 0;
4562         let maxEntries = 0;
4563   
4564         for (var j = 0; j < priorities.length; j++) {
4565           if (priorities[j][1].length > maxLevels) {
4566             maxLevels = priorities[j][1].length;
4567           }
4568   
4569           for (var k = 0; k < priorities[j][1].length; k++) {
4570             if (priorities[j][1][k].length > maxEntries) {
4571               maxEntries = priorities[j][1][k].length;
4572             }
4573           }
4574         }
4575   
4576         for (var j = 0; j < priorities.length; j++) {
4577           let diff = maxLevels - priorities[j][1].length;
4578   
4579           for (var k = 0; k < diff; k++) {
4580             priorities[j][1].push([]);
4581           } // Break ties by the position in the SMILES string as per specification
4582   
4583   
4584           priorities[j][1].push([neighbours[j]]); // Make all same length. Fill with zeroes.
4585   
4586           for (var k = 0; k < priorities[j][1].length; k++) {
4587             let diff = maxEntries - priorities[j][1][k].length;
4588   
4589             for (var l = 0; l < diff; l++) {
4590               priorities[j][1][k].push(0);
4591             }
4592           }
4593         }
4594   
4595         priorities.sort(function (a, b) {
4596           for (var j = 0; j < a[1].length; j++) {
4597             for (var k = 0; k < a[1][j].length; k++) {
4598               if (a[1][j][k] > b[1][j][k]) {
4599                 return -1;
4600               } else if (a[1][j][k] < b[1][j][k]) {
4601                 return 1;
4602               }
4603             }
4604           }
4605   
4606           return 0;
4607         });
4608         let order = new Uint8Array(nNeighbours);
4609   
4610         for (var j = 0; j < nNeighbours; j++) {
4611           order[j] = priorities[j][0];
4612           vertex.value.priority = j;
4613         } // Check the angles between elements 0 and 1, and 0 and 2 to determine whether they are
4614         // drawn cw or ccw
4615         // TODO: OC(Cl)=[C@]=C(C)F currently fails here, however this is, IMHO, not a valid SMILES.
4616   
4617   
4618         let posA = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[order[0]]].position;
4619         let posB = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[order[1]]].position;
4620         let posC = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[order[2]]].position;
4621         let cwA = posA.relativeClockwise(posB, vertex.position);
4622         let cwB = posA.relativeClockwise(posC, vertex.position); // If the second priority is clockwise from the first, the ligands are drawn clockwise, since
4623         // The hydrogen can be drawn on either side
4624   
4625         let isCw = cwA === -1;
4626         let rotation = vertex.value.bracket.chirality === '@' ? -1 : 1;
4627         let rs = MathHelper.parityOfPermutation(order) * rotation === 1 ? 'R' : 'S'; // Flip the hydrogen direction when the drawing doesn't match the chirality.
4628   
4629         let wedgeA = 'down';
4630         let wedgeB = 'up';
4631   
4632         if (isCw && rs !== 'R' || !isCw && rs !== 'S') {
4633           vertex.value.hydrogenDirection = 'up';
4634           wedgeA = 'up';
4635           wedgeB = 'down';
4636         }
4637   
4638         if (vertex.value.hasHydrogen) {
4639           this.graph.getEdge(vertex.id, neighbours[order[order.length - 1]]).wedge = wedgeA;
4640         } // Get the shortest subtree to flip up / down. Ignore lowest priority
4641         // The rules are following:
4642         // 1. Do not draw wedge between two stereocenters
4643         // 2. Heteroatoms
4644         // 3. Draw outside ring
4645         // 4. Shortest subtree
4646   
4647   
4648         let wedgeOrder = new Array(neighbours.length - 1);
4649         let showHydrogen = vertex.value.rings.length > 1 && vertex.value.hasHydrogen;
4650         let offset = vertex.value.hasHydrogen ? 1 : 0;
4651   
4652         for (var j = 0; j < order.length - offset; j++) {
4653           wedgeOrder[j] = new Uint32Array(2);
4654           let neighbour = this.graph.vertices[neighbours[order[j]]];
4655           wedgeOrder[j][0] += neighbour.value.isStereoCenter ? 0 : 100000; // wedgeOrder[j][0] += neighbour.value.rings.length > 0 ? 0 : 10000;
4656           // Only add if in same ring, unlike above
4657   
4658           wedgeOrder[j][0] += this.areVerticesInSameRing(neighbour, vertex) ? 0 : 10000;
4659           wedgeOrder[j][0] += neighbour.value.isHeteroAtom() ? 1000 : 0;
4660           wedgeOrder[j][0] -= neighbour.value.subtreeDepth === 0 ? 1000 : 0;
4661           wedgeOrder[j][0] += 1000 - neighbour.value.subtreeDepth;
4662           wedgeOrder[j][1] = neighbours[order[j]];
4663         }
4664   
4665         wedgeOrder.sort(function (a, b) {
4666           if (a[0] > b[0]) {
4667             return -1;
4668           } else if (a[0] < b[0]) {
4669             return 1;
4670           }
4671   
4672           return 0;
4673         }); // If all neighbours are in a ring, do not draw wedge, the hydrogen will be drawn.
4674   
4675         if (!showHydrogen) {
4676           let wedgeId = wedgeOrder[0][1];
4677   
4678           if (vertex.value.hasHydrogen) {
4679             this.graph.getEdge(vertex.id, wedgeId).wedge = wedgeB;
4680           } else {
4681             let wedge = wedgeB;
4682   
4683             for (var j = order.length - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
4684               if (wedge === wedgeA) {
4685                 wedge = wedgeB;
4686               } else {
4687                 wedge = wedgeA;
4688               }
4689   
4690               if (neighbours[order[j]] === wedgeId) {
4691                 break;
4692               }
4693             }
4694   
4695             this.graph.getEdge(vertex.id, wedgeId).wedge = wedge;
4696           }
4697         }
4698   
4699         vertex.value.chirality = rs;
4700       }
4701     }
4702     /**
4703      * 
4704      * 
4705      * @param {Number} vertexId The id of a vertex.
4706      * @param {(Number|null)} previousVertexId The id of the parent vertex of the vertex.
4707      * @param {Uint8Array} visited An array containing the visited flag for all vertices in the graph.
4708      * @param {Array} priority An array of arrays storing the atomic numbers for each level.
4709      * @param {Number} maxDepth The maximum depth.
4710      * @param {Number} depth The current depth.
4711      */
4712   
4713   
4714     visitStereochemistry(vertexId, previousVertexId, visited, priority, maxDepth, depth, parentAtomicNumber = 0) {
4715       visited[vertexId] = 1;
4716       let vertex = this.graph.vertices[vertexId];
4717       let atomicNumber = vertex.value.getAtomicNumber();
4718   
4719       if (priority.length <= depth) {
4720         priority.push(Array());
4721       }
4722   
4723       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.getEdge(vertexId, previousVertexId).weight; i++) {
4724         priority[depth].push(parentAtomicNumber * 1000 + atomicNumber);
4725       }
4726   
4727       let neighbours = this.graph.vertices[vertexId].neighbours;
4728   
4729       for (var i = 0; i < neighbours.length; i++) {
4730         if (visited[neighbours[i]] !== 1 && depth < maxDepth - 1) {
4731           this.visitStereochemistry(neighbours[i], vertexId, visited.slice(), priority, maxDepth, depth + 1, atomicNumber);
4732         }
4733       } // Valences are filled with hydrogens and passed to the next level.
4734   
4735   
4736       if (depth < maxDepth - 1) {
4737         let bonds = 0;
4738   
4739         for (var i = 0; i < neighbours.length; i++) {
4740           bonds += this.graph.getEdge(vertexId, neighbours[i]).weight;
4741         }
4742   
4743         for (var i = 0; i < vertex.value.getMaxBonds() - bonds; i++) {
4744           if (priority.length <= depth + 1) {
4745             priority.push(Array());
4746           }
4747   
4748           priority[depth + 1].push(atomicNumber * 1000 + 1);
4749         }
4750       }
4751     }
4752     /**
4753      * Creates pseudo-elements (such as Et, Me, Ac, Bz, ...) at the position of the carbon sets
4754      * the involved atoms not to be displayed.
4755      */
4756   
4757   
4758     initPseudoElements() {
4759       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
4760         const vertex = this.graph.vertices[i];
4761         const neighbourIds = vertex.neighbours;
4762         let neighbours = Array(neighbourIds.length);
4763   
4764         for (var j = 0; j < neighbourIds.length; j++) {
4765           neighbours[j] = this.graph.vertices[neighbourIds[j]];
4766         } // Ignore atoms that have less than 3 neighbours, except if
4767         // the vertex is connected to a ring and has two neighbours
4768   
4769   
4770         if (vertex.getNeighbourCount() < 3 || vertex.value.rings.length > 0) {
4771           continue;
4772         } // TODO: This exceptions should be handled more elegantly (via config file?)
4773         // Ignore phosphates (especially for triphosphates)
4774   
4775   
4776         if (vertex.value.element === 'P') {
4777           continue;
4778         } // Ignore also guanidine
4779   
4780   
4781         if (vertex.value.element === 'C' && neighbours.length === 3 && neighbours[0].value.element === 'N' && neighbours[1].value.element === 'N' && neighbours[2].value.element === 'N') {
4782           continue;
4783         } // Continue if there are less than two heteroatoms
4784         // or if a neighbour has more than 1 neighbour
4785   
4786   
4787         let heteroAtomCount = 0;
4788         let ctn = 0;
4789   
4790         for (var j = 0; j < neighbours.length; j++) {
4791           let neighbour = neighbours[j];
4792           let neighbouringElement = neighbour.value.element;
4793           let neighbourCount = neighbour.getNeighbourCount();
4794   
4795           if (neighbouringElement !== 'C' && neighbouringElement !== 'H' && neighbourCount === 1) {
4796             heteroAtomCount++;
4797           }
4798   
4799           if (neighbourCount > 1) {
4800             ctn++;
4801           }
4802         }
4803   
4804         if (ctn > 1 || heteroAtomCount < 2) {
4805           continue;
4806         } // Get the previous atom (the one which is not terminal)
4807   
4808   
4809         let previous = null;
4810   
4811         for (var j = 0; j < neighbours.length; j++) {
4812           let neighbour = neighbours[j];
4813   
4814           if (neighbour.getNeighbourCount() > 1) {
4815             previous = neighbour;
4816           }
4817         }
4818   
4819         for (var j = 0; j < neighbours.length; j++) {
4820           let neighbour = neighbours[j];
4821   
4822           if (neighbour.getNeighbourCount() > 1) {
4823             continue;
4824           }
4825   
4826           neighbour.value.isDrawn = false;
4827           let hydrogens = Atom.maxBonds[neighbour.value.element] - neighbour.value.bondCount;
4828           let charge = '';
4829   
4830           if (neighbour.value.bracket) {
4831             hydrogens = neighbour.value.bracket.hcount;
4832             charge = neighbour.value.bracket.charge || 0;
4833           }
4834   
4835           vertex.value.attachPseudoElement(neighbour.value.element, previous ? previous.value.element : null, hydrogens, charge);
4836         }
4837       } // The second pass
4838   
4839   
4840       for (var i = 0; i < this.graph.vertices.length; i++) {
4841         const vertex = this.graph.vertices[i];
4842         const atom = vertex.value;
4843         const element = atom.element;
4844   
4845         if (element === 'C' || element === 'H' || !atom.isDrawn) {
4846           continue;
4847         }
4848   
4849         const neighbourIds = vertex.neighbours;
4850         let neighbours = Array(neighbourIds.length);
4851   
4852         for (var j = 0; j < neighbourIds.length; j++) {
4853           neighbours[j] = this.graph.vertices[neighbourIds[j]];
4854         }
4855   
4856         for (var j = 0; j < neighbours.length; j++) {
4857           let neighbour = neighbours[j].value;
4858   
4859           if (!neighbour.hasAttachedPseudoElements || neighbour.getAttachedPseudoElementsCount() !== 2) {
4860             continue;
4861           }
4862   
4863           const pseudoElements = neighbour.getAttachedPseudoElements();
4864   
4865           if (pseudoElements.hasOwnProperty('0O') && pseudoElements.hasOwnProperty('3C')) {
4866             neighbour.isDrawn = false;
4867             vertex.value.attachPseudoElement('Ac', '', 0);
4868           }
4869         }
4870       }
4871     }
4872   
4873   }

4945   "use strict";
4946   
4947   //@ts-check
4948   const MathHelper = require('./MathHelper');
4949   
4950   const Vector2 = require('./Vector2');
4951
