4959   /** 
4960    * A class representing the molecular graph. 
4961    * 
4962    * @property {Vertex[]} vertices The vertices of the graph.
4963    * @property {Edge[]} edges The edges of this graph.
4964    * @property {Object} vertexIdsToEdgeId A map mapping vertex ids to the edge between the two vertices. The key is defined as vertexAId + '_' + vertexBId.
4965    * @property {Boolean} isometric A boolean indicating whether or not the SMILES associated with this graph is isometric.
4966    */
4967   
4968   
4969   class Graph {
4970     /**
4971      * The constructor of the class Graph.
4972      * 
4973      * @param {Object} parseTree A SMILES parse tree.
4974      * @param {Boolean} [isomeric=false] A boolean specifying whether or not the SMILES is isomeric.
4975      */
4976     constructor(parseTree, isomeric = false) {
4977       this.vertices = Array();
4978       this.edges = Array();
4979       this.vertexIdsToEdgeId = {};
4980       this.isomeric = isomeric; // Used for the bridge detection algorithm
4981   
4982       this._time = 0;
4983   
4984       this._init(parseTree);
4985     }
4986     /**
4987      * PRIVATE FUNCTION. Initializing the graph from the parse tree.
4988      *
4989      * @param {Object} node The current node in the parse tree.
4990      * @param {Number} parentVertexId=null The id of the previous vertex.
4991      * @param {Boolean} isBranch=false Whether or not the bond leading to this vertex is a branch bond. Branches are represented by parentheses in smiles (e.g. CC(O)C).
4992      */
4993   
4994   
4995     _init(node, order = 0, parentVertexId = null, isBranch = false) {
4996       // Create a new vertex object
4997       let atom = new Atom(node.atom.element ? node.atom.element : node.atom, node.bond);
4998       atom.branchBond = node.branchBond;
4999       atom.ringbonds = node.ringbonds;
5000       atom.bracket = node.atom.element ? node.atom : null;
5001       let vertex = new Vertex(atom);
5002       let parentVertex = this.vertices[parentVertexId];
5003       this.addVertex(vertex); // Add the id of this node to the parent as child
5004   
5005       if (parentVertexId !== null) {
5006         vertex.setParentVertexId(parentVertexId);
5007         vertex.value.addNeighbouringElement(parentVertex.value.element);
5008         parentVertex.addChild(vertex.id);
5009         parentVertex.value.addNeighbouringElement(atom.element); // In addition create a spanningTreeChildren property, which later will
5010         // not contain the children added through ringbonds
5011   
5012         parentVertex.spanningTreeChildren.push(vertex.id); // Add edge between this node and its parent
5013   
5014         let edge = new Edge(parentVertexId, vertex.id, 1);
5015         let vertexId = null;
5016   
5017         if (isBranch) {
5018           edge.setBondType(vertex.value.branchBond || '-');
5019           vertexId = vertex.id;
5020           edge.setBondType(vertex.value.branchBond || '-');
5021           vertexId = vertex.id;
5022         } else {
5023           edge.setBondType(parentVertex.value.bondType || '-');
5024           vertexId = parentVertex.id;
5025         }
5026   
5027         let edgeId = this.addEdge(edge);
5028       }
5029   
5030       let offset = node.ringbondCount + 1;
5031   
5032       if (atom.bracket) {
5033         offset += atom.bracket.hcount;
5034       }
5035   
5036       let stereoHydrogens = 0;
5037   
5038       if (atom.bracket && atom.bracket.chirality) {
5039         atom.isStereoCenter = true;
5040         stereoHydrogens = atom.bracket.hcount;
5041   
5042         for (var i = 0; i < stereoHydrogens; i++) {
5043           this._init({
5044             atom: 'H',
5045             isBracket: 'false',
5046             branches: Array(),
5047             branchCount: 0,
5048             ringbonds: Array(),
5049             ringbondCount: false,
5050             next: null,
5051             hasNext: false,
5052             bond: '-'
5053           }, i, vertex.id, true);
5054         }
5055       }
5056   
5057       for (var i = 0; i < node.branchCount; i++) {
5058         this._init(node.branches[i], i + offset, vertex.id, true);
5059       }
5060   
5061       if (node.hasNext) {
5062         this._init(node.next, node.branchCount + offset, vertex.id);
5063       }
5064     }
5065     /**
5066      * Clears all the elements in this graph (edges and vertices).
5067      */
5068   
5069   
5070     clear() {
5071       this.vertices = Array();
5072       this.edges = Array();
5073       this.vertexIdsToEdgeId = {};
5074     }
5075     /**
5076      * Add a vertex to the graph.
5077      *
5078      * @param {Vertex} vertex A new vertex.
5079      * @returns {Number} The vertex id of the new vertex.
5080      */
5081   
5082   
5083     addVertex(vertex) {
5084       vertex.id = this.vertices.length;
5085       this.vertices.push(vertex);
5086       return vertex.id;
5087     }
5088     /**
5089      * Add an edge to the graph.
5090      *
5091      * @param {Edge} edge A new edge.
5092      * @returns {Number} The edge id of the new edge.
5093      */
5094   
5095   
5096     addEdge(edge) {
5097       let source = this.vertices[edge.sourceId];
5098       let target = this.vertices[edge.targetId];
5099       edge.id = this.edges.length;
5100       this.edges.push(edge);
5101       this.vertexIdsToEdgeId[edge.sourceId + '_' + edge.targetId] = edge.id;
5102       this.vertexIdsToEdgeId[edge.targetId + '_' + edge.sourceId] = edge.id;
5103       edge.isPartOfAromaticRing = source.value.isPartOfAromaticRing && target.value.isPartOfAromaticRing;
5104       source.value.bondCount += edge.weight;
5105       target.value.bondCount += edge.weight;
5106       source.edges.push(edge.id);
5107       target.edges.push(edge.id);
5108       return edge.id;
5109     }
5110     /**
5111      * Returns the edge between two given vertices.
5112      *
5113      * @param {Number} vertexIdA A vertex id.
5114      * @param {Number} vertexIdB A vertex id.
5115      * @returns {(Edge|null)} The edge or, if no edge can be found, null.
5116      */
5117   
5118   
5119     getEdge(vertexIdA, vertexIdB) {
5120       let edgeId = this.vertexIdsToEdgeId[vertexIdA + '_' + vertexIdB];
5121       return edgeId === undefined ? null : this.edges[edgeId];
5122     }
5123     /**
5124      * Returns the ids of edges connected to a vertex.
5125      *
5126      * @param {Number} vertexId A vertex id.
5127      * @returns {Number[]} An array containing the ids of edges connected to the vertex.
5128      */
5129   
5130   
5131     getEdges(vertexId) {
5132       let edgeIds = Array();
5133       let vertex = this.vertices[vertexId];
5134   
5135       for (var i = 0; i < vertex.neighbours.length; i++) {
5136         edgeIds.push(this.vertexIdsToEdgeId[vertexId + '_' + vertex.neighbours[i]]);
5137       }
5138   
5139       return edgeIds;
5140     }
5141     /**
5142      * Check whether or not two vertices are connected by an edge.
5143      *
5144      * @param {Number} vertexIdA A vertex id.
5145      * @param {Number} vertexIdB A vertex id.
5146      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not two vertices are connected by an edge.
5147      */
5148   
5149   
5150     hasEdge(vertexIdA, vertexIdB) {
5151       return this.vertexIdsToEdgeId[vertexIdA + '_' + vertexIdB] !== undefined;
5152     }
5153     /**
5154      * Returns an array containing the vertex ids of this graph.
5155      * 
5156      * @returns {Number[]} An array containing all vertex ids of this graph.
5157      */
5158   
5159   
5160     getVertexList() {
5161       let arr = [this.vertices.length];
5162   
5163       for (var i = 0; i < this.vertices.length; i++) {
5164         arr[i] = this.vertices[i].id;
5165       }
5166   
5167       return arr;
5168     }
5169     /**
5170      * Returns an array containing source, target arrays of this graphs edges.
5171      * 
5172      * @returns {Array[]} An array containing source, target arrays of this graphs edges. Example: [ [ 2, 5 ], [ 6, 9 ] ].
5173      */
5174   
5175   
5176     getEdgeList() {
5177       let arr = Array(this.edges.length);
5178   
5179       for (var i = 0; i < this.edges.length; i++) {
5180         arr[i] = [this.edges[i].sourceId, this.edges[i].targetId];
5181       }
5182   
5183       return arr;
5184     }
5185     /**
5186      * Get the adjacency matrix of the graph.
5187      * 
5188      * @returns {Array[]} The adjancency matrix of the molecular graph.
5189      */
5190   
5191   
5192     getAdjacencyMatrix() {
5193       let length = this.vertices.length;
5194       let adjacencyMatrix = Array(length);
5195   
5196       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5197         adjacencyMatrix[i] = new Array(length);
5198         adjacencyMatrix[i].fill(0);
5199       }
5200   
5201       for (var i = 0; i < this.edges.length; i++) {
5202         let edge = this.edges[i];
5203         adjacencyMatrix[edge.sourceId][edge.targetId] = 1;
5204         adjacencyMatrix[edge.targetId][edge.sourceId] = 1;
5205       }
5206   
5207       return adjacencyMatrix;
5208     }
5209     /**
5210      * Get the adjacency matrix of the graph with all bridges removed (thus the components). Thus the remaining vertices are all part of ring systems.
5211      * 
5212      * @returns {Array[]} The adjancency matrix of the molecular graph with all bridges removed.
5213      */
5214   
5215   
5216     getComponentsAdjacencyMatrix() {
5217       let length = this.vertices.length;
5218       let adjacencyMatrix = Array(length);
5219       let bridges = this.getBridges();
5220   
5221       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5222         adjacencyMatrix[i] = new Array(length);
5223         adjacencyMatrix[i].fill(0);
5224       }
5225   
5226       for (var i = 0; i < this.edges.length; i++) {
5227         let edge = this.edges[i];
5228         adjacencyMatrix[edge.sourceId][edge.targetId] = 1;
5229         adjacencyMatrix[edge.targetId][edge.sourceId] = 1;
5230       }
5231   
5232       for (var i = 0; i < bridges.length; i++) {
5233         adjacencyMatrix[bridges[i][0]][bridges[i][1]] = 0;
5234         adjacencyMatrix[bridges[i][1]][bridges[i][0]] = 0;
5235       }
5236   
5237       return adjacencyMatrix;
5238     }
5239     /**
5240      * Get the adjacency matrix of a subgraph.
5241      * 
5242      * @param {Number[]} vertexIds An array containing the vertex ids contained within the subgraph.
5243      * @returns {Array[]} The adjancency matrix of the subgraph.
5244      */
5245   
5246   
5247     getSubgraphAdjacencyMatrix(vertexIds) {
5248       let length = vertexIds.length;
5249       let adjacencyMatrix = Array(length);
5250   
5251       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5252         adjacencyMatrix[i] = new Array(length);
5253         adjacencyMatrix[i].fill(0);
5254   
5255         for (var j = 0; j < length; j++) {
5256           if (i === j) {
5257             continue;
5258           }
5259   
5260           if (this.hasEdge(vertexIds[i], vertexIds[j])) {
5261             adjacencyMatrix[i][j] = 1;
5262           }
5263         }
5264       }
5265   
5266       return adjacencyMatrix;
5267     }
5268     /**
5269      * Get the distance matrix of the graph.
5270      * 
5271      * @returns {Array[]} The distance matrix of the graph.
5272      */
5273   
5274   
5275     getDistanceMatrix() {
5276       let length = this.vertices.length;
5277       let adja = this.getAdjacencyMatrix();
5278       let dist = Array(length);
5279   
5280       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5281         dist[i] = Array(length);
5282         dist[i].fill(Infinity);
5283       }
5284   
5285       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5286         for (var j = 0; j < length; j++) {
5287           if (adja[i][j] === 1) {
5288             dist[i][j] = 1;
5289           }
5290         }
5291       }
5292   
5293       for (var k = 0; k < length; k++) {
5294         for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5295           for (var j = 0; j < length; j++) {
5296             if (dist[i][j] > dist[i][k] + dist[k][j]) {
5297               dist[i][j] = dist[i][k] + dist[k][j];
5298             }
5299           }
5300         }
5301       }
5302   
5303       return dist;
5304     }
5305     /**
5306      * Get the distance matrix of a subgraph.
5307      * 
5308      * @param {Number[]} vertexIds An array containing the vertex ids contained within the subgraph.
5309      * @returns {Array[]} The distance matrix of the subgraph.
5310      */
5311   
5312   
5313     getSubgraphDistanceMatrix(vertexIds) {
5314       let length = vertexIds.length;
5315       let adja = this.getSubgraphAdjacencyMatrix(vertexIds);
5316       let dist = Array(length);
5317   
5318       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5319         dist[i] = Array(length);
5320         dist[i].fill(Infinity);
5321       }
5322   
5323       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5324         for (var j = 0; j < length; j++) {
5325           if (adja[i][j] === 1) {
5326             dist[i][j] = 1;
5327           }
5328         }
5329       }
5330   
5331       for (var k = 0; k < length; k++) {
5332         for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5333           for (var j = 0; j < length; j++) {
5334             if (dist[i][j] > dist[i][k] + dist[k][j]) {
5335               dist[i][j] = dist[i][k] + dist[k][j];
5336             }
5337           }
5338         }
5339       }
5340   
5341       return dist;
5342     }
5343     /**
5344      * Get the adjacency list of the graph.
5345      * 
5346      * @returns {Array[]} The adjancency list of the graph.
5347      */
5348   
5349   
5350     getAdjacencyList() {
5351       let length = this.vertices.length;
5352       let adjacencyList = Array(length);
5353   
5354       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5355         adjacencyList[i] = [];
5356   
5357         for (var j = 0; j < length; j++) {
5358           if (i === j) {
5359             continue;
5360           }
5361   
5362           if (this.hasEdge(this.vertices[i].id, this.vertices[j].id)) {
5363             adjacencyList[i].push(j);
5364           }
5365         }
5366       }
5367   
5368       return adjacencyList;
5369     }
5370     /**
5371      * Get the adjacency list of a subgraph.
5372      * 
5373      * @param {Number[]} vertexIds An array containing the vertex ids contained within the subgraph.
5374      * @returns {Array[]} The adjancency list of the subgraph.
5375      */
5376   
5377   
5378     getSubgraphAdjacencyList(vertexIds) {
5379       let length = vertexIds.length;
5380       let adjacencyList = Array(length);
5381   
5382       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5383         adjacencyList[i] = Array();
5384   
5385         for (var j = 0; j < length; j++) {
5386           if (i === j) {
5387             continue;
5388           }
5389   
5390           if (this.hasEdge(vertexIds[i], vertexIds[j])) {
5391             adjacencyList[i].push(j);
5392           }
5393         }
5394       }
5395   
5396       return adjacencyList;
5397     }
5398     /**
5399      * Returns an array containing the edge ids of bridges. A bridge splits the graph into multiple components when removed.
5400      * 
5401      * @returns {Number[]} An array containing the edge ids of the bridges.
5402      */
5403   
5404   
5405     getBridges() {
5406       let length = this.vertices.length;
5407       let visited = new Array(length);
5408       let disc = new Array(length);
5409       let low = new Array(length);
5410       let parent = new Array(length);
5411       let adj = this.getAdjacencyList();
5412       let outBridges = Array();
5413       visited.fill(false);
5414       parent.fill(null);
5415       this._time = 0;
5416   
5417       for (var i = 0; i < length; i++) {
5418         if (!visited[i]) {
5419           this._bridgeDfs(i, visited, disc, low, parent, adj, outBridges);
5420         }
5421       }
5422   
5423       return outBridges;
5424     }
5425     /**
5426      * Traverses the graph in breadth-first order.
5427      * 
5428      * @param {Number} startVertexId The id of the starting vertex.
5429      * @param {Function} callback The callback function to be called on every vertex.
5430      */
5431   
5432   
5433     traverseBF(startVertexId, callback) {
5434       let length = this.vertices.length;
5435       let visited = new Array(length);
5436       visited.fill(false);
5437       var queue = [startVertexId];
5438   
5439       while (queue.length > 0) {
5440         // JavaScripts shift() is O(n) ... bad JavaScript, bad!
5441         let u = queue.shift();
5442         let vertex = this.vertices[u];
5443         callback(vertex);
5444   
5445         for (var i = 0; i < vertex.neighbours.length; i++) {
5446           let v = vertex.neighbours[i];
5447   
5448           if (!visited[v]) {
5449             visited[v] = true;
5450             queue.push(v);
5451           }
5452         }
5453       }
5454     }
5455     /**
5456      * Get the depth of a subtree in the direction opposite to the vertex specified as the parent vertex.
5457      *
5458      * @param {Number} vertexId A vertex id.
5459      * @param {Number} parentVertexId The id of a neighbouring vertex.
5460      * @returns {Number} The depth of the sub-tree.
5461      */
5462   
5463   
5464     getTreeDepth(vertexId, parentVertexId) {
5465       if (vertexId === null || parentVertexId === null) {
5466         return 0;
5467       }
5468   
5469       let neighbours = this.vertices[vertexId].getSpanningTreeNeighbours(parentVertexId);
5470       let max = 0;
5471   
5472       for (var i = 0; i < neighbours.length; i++) {
5473         let childId = neighbours[i];
5474         let d = this.getTreeDepth(childId, vertexId);
5475   
5476         if (d > max) {
5477           max = d;
5478         }
5479       }
5480   
5481       return max + 1;
5482     }
5483     /**
5484      * Traverse a sub-tree in the graph.
5485      *
5486      * @param {Number} vertexId A vertex id.
5487      * @param {Number} parentVertexId A neighbouring vertex.
5488      * @param {Function} callback The callback function that is called with each visited as an argument.
5489      * @param {Number} [maxDepth=999999] The maximum depth of the recursion.
5490      * @param {Boolean} [ignoreFirst=false] Whether or not to ignore the starting vertex supplied as vertexId in the callback.
5491      * @param {Number} [depth=1] The current depth in the tree.
5492      * @param {Uint8Array} [visited=null] An array holding a flag on whether or not a node has been visited.
5493      */
5494   
5495   
5496     traverseTree(vertexId, parentVertexId, callback, maxDepth = 999999, ignoreFirst = false, depth = 1, visited = null) {
5497       if (visited === null) {
5498         visited = new Uint8Array(this.vertices.length);
5499       }
5500   
5501       if (depth > maxDepth + 1 || visited[vertexId] === 1) {
5502         return;
5503       }
5504   
5505       visited[vertexId] = 1;
5506       let vertex = this.vertices[vertexId];
5507       let neighbours = vertex.getNeighbours(parentVertexId);
5508   
5509       if (!ignoreFirst || depth > 1) {
5510         callback(vertex);
5511       }
5512   
5513       for (var i = 0; i < neighbours.length; i++) {
5514         this.traverseTree(neighbours[i], vertexId, callback, maxDepth, ignoreFirst, depth + 1, visited);
5515       }
5516     }
5517     /**
5518      * Positiones the (sub)graph using Kamada and Kawais algorithm for drawing general undirected graphs. https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/b8d3/bca50ccc573c5cb99f7d201e8acce6618f04.pdf
5519      * There are undocumented layout parameters. They are undocumented for a reason, so be very careful.
5520      * 
5521      * @param {Number[]} vertexIds An array containing vertexIds to be placed using the force based layout.
5522      * @param {Vector2} center The center of the layout.
5523      * @param {Number} startVertexId A vertex id. Should be the starting vertex - e.g. the first to be positioned and connected to a previously place vertex.
5524      * @param {Ring} ring The bridged ring associated with this force-based layout.
5525      */
5526   
5527   
5528     kkLayout(vertexIds, center, startVertexId, ring, bondLength, threshold = 0.1, innerThreshold = 0.1, maxIteration = 2000, maxInnerIteration = 50, maxEnergy = 1e9) {
5529       let edgeStrength = bondLength; // Add vertices that are directly connected to the ring
5530   
5531       var i = vertexIds.length;
5532   
5533       while (i--) {
5534         let vertex = this.vertices[vertexIds[i]];
5535         var j = vertex.neighbours.length;
5536       }
5537   
5538       let matDist = this.getSubgraphDistanceMatrix(vertexIds);
5539       let length = vertexIds.length; // Initialize the positions. Place all vertices on a ring around the center
5540   
5541       let radius = MathHelper.polyCircumradius(500, length);
5542       let angle = MathHelper.centralAngle(length);
5543       let a = 0.0;
5544       let arrPositionX = new Float32Array(length);
5545       let arrPositionY = new Float32Array(length);
5546       let arrPositioned = Array(length);
5547       i = length;
5548   
5549       while (i--) {
5550         let vertex = this.vertices[vertexIds[i]];
5551   
5552         if (!vertex.positioned) {
5553           arrPositionX[i] = center.x + Math.cos(a) * radius;
5554           arrPositionY[i] = center.y + Math.sin(a) * radius;
5555         } else {
5556           arrPositionX[i] = vertex.position.x;
5557           arrPositionY[i] = vertex.position.y;
5558         }
5559   
5560         arrPositioned[i] = vertex.positioned;
5561         a += angle;
5562       } // Create the matrix containing the lengths
5563   
5564   
5565       let matLength = Array(length);
5566       i = length;
5567   
5568       while (i--) {
5569         matLength[i] = new Array(length);
5570         var j = length;
5571   
5572         while (j--) {
5573           matLength[i][j] = bondLength * matDist[i][j];
5574         }
5575       } // Create the matrix containing the spring strenghts
5576   
5577   
5578       let matStrength = Array(length);
5579       i = length;
5580   
5581       while (i--) {
5582         matStrength[i] = Array(length);
5583         var j = length;
5584   
5585         while (j--) {
5586           matStrength[i][j] = edgeStrength * Math.pow(matDist[i][j], -2.0);
5587         }
5588       } // Create the matrix containing the energies
5589   
5590   
5591       let matEnergy = Array(length);
5592       let arrEnergySumX = new Float32Array(length);
5593       let arrEnergySumY = new Float32Array(length);
5594       i = length;
5595   
5596       while (i--) {
5597         matEnergy[i] = Array(length);
5598       }
5599   
5600       i = length;
5601       let ux, uy, dEx, dEy, vx, vy, denom;
5602   
5603       while (i--) {
5604         ux = arrPositionX[i];
5605         uy = arrPositionY[i];
5606         dEx = 0.0;
5607         dEy = 0.0;
5608         let j = length;
5609   
5610         while (j--) {
5611           if (i === j) {
5612             continue;
5613           }
5614   
5615           vx = arrPositionX[j];
5616           vy = arrPositionY[j];
5617           denom = 1.0 / Math.sqrt((ux - vx) * (ux - vx) + (uy - vy) * (uy - vy));
5618           matEnergy[i][j] = [matStrength[i][j] * (ux - vx - matLength[i][j] * (ux - vx) * denom), matStrength[i][j] * (uy - vy - matLength[i][j] * (uy - vy) * denom)];
5619           matEnergy[j][i] = matEnergy[i][j];
5620           dEx += matEnergy[i][j][0];
5621           dEy += matEnergy[i][j][1];
5622         }
5623   
5624         arrEnergySumX[i] = dEx;
5625         arrEnergySumY[i] = dEy;
5626       } // Utility functions, maybe inline them later
5627   
5628   
5629       let energy = function (index) {
5630         return [arrEnergySumX[index] * arrEnergySumX[index] + arrEnergySumY[index] * arrEnergySumY[index], arrEnergySumX[index], arrEnergySumY[index]];
5631       };
5632   
5633       let highestEnergy = function () {
5634         let maxEnergy = 0.0;
5635         let maxEnergyId = 0;
5636         let maxDEX = 0.0;
5637         let maxDEY = 0.0;
5638         i = length;
5639   
5640         while (i--) {
5641           let [delta, dEX, dEY] = energy(i);
5642   
5643           if (delta > maxEnergy && arrPositioned[i] === false) {
5644             maxEnergy = delta;
5645             maxEnergyId = i;
5646             maxDEX = dEX;
5647             maxDEY = dEY;
5648           }
5649         }
5650   
5651         return [maxEnergyId, maxEnergy, maxDEX, maxDEY];
5652       };
5653   
5654       let update = function (index, dEX, dEY) {
5655         let dxx = 0.0;
5656         let dyy = 0.0;
5657         let dxy = 0.0;
5658         let ux = arrPositionX[index];
5659         let uy = arrPositionY[index];
5660         let arrL = matLength[index];
5661         let arrK = matStrength[index];
5662         i = length;
5663   
5664         while (i--) {
5665           if (i === index) {
5666             continue;
5667           }
5668   
5669           let vx = arrPositionX[i];
5670           let vy = arrPositionY[i];
5671           let l = arrL[i];
5672           let k = arrK[i];
5673           let m = (ux - vx) * (ux - vx);
5674           let denom = 1.0 / Math.pow(m + (uy - vy) * (uy - vy), 1.5);
5675           dxx += k * (1 - l * (uy - vy) * (uy - vy) * denom);
5676           dyy += k * (1 - l * m * denom);
5677           dxy += k * (l * (ux - vx) * (uy - vy) * denom);
5678         } // Prevent division by zero
5679   
5680   
5681         if (dxx === 0) {
5682           dxx = 0.1;
5683         }
5684   
5685         if (dyy === 0) {
5686           dyy = 0.1;
5687         }
5688   
5689         if (dxy === 0) {
5690           dxy = 0.1;
5691         }
5692   
5693         let dy = dEX / dxx + dEY / dxy;
5694         dy /= dxy / dxx - dyy / dxy; // had to split this onto two lines because the syntax highlighter went crazy.
5695   
5696         let dx = -(dxy * dy + dEX) / dxx;
5697         arrPositionX[index] += dx;
5698         arrPositionY[index] += dy; // Update the energies
5699   
5700         let arrE = matEnergy[index];
5701         dEX = 0.0;
5702         dEY = 0.0;
5703         ux = arrPositionX[index];
5704         uy = arrPositionY[index];
5705         let vx, vy, prevEx, prevEy, denom;
5706         i = length;
5707   
5708         while (i--) {
5709           if (index === i) {
5710             continue;
5711           }
5712   
5713           vx = arrPositionX[i];
5714           vy = arrPositionY[i]; // Store old energies
5715   
5716           prevEx = arrE[i][0];
5717           prevEy = arrE[i][1];
5718           denom = 1.0 / Math.sqrt((ux - vx) * (ux - vx) + (uy - vy) * (uy - vy));
5719           dx = arrK[i] * (ux - vx - arrL[i] * (ux - vx) * denom);
5720           dy = arrK[i] * (uy - vy - arrL[i] * (uy - vy) * denom);
5721           arrE[i] = [dx, dy];
5722           dEX += dx;
5723           dEY += dy;
5724           arrEnergySumX[i] += dx - prevEx;
5725           arrEnergySumY[i] += dy - prevEy;
5726         }
5727   
5728         arrEnergySumX[index] = dEX;
5729         arrEnergySumY[index] = dEY;
5730       }; // Setting up variables for the while loops
5731   
5732   
5733       let maxEnergyId = 0;
5734       let dEX = 0.0;
5735       let dEY = 0.0;
5736       let delta = 0.0;
5737       let iteration = 0;
5738       let innerIteration = 0;
5739   
5740       while (maxEnergy > threshold && maxIteration > iteration) {
5741         iteration++;
5742         [maxEnergyId, maxEnergy, dEX, dEY] = highestEnergy();
5743         delta = maxEnergy;
5744         innerIteration = 0;
5745   
5746         while (delta > innerThreshold && maxInnerIteration > innerIteration) {
5747           innerIteration++;
5748           update(maxEnergyId, dEX, dEY);
5749           [delta, dEX, dEY] = energy(maxEnergyId);
5750         }
5751       }
5752   
5753       i = length;
5754   
5755       while (i--) {
5756         let index = vertexIds[i];
5757         let vertex = this.vertices[index];
5758         vertex.position.x = arrPositionX[i];
5759         vertex.position.y = arrPositionY[i];
5760         vertex.positioned = true;
5761         vertex.forcePositioned = true;
5762       }
5763     }
5764     /**
5765      * PRIVATE FUNCTION used by getBridges().
5766      */
5767   
5768   
5769     _bridgeDfs(u, visited, disc, low, parent, adj, outBridges) {
5770       visited[u] = true;
5771       disc[u] = low[u] = ++this._time;
5772   
5773       for (var i = 0; i < adj[u].length; i++) {
5774         let v = adj[u][i];
5775   
5776         if (!visited[v]) {
5777           parent[v] = u;
5778   
5779           this._bridgeDfs(v, visited, disc, low, parent, adj, outBridges);
5780   
5781           low[u] = Math.min(low[u], low[v]); // If low > disc, we have a bridge
5782   
5783           if (low[v] > disc[u]) {
5784             outBridges.push([u, v]);
5785           }
5786         } else if (v !== parent[u]) {
5787           low[u] = Math.min(low[u], disc[v]);
5788         }
5789       }
5790     }
5791     /**
5792      * Returns the connected components of the graph.
5793      * 
5794      * @param {Array[]} adjacencyMatrix An adjacency matrix.
5795      * @returns {Set[]} Connected components as sets.
5796      */
5797   
5798   
5799     static getConnectedComponents(adjacencyMatrix) {
5800       let length = adjacencyMatrix.length;
5801       let visited = new Array(length);
5802       let components = new Array();
5803       let count = 0;
5804       visited.fill(false);
5805   
5806       for (var u = 0; u < length; u++) {
5807         if (!visited[u]) {
5808           let component = Array();
5809           visited[u] = true;
5810           component.push(u);
5811           count++;
5812   
5813           Graph._ccGetDfs(u, visited, adjacencyMatrix, component);
5814   
5815           if (component.length > 1) {
5816             components.push(component);
5817           }
5818         }
5819       }
5820   
5821       return components;
5822     }
5823     /**
5824      * Returns the number of connected components for the graph. 
5825      * 
5826      * @param {Array[]} adjacencyMatrix An adjacency matrix.
5827      * @returns {Number} The number of connected components of the supplied graph.
5828      */
5829   
5830   
5831     static getConnectedComponentCount(adjacencyMatrix) {
5832       let length = adjacencyMatrix.length;
5833       let visited = new Array(length);
5834       let count = 0;
5835       visited.fill(false);
5836   
5837       for (var u = 0; u < length; u++) {
5838         if (!visited[u]) {
5839           visited[u] = true;
5840           count++;
5841   
5842           Graph._ccCountDfs(u, visited, adjacencyMatrix);
5843         }
5844       }
5845   
5846       return count;
5847     }
5848     /**
5849      * PRIVATE FUNCTION used by getConnectedComponentCount().
5850      */
5851   
5852   
5853     static _ccCountDfs(u, visited, adjacencyMatrix) {
5854       for (var v = 0; v < adjacencyMatrix[u].length; v++) {
5855         let c = adjacencyMatrix[u][v];
5856   
5857         if (!c || visited[v] || u === v) {
5858           continue;
5859         }
5860   
5861         visited[v] = true;
5862   
5863         Graph._ccCountDfs(v, visited, adjacencyMatrix);
5864       }
5865     }
5866     /**
5867      * PRIVATE FUNCTION used by getConnectedComponents().
5868      */
5869   
5870   
5871     static _ccGetDfs(u, visited, adjacencyMatrix, component) {
5872       for (var v = 0; v < adjacencyMatrix[u].length; v++) {
5873         let c = adjacencyMatrix[u][v];
5874   
5875         if (!c || visited[v] || u === v) {
5876           continue;
5877         }
5878   
5879         visited[v] = true;
5880         component.push(v);
5881   
5882         Graph._ccGetDfs(v, visited, adjacencyMatrix, component);
5883       }
5884     }
5885   
5886   }

5922       this.elementTo = elementTo;
5923       this.chiralFrom = chiralFrom;

6079         this.to.y = y;

6094       return this;

6096     /**
6097      * Rotate the line by a given value (in radians). The center of rotation is the left vector.
6098      *
6099      * @param {Number} theta The angle (in radians) to rotate the line.
6100      * @returns {Line} This line.
6101      */
6102   
6103   
6104     rotate(theta) {
6105       let l = this.getLeftVector();
6106       let r = this.getRightVector();
6107       let sinTheta = Math.sin(theta);
6108       let cosTheta = Math.cos(theta);
6109       let x = cosTheta * (r.x - l.x) - sinTheta * (r.y - l.y) + l.x;
6110       let y = sinTheta * (r.x - l.x) - cosTheta * (r.y - l.y) + l.y;
6111       this.setRightVector(x, y);
6112       return this;

6190       this.to.add(f);

6205   class MathHelper {
6206     /**
6207      * Rounds a value to a given number of decimals.
6208      *
6209      * @static
6210      * @param {Number} value A number.
6211      * @param {Number} decimals The number of decimals.
6212      * @returns {Number} A number rounded to a given number of decimals.
6213      */
6214     static round(value, decimals) {
6215       decimals = decimals ? decimals : 1;
6216       return Number(Math.round(value + 'e' + decimals) + 'e-' + decimals);
6217     }
6218     /**
6219      * Returns the means of the angles contained in an array. In radians.
6220      *
6221      * @static
6222      * @param {Number[]} arr An array containing angles (in radians).
6223      * @returns {Number} The mean angle in radians.
6224      */
6225   
6226   
6227     static meanAngle(arr) {
6228       let sin = 0.0;
6229       let cos = 0.0;
6230   
6231       for (var i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
6232         sin += Math.sin(arr[i]);
6233         cos += Math.cos(arr[i]);
6234       }
6235   
6236       return Math.atan2(sin / arr.length, cos / arr.length);
6237     }
6238     /**
6239      * Returns the inner angle of a n-sided regular polygon.
6240      *
6241      * @static
6242      * @param {Number} n Number of sides of a regular polygon.
6243      * @returns {Number} The inner angle of a given regular polygon.
6244      */
6245   
6246   
6247     static innerAngle(n) {
6248       return MathHelper.toRad((n - 2) * 180 / n);
6249     }
6250     /**
6251      * Returns the circumradius of a n-sided regular polygon with a given side-length.
6252      *
6253      * @static
6254      * @param {Number} s The side length of the regular polygon.
6255      * @param {Number} n The number of sides.
6256      * @returns {Number} The circumradius of the regular polygon.
6257      */
6258   
6259   
6260     static polyCircumradius(s, n) {
6261       return s / (2 * Math.sin(Math.PI / n));
6262     }
6263     /**
6264      * Returns the apothem of a regular n-sided polygon based on its radius.
6265      *
6266      * @static
6267      * @param {Number} r The radius.
6268      * @param {Number} n The number of edges of the regular polygon.
6269      * @returns {Number} The apothem of a n-sided polygon based on its radius.
6270      */
6271   
6272   
6273     static apothem(r, n) {
6274       return r * Math.cos(Math.PI / n);
6275     }
6276   
6277     static apothemFromSideLength(s, n) {
6278       let r = MathHelper.polyCircumradius(s, n);
6279       return MathHelper.apothem(r, n);
6280     }

6286      * @returns {Number} The central angle of the n-sided polygon in radians.
6287      */
6288   
6289

6291       return MathHelper.toRad(360 / n);

6293     /**

6296      * @static
6297      * @param {Number} rad An angle in radians.
6298      * @returns {Number} The angle in degrees.
6299      */
6300   
6301   
6302     static toDeg(rad) {
6303       return rad * MathHelper.degFactor;
6304     }
6305     /**
6306      * Converts degrees to radians.
6307      *
6308      * @static
6309      * @param {Number} deg An angle in degrees.
6310      * @returns {Number} The angle in radians.
6311      */
6312   
6313   
6314     static toRad(deg) {
6315       return deg * MathHelper.radFactor;
6316     }
6317     /**
6318      * Returns the parity of the permutation (1 or -1)
6319      * @param {(Array|Uint8Array)} arr An array containing the permutation.
6320      * @returns {Number} The parity of the permutation (1 or -1), where 1 means even and -1 means odd.
6321      */
6322   
6323   
6324     static parityOfPermutation(arr) {
6325       let visited = new Uint8Array(arr.length);
6326       let evenLengthCycleCount = 0;
6327   
6328       let traverseCycle = function (i, cycleLength = 0) {
6329         if (visited[i] === 1) {
6330           return cycleLength;
6331         }
6332   
6333         cycleLength++;
6334         visited[i] = 1;
6335         return traverseCycle(arr[i], cycleLength);
6336       };
6337   
6338       for (var i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
6339         if (visited[i] === 1) {
6340           continue;
6341         }
6342   
6343         let cycleLength = traverseCycle(i);
6344         evenLengthCycleCount += 1 - cycleLength % 2;
6345       }
6346   
6347       return evenLengthCycleCount % 2 ? -1 : 1;
6348     }
6349     /** The factor to convert degrees to radians. */
6350   
6351   
6352     static get radFactor() {
6353       return Math.PI / 180.0;
6354     }
6355     /** The factor to convert radians to degrees. */
6356   
6357   
6358     static get degFactor() {
6359       return 180.0 / Math.PI;
6360     }
6361     /** Two times PI. */
6362   
6363   
6364     static get twoPI() {
6365       return 2.0 * Math.PI;
6366     }
6367   
6368   }

8275   //@ts-check
8276   const ArrayHelper = require('./ArrayHelper');

8278   const Vector2 = require('./Vector2');
8279   
8280   const Vertex = require('./Vertex');
8281   
8282   const RingConnection = require('./RingConnection');
8283   /** 
8284    * A class representing a ring.
8285    * 
8286    * @property {Number} id The id of this ring.
8287    * @property {Number[]} members An array containing the vertex ids of the ring members.
8288    * @property {Number[]} edges An array containing the edge ids of the edges between the ring members.
8289    * @property {Number[]} insiders An array containing the vertex ids of the vertices contained within the ring if it is a bridged ring.
8290    * @property {Number[]} neighbours An array containing the ids of neighbouring rings.
8291    * @property {Boolean} positioned A boolean indicating whether or not this ring has been positioned.
8292    * @property {Vector2} center The center of this ring.
8293    * @property {Ring[]} rings The rings contained within this ring if this ring is bridged.
8294    * @property {Boolean} isBridged A boolean whether or not this ring is bridged.
8295    * @property {Boolean} isPartOfBridged A boolean whether or not this ring is part of a bridge ring.
8296    * @property {Boolean} isSpiro A boolean whether or not this ring is part of a spiro.
8297    * @property {Boolean} isFused A boolean whether or not this ring is part of a fused ring.
8298    * @property {Number} centralAngle The central angle of this ring.
8299    * @property {Boolean} canFlip A boolean indicating whether or not this ring allows flipping of attached vertices to the inside of the ring.
8300    */
8301   
8302   
8303   class Ring {
8304     /**
8305      * The constructor for the class Ring.
8306      *
8307      * @param {Number[]} members An array containing the vertex ids of the members of the ring to be created.
8308      */
8309     constructor(members) {
8310       this.id = null;
8311       this.members = members;
8312       this.edges = [];
8313       this.insiders = [];
8314       this.neighbours = [];
8315       this.positioned = false;
8316       this.center = new Vector2(0, 0);
8317       this.rings = [];
8318       this.isBridged = false;
8319       this.isPartOfBridged = false;
8320       this.isSpiro = false;
8321       this.isFused = false;
8322       this.centralAngle = 0.0;
8323       this.canFlip = true;
8324     }
8325     /**
8326      * Clones this ring and returns the clone.
8327      *
8328      * @returns {Ring} A clone of this ring.
8329      */
8330   
8331   
8332     clone() {
8333       let clone = new Ring(this.members);
8334       clone.id = this.id;
8335       clone.insiders = ArrayHelper.clone(this.insiders);
8336       clone.neighbours = ArrayHelper.clone(this.neighbours);
8337       clone.positioned = this.positioned;
8338       clone.center = this.center.clone();
8339       clone.rings = ArrayHelper.clone(this.rings);
8340       clone.isBridged = this.isBridged;
8341       clone.isPartOfBridged = this.isPartOfBridged;
8342       clone.isSpiro = this.isSpiro;
8343       clone.isFused = this.isFused;
8344       clone.centralAngle = this.centralAngle;
8345       clone.canFlip = this.canFlip;
8346       return clone;
8347     }
8348     /**
8349      * Returns the size (number of members) of this ring.
8350      *
8351      * @returns {Number} The size (number of members) of this ring.
8352      */
8353   
8354   
8355     getSize() {
8356       return this.members.length;
8357     }
8358     /**
8359      * Gets the polygon representation (an array of the ring-members positional vectors) of this ring.
8360      *
8361      * @param {Vertex[]} vertices An array of vertices representing the current molecule.
8362      * @returns {Vector2[]} An array of the positional vectors of the ring members.
8363      */
8364   
8365   
8366     getPolygon(vertices) {
8367       let polygon = [];
8368   
8369       for (let i = 0; i < this.members.length; i++) {
8370         polygon.push(vertices[this.members[i]].position);
8371       }
8372   
8373       return polygon;
8374     }
8375     /**
8376      * Returns the angle of this ring in relation to the coordinate system.
8377      *
8378      * @returns {Number} The angle in radians.
8379      */
8380   
8381   
8382     getAngle() {
8383       return Math.PI - this.centralAngle;
8384     }
8385     /**
8386      * Loops over the members of this ring from a given start position in a direction opposite to the vertex id passed as the previousId.
8387      *
8388      * @param {Vertex[]} vertices The vertices associated with the current molecule.
8389      * @param {Function} callback A callback with the current vertex id as a parameter.
8390      * @param {Number} startVertexId The vertex id of the start vertex.
8391      * @param {Number} previousVertexId The vertex id of the previous vertex (the loop calling the callback function will run in the opposite direction of this vertex).
8392      */
8393   
8394   
8395     eachMember(vertices, callback, startVertexId, previousVertexId) {
8396       startVertexId = startVertexId || startVertexId === 0 ? startVertexId : this.members[0];
8397       let current = startVertexId;
8398       let max = 0;
8399   
8400       while (current != null && max < 100) {
8401         let prev = current;
8402         callback(prev);
8403         current = vertices[current].getNextInRing(vertices, this.id, previousVertexId);
8404         previousVertexId = prev; // Stop while loop when arriving back at the start vertex
8405   
8406         if (current == startVertexId) {
8407           current = null;
8408         }
8409   
8410         max++;
8411       }
8412     }
8413     /**
8414      * Returns an array containing the neighbouring rings of this ring ordered by ring size.
8415      *
8416      * @param {RingConnection[]} ringConnections An array of ring connections associated with the current molecule.
8417      * @returns {Object[]} An array of neighbouring rings sorted by ring size. Example: { n: 5, neighbour: 1 }.
8418      */
8419   
8420   
8421     getOrderedNeighbours(ringConnections) {
8422       let orderedNeighbours = Array(this.neighbours.length);
8423   
8424       for (let i = 0; i < this.neighbours.length; i++) {
8425         let vertices = RingConnection.getVertices(ringConnections, this.id, this.neighbours[i]);
8426         orderedNeighbours[i] = {
8427           n: vertices.length,
8428           neighbour: this.neighbours[i]
8429         };
8430       }
8431   
8432       orderedNeighbours.sort(function (a, b) {
8433         // Sort highest to lowest
8434         return b.n - a.n;
8435       });
8436       return orderedNeighbours;
8437     }
8438     /**
8439      * Check whether this ring is an implicitly defined benzene-like (e.g. C1=CC=CC=C1) with 6 members and 3 double bonds.
8440      *
8441      * @param {Vertex[]} vertices An array of vertices associated with the current molecule.
8442      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not this ring is an implicitly defined benzene-like.
8443      */
8444   
8445   
8446     isBenzeneLike(vertices) {
8447       let db = this.getDoubleBondCount(vertices);
8448       let length = this.members.length;
8449       return db === 3 && length === 6 || db === 2 && length === 5;
8450     }
8451     /**
8452      * Get the number of double bonds inside this ring.
8453      *
8454      * @param {Vertex[]} vertices An array of vertices associated with the current molecule.
8455      * @returns {Number} The number of double bonds inside this ring.
8456      */
8457   
8458   
8459     getDoubleBondCount(vertices) {
8460       let doubleBondCount = 0;
8461   
8462       for (let i = 0; i < this.members.length; i++) {
8463         let atom = vertices[this.members[i]].value;
8464   
8465         if (atom.bondType === '=' || atom.branchBond === '=') {
8466           doubleBondCount++;
8467         }
8468       }
8469   
8470       return doubleBondCount;
8471     }
8472     /**
8473      * Checks whether or not this ring contains a member with a given vertex id.
8474      *
8475      * @param {Number} vertexId A vertex id.
8476      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not this ring contains a member with the given vertex id.
8477      */
8478   
8479   
8480     contains(vertexId) {
8481       for (let i = 0; i < this.members.length; i++) {
8482         if (this.members[i] == vertexId) {
8483           return true;
8484         }
8485       }
8486   
8487       return false;
8488     }

8659           return [...ringConnection.vertices];

8672   const Graph = require('./Graph');
8673   /** A class encapsulating the functionality to find the smallest set of smallest rings in a graph. */
8674   
8675   
8676   class SSSR {
8677     /**
8678      * Returns an array containing arrays, each representing a ring from the smallest set of smallest rings in the graph.
8679      * 
8680      * @param {Graph} graph A Graph object.
8681      * @param {Boolean} [experimental=false] Whether or not to use experimental SSSR.
8682      * @returns {Array[]} An array containing arrays, each representing a ring from the smallest set of smallest rings in the group.
8683      */
8684     static getRings(graph, experimental = false) {
8685       let adjacencyMatrix = graph.getComponentsAdjacencyMatrix();
8686   
8687       if (adjacencyMatrix.length === 0) {
8688         return null;
8689       }
8690   
8691       let connectedComponents = Graph.getConnectedComponents(adjacencyMatrix);
8692       let rings = Array();
8693   
8694       for (var i = 0; i < connectedComponents.length; i++) {
8695         let connectedComponent = connectedComponents[i];
8696         let ccAdjacencyMatrix = graph.getSubgraphAdjacencyMatrix([...connectedComponent]);
8697         let arrBondCount = new Uint16Array(ccAdjacencyMatrix.length);
8698         let arrRingCount = new Uint16Array(ccAdjacencyMatrix.length);
8699   
8700         for (var j = 0; j < ccAdjacencyMatrix.length; j++) {
8701           arrRingCount[j] = 0;
8702           arrBondCount[j] = 0;
8703   
8704           for (var k = 0; k < ccAdjacencyMatrix[j].length; k++) {
8705             arrBondCount[j] += ccAdjacencyMatrix[j][k];
8706           }
8707         } // Get the edge number and the theoretical number of rings in SSSR
8708   
8709   
8710         let nEdges = 0;
8711   
8712         for (var j = 0; j < ccAdjacencyMatrix.length; j++) {
8713           for (var k = j + 1; k < ccAdjacencyMatrix.length; k++) {
8714             nEdges += ccAdjacencyMatrix[j][k];
8715           }
8716         }
8717   
8718         let nSssr = nEdges - ccAdjacencyMatrix.length + 1; // console.log(nEdges, ccAdjacencyMatrix.length, nSssr);
8719         // console.log(SSSR.getEdgeList(ccAdjacencyMatrix));
8720         // console.log(ccAdjacencyMatrix);
8721         // If all vertices have 3 incident edges, calculate with different formula (see Euler)
8722   
8723         let allThree = true;
8724   
8725         for (var j = 0; j < arrBondCount.length; j++) {
8726           if (arrBondCount[j] !== 3) {
8727             allThree = false;
8728           }
8729         }
8730   
8731         if (allThree) {
8732           nSssr = 2.0 + nEdges - ccAdjacencyMatrix.length;
8733         } // All vertices are part of one ring if theres only one ring.
8734   
8735   
8736         if (nSssr === 1) {
8737           rings.push([...connectedComponent]);
8738           continue;
8739         }
8740   
8741         if (experimental) {
8742           nSssr = 999;
8743         }
8744

8746           d,
8747           pe,
8748           pe_prime
8749         } = SSSR.getPathIncludedDistanceMatrices(ccAdjacencyMatrix);
8750         let c = SSSR.getRingCandidates(d, pe, pe_prime);
8751         let sssr = SSSR.getSSSR(c, d, ccAdjacencyMatrix, pe, pe_prime, arrBondCount, arrRingCount, nSssr);
8752   
8753         for (var j = 0; j < sssr.length; j++) {
8754           let ring = Array(sssr[j].size);
8755           let index = 0;
8756   
8757           for (let val of sssr[j]) {
8758             // Get the original id of the vertex back
8759             ring[index++] = connectedComponent[val];
8760           }
8761   
8762           rings.push(ring);
8763         }
8764       } // So, for some reason, this would return three rings for C1CCCC2CC1CCCC2, which is wrong
8765       // As I don't have time to fix this properly, it will stay in. I'm sorry next person who works
8766       // on it. At that point it might be best to reimplement the whole SSSR thing...
8767   
8768   
8769       return rings;
8770     }
8771     /**
8772      * Creates a printable string from a matrix (2D array).
8773      * 
8774      * @param {Array[]} matrix A 2D array.
8775      * @returns {String} A string representing the matrix.
8776      */
8777   
8778   
8779     static matrixToString(matrix) {
8780       let str = '';
8781   
8782       for (var i = 0; i < matrix.length; i++) {
8783         for (var j = 0; j < matrix[i].length; j++) {
8784           str += matrix[i][j] + ' ';
8785         }
8786   
8787         str += '\n';
8788       }
8789   
8790       return str;
8791     }
8792     /**
8793      * Returnes the two path-included distance matrices used to find the sssr.
8794      * 
8795      * @param {Array[]} adjacencyMatrix An adjacency matrix.
8796      * @returns {Object} The path-included distance matrices. { p1, p2 }
8797      */
8798   
8799   
8800     static getPathIncludedDistanceMatrices(adjacencyMatrix) {
8801       let length = adjacencyMatrix.length;
8802       let d = Array(length);
8803       let pe = Array(length);
8804       let pe_prime = Array(length);
8805       var l = 0;
8806       var m = 0;
8807       var n = 0;
8808       var i = length;
8809   
8810       while (i--) {
8811         d[i] = Array(length);
8812         pe[i] = Array(length);
8813         pe_prime[i] = Array(length);
8814         var j = length;
8815   
8816         while (j--) {
8817           d[i][j] = i === j || adjacencyMatrix[i][j] === 1 ? adjacencyMatrix[i][j] : Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY;
8818   
8819           if (d[i][j] === 1) {
8820             pe[i][j] = [[[i, j]]];
8821           } else {
8822             pe[i][j] = Array();
8823           }
8824   
8825           pe_prime[i][j] = Array();
8826         }
8827       }
8828   
8829       var k = length;
8830       var j;
8831   
8832       while (k--) {
8833         i = length;
8834   
8835         while (i--) {
8836           j = length;
8837   
8838           while (j--) {
8839             const previousPathLength = d[i][j];
8840             const newPathLength = d[i][k] + d[k][j];
8841   
8842             if (previousPathLength > newPathLength) {
8843               var l, m, n;
8844   
8845               if (previousPathLength === newPathLength + 1) {
8846                 pe_prime[i][j] = [pe[i][j].length];
8847                 l = pe[i][j].length;
8848   
8849                 while (l--) {
8850                   pe_prime[i][j][l] = [pe[i][j][l].length];
8851                   m = pe[i][j][l].length;
8852   
8853                   while (m--) {
8854                     pe_prime[i][j][l][m] = [pe[i][j][l][m].length];
8855                     n = pe[i][j][l][m].length;
8856   
8857                     while (n--) {
8858                       pe_prime[i][j][l][m][n] = [pe[i][j][l][m][0], pe[i][j][l][m][1]];
8859                     }
8860                   }
8861                 }
8862               } else {
8863                 pe_prime[i][j] = Array();
8864               }
8865   
8866               d[i][j] = newPathLength;
8867               pe[i][j] = [[]];
8868               l = pe[i][k][0].length;
8869   
8870               while (l--) {
8871                 pe[i][j][0].push(pe[i][k][0][l]);
8872               }
8873   
8874               l = pe[k][j][0].length;
8875   
8876               while (l--) {
8877                 pe[i][j][0].push(pe[k][j][0][l]);
8878               }
8879             } else if (previousPathLength === newPathLength) {
8880               if (pe[i][k].length && pe[k][j].length) {
8881                 var l;
8882   
8883                 if (pe[i][j].length) {
8884                   let tmp = Array();
8885                   l = pe[i][k][0].length;
8886   
8887                   while (l--) {
8888                     tmp.push(pe[i][k][0][l]);
8889                   }
8890   
8891                   l = pe[k][j][0].length;
8892   
8893                   while (l--) {
8894                     tmp.push(pe[k][j][0][l]);
8895                   }
8896   
8897                   pe[i][j].push(tmp);
8898                 } else {
8899                   let tmp = Array();
8900                   l = pe[i][k][0].length;
8901   
8902                   while (l--) {
8903                     tmp.push(pe[i][k][0][l]);
8904                   }
8905   
8906                   l = pe[k][j][0].length;
8907   
8908                   while (l--) {
8909                     tmp.push(pe[k][j][0][l]);
8910                   }
8911   
8912                   pe[i][j][0] = tmp;
8913                 }
8914               }
8915             } else if (previousPathLength === newPathLength - 1) {
8916               var l;
8917   
8918               if (pe_prime[i][j].length) {
8919                 let tmp = Array();
8920                 l = pe[i][k][0].length;
8921   
8922                 while (l--) {
8923                   tmp.push(pe[i][k][0][l]);
8924                 }

8939                 }

8951         }

8953

8956         pe: pe,
8957         pe_prime: pe_prime

8959     }
8960     /**
8961      * Get the ring candidates from the path-included distance matrices.
8962      * 
8963      * @param {Array[]} d The distance matrix.
8964      * @param {Array[]} pe A matrix containing the shortest paths.
8965      * @param {Array[]} pe_prime A matrix containing the shortest paths + one vertex.
8966      * @returns {Array[]} The ring candidates.
8967      */
8968   
8969   
8970     static getRingCandidates(d, pe, pe_prime) {
8971       let length = d.length;
8972       let candidates = Array();
8973       let c = 0;
8974   
8975       for (let i = 0; i < length; i++) {
8976         for (let j = 0; j < length; j++) {
8977           if (d[i][j] === 0 || pe[i][j].length === 1 && pe_prime[i][j] === 0) {
8978             continue;
8979           } else {
8980             // c is the number of vertices in the cycle.
8981             if (pe_prime[i][j].length !== 0) {
8982               c = 2 * (d[i][j] + 0.5);
8983             } else {
8984               c = 2 * d[i][j];
8985             }
8986   
8987             if (c !== Infinity) {
8988               candidates.push([c, pe[i][j], pe_prime[i][j]]);
8989             }
8990           }
8991         }
8992       } // Candidates have to be sorted by c
8993   
8994   
8995       candidates.sort(function (a, b) {
8996         return a[0] - b[0];
8997       });
8998       return candidates;
8999     }
9000     /**
9001      * Searches the candidates for the smallest set of smallest rings.
9002      * 
9003      * @param {Array[]} c The candidates.
9004      * @param {Array[]} d The distance matrix.
9005      * @param {Array[]} adjacencyMatrix An adjacency matrix.
9006      * @param {Array[]} pe A matrix containing the shortest paths.
9007      * @param {Array[]} pe_prime A matrix containing the shortest paths + one vertex.
9008      * @param {Uint16Array} arrBondCount A matrix containing the bond count of each vertex.
9009      * @param {Uint16Array} arrRingCount A matrix containing the number of rings associated with each vertex.
9010      * @param {Number} nsssr The theoretical number of rings in the graph.
9011      * @returns {Set[]} The smallest set of smallest rings.
9012      */
9013   
9014   
9015     static getSSSR(c, d, adjacencyMatrix, pe, pe_prime, arrBondCount, arrRingCount, nsssr) {
9016       let cSssr = Array();
9017       let allBonds = Array();
9018   
9019       for (let i = 0; i < c.length; i++) {
9020         if (c[i][0] % 2 !== 0) {
9021           for (let j = 0; j < c[i][2].length; j++) {
9022             let bonds = c[i][1][0].concat(c[i][2][j]); // Some bonds are added twice, resulting in [[u, v], [u, v]] instead of [u, v].
9023             // TODO: This is a workaround, fix later. Probably should be a set rather than an array, however the computational overhead
9024             //       is probably bigger compared to leaving it like this.
9025   
9026             for (var k = 0; k < bonds.length; k++) {
9027               if (bonds[k][0].constructor === Array) bonds[k] = bonds[k][0];
9028             }
9029   
9030             let atoms = SSSR.bondsToAtoms(bonds);
9031   
9032             if (SSSR.getBondCount(atoms, adjacencyMatrix) === atoms.size && !SSSR.pathSetsContain(cSssr, atoms, bonds, allBonds, arrBondCount, arrRingCount)) {
9033               cSssr.push(atoms);
9034               allBonds = allBonds.concat(bonds);
9035             }
9036   
9037             if (cSssr.length > nsssr) {
9038               return cSssr;
9039             }
9040           }
9041         } else {
9042           for (let j = 0; j < c[i][1].length - 1; j++) {
9043             let bonds = c[i][1][j].concat(c[i][1][j + 1]); // Some bonds are added twice, resulting in [[u, v], [u, v]] instead of [u, v].
9044             // TODO: This is a workaround, fix later. Probably should be a set rather than an array, however the computational overhead
9045             //       is probably bigger compared to leaving it like this.
9046   
9047             for (var k = 0; k < bonds.length; k++) {
9048               if (bonds[k][0].constructor === Array) bonds[k] = bonds[k][0];
9049             }
9050   
9051             let atoms = SSSR.bondsToAtoms(bonds);
9052   
9053             if (SSSR.getBondCount(atoms, adjacencyMatrix) === atoms.size && !SSSR.pathSetsContain(cSssr, atoms, bonds, allBonds, arrBondCount, arrRingCount)) {
9054               cSssr.push(atoms);
9055               allBonds = allBonds.concat(bonds);
9056             }
9057   
9058             if (cSssr.length > nsssr) {
9059               return cSssr;
9060             }
9061           }
9062         }
9063       }
9064   
9065       return cSssr;
9066     }
9067     /**
9068      * Returns the number of edges in a graph defined by an adjacency matrix.
9069      * 
9070      * @param {Array[]} adjacencyMatrix An adjacency matrix.
9071      * @returns {Number} The number of edges in the graph defined by the adjacency matrix.
9072      */
9073   
9074   
9075     static getEdgeCount(adjacencyMatrix) {
9076       let edgeCount = 0;
9077       let length = adjacencyMatrix.length;
9078       var i = length - 1;
9079   
9080       while (i--) {
9081         var j = length;
9082   
9083         while (j--) {
9084           if (adjacencyMatrix[i][j] === 1) {
9085             edgeCount++;
9086           }
9087         }
9088       }
9089   
9090       return edgeCount;
9091     }
9092     /**
9093      * Returns an edge list constructed form an adjacency matrix.
9094      * 
9095      * @param {Array[]} adjacencyMatrix An adjacency matrix.
9096      * @returns {Array[]} An edge list. E.g. [ [ 0, 1 ], ..., [ 16, 2 ] ]
9097      */
9098   
9099   
9100     static getEdgeList(adjacencyMatrix) {
9101       let length = adjacencyMatrix.length;
9102       let edgeList = Array();
9103       var i = length - 1;
9104   
9105       while (i--) {
9106         var j = length;
9107   
9108         while (j--) {
9109           if (adjacencyMatrix[i][j] === 1) {
9110             edgeList.push([i, j]);
9111           }
9112         }
9113       }
9114   
9115       return edgeList;
9116     }
9117     /**
9118      * Return a set of vertex indices contained in an array of bonds.
9119      * 
9120      * @param {Array} bonds An array of bonds. A bond is defined as [ sourceVertexId, targetVertexId ].
9121      * @returns {Set<Number>} An array of vertices.
9122      */
9123   
9124   
9125     static bondsToAtoms(bonds) {
9126       let atoms = new Set();
9127       var i = bonds.length;
9128   
9129       while (i--) {
9130         atoms.add(bonds[i][0]);
9131         atoms.add(bonds[i][1]);
9132       }
9133   
9134       return atoms;
9135     }
9136     /**
9137     * Returns the number of bonds within a set of atoms.
9138     * 
9139     * @param {Set<Number>} atoms An array of atom ids.
9140     * @param {Array[]} adjacencyMatrix An adjacency matrix.
9141     * @returns {Number} The number of bonds in a set of atoms.
9142     */
9143   
9144   
9145     static getBondCount(atoms, adjacencyMatrix) {
9146       let count = 0;
9147   
9148       for (let u of atoms) {
9149         for (let v of atoms) {
9150           if (u === v) {
9151             continue;
9152           }
9153   
9154           count += adjacencyMatrix[u][v];
9155         }
9156       }
9157   
9158       return count / 2;
9159     }
9160     /**
9161      * Checks whether or not a given path already exists in an array of paths.
9162      * 
9163      * @param {Set[]} pathSets An array of sets each representing a path.
9164      * @param {Set<Number>} pathSet A set representing a path.
9165      * @param {Array[]} bonds The bonds associated with the current path.
9166      * @param {Array[]} allBonds All bonds currently associated with rings in the SSSR set.
9167      * @param {Uint16Array} arrBondCount A matrix containing the bond count of each vertex.
9168      * @param {Uint16Array} arrRingCount A matrix containing the number of rings associated with each vertex.
9169      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not a give path is contained within a set.
9170      */
9171   
9172   
9173     static pathSetsContain(pathSets, pathSet, bonds, allBonds, arrBondCount, arrRingCount) {
9174       var i = pathSets.length;
9175   
9176       while (i--) {
9177         if (SSSR.isSupersetOf(pathSet, pathSets[i])) {
9178           return true;
9179         }
9180   
9181         if (pathSets[i].size !== pathSet.size) {
9182           continue;
9183         }
9184   
9185         if (SSSR.areSetsEqual(pathSets[i], pathSet)) {
9186           return true;
9187         }
9188       } // Check if the edges from the candidate are already all contained within the paths of the set of paths.
9189       // TODO: For some reason, this does not replace the isSupersetOf method above -> why?
9190   
9191   
9192       let count = 0;
9193       let allContained = false;
9194       i = bonds.length;
9195   
9196       while (i--) {
9197         var j = allBonds.length;
9198   
9199         while (j--) {
9200           if (bonds[i][0] === allBonds[j][0] && bonds[i][1] === allBonds[j][1] || bonds[i][1] === allBonds[j][0] && bonds[i][0] === allBonds[j][1]) {
9201             count++;
9202           }
9203   
9204           if (count === bonds.length) {
9205             allContained = true;
9206           }
9207         }
9208       } // If all the bonds and thus vertices are already contained within other rings
9209       // check if there's one vertex with ringCount < bondCount
9210   
9211   
9212       let specialCase = false;
9213   
9214       if (allContained) {
9215         for (let element of pathSet) {
9216           if (arrRingCount[element] < arrBondCount[element]) {
9217             specialCase = true;
9218             break;
9219           }
9220         }
9221       }
9222   
9223       if (allContained && !specialCase) {
9224         return true;
9225       } // Update the ring counts for the vertices
9226   
9227   
9228       for (let element of pathSet) {
9229         arrRingCount[element]++;
9230       }
9231   
9232       return false;
9233     }
9234     /**
9235      * Checks whether or not two sets are equal (contain the same elements).
9236      * 
9237      * @param {Set<Number>} setA A set.
9238      * @param {Set<Number>} setB A set.
9239      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not the two sets are equal.
9240      */
9241   
9242   
9243     static areSetsEqual(setA, setB) {
9244       if (setA.size !== setB.size) {
9245         return false;
9246       }
9247   
9248       for (let element of setA) {
9249         if (!setB.has(element)) {
9250           return false;
9251         }
9252       }
9253   
9254       return true;
9255     }
9256     /**
9257      * Checks whether or not a set (setA) is a superset of another set (setB).
9258      * 
9259      * @param {Set<Number>} setA A set.
9260      * @param {Set<Number>} setB A set.
9261      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not setB is a superset of setA.
9262      */
9263   
9264   
9265     static isSupersetOf(setA, setB) {
9266       for (var element of setB) {
9267         if (!setA.has(element)) {
9268           return false;
9269         }
9270       }
9271   
9272       return true;
9273     }
9274   
9275   }

9657       // TODO: add the defs element to put gradients in
9658       let defs = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'defs'),
9659           masks = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'mask'),
9660           style = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'style'),
9661           paths = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'g'),
9662           vertices = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'g'),
9663           pathChildNodes = this.paths; // give the mask an id
9664   
9665       masks.setAttributeNS(null, 'id', 'text-mask'); // create the css styles
9666   
9667       style.appendChild(document.createTextNode(`
9668                   .element {
9669                       font: ${this.opts.fontSizeLarge}pt Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
9670                       alignment-baseline: 'middle';
9671                   }
9672                   .sub {
9673                       font: ${this.opts.fontSizeSmall}pt Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
9674                   }
9675               `));
9676   
9677       for (let path of pathChildNodes) {
9678         paths.appendChild(path);
9679       }
9680   
9681       for (let vertex of this.vertices) {
9682         vertices.appendChild(vertex);
9683       }
9684   
9685       for (let mask of this.maskElements) {
9686         masks.appendChild(mask);
9687       }
9688   
9689       for (let gradient of this.gradients) {
9690         defs.appendChild(gradient);
9691       }
9692   
9693       paths.setAttributeNS(null, 'mask', 'url(#text-mask)');
9694   
9695       if (this.svg) {
9696         this.svg.appendChild(defs);
9697         this.svg.appendChild(masks);
9698         this.svg.appendChild(style);
9699         this.svg.appendChild(paths);
9700         this.svg.appendChild(vertices);
9701         return this.svg;
9702       } else {
9703         let container = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'g');
9704         container.appendChild(defs);
9705         container.appendChild(masks);
9706         container.appendChild(style);
9707         container.appendChild(paths);
9708         container.appendChild(vertices);
9709         return container;
9710       }
9711     }
9712     /**
9713      * Create a linear gradient to apply to a line
9714      *
9715      * @param {Line} line the line to apply the gradiation to.
9716      */
9717   
9718   
9719     createGradient(line) {
9720       // create the gradient and add it
9721       let gradient = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'linearGradient'),
9722           gradientUrl = `line-${this.gradientId++}`,
9723           l = line.getLeftVector(),
9724           r = line.getRightVector(),
9725           fromX = l.x + this.offsetX,
9726           fromY = l.y + this.offsetY,
9727           toX = r.x + this.offsetX,
9728           toY = r.y + this.offsetY;
9729       gradient.setAttributeNS(null, 'id', gradientUrl);
9730       gradient.setAttributeNS(null, 'gradientUnits', 'userSpaceOnUse');
9731       gradient.setAttributeNS(null, 'x1', fromX);
9732       gradient.setAttributeNS(null, 'y1', fromY);
9733       gradient.setAttributeNS(null, 'x2', toX);
9734       gradient.setAttributeNS(null, 'y2', toY);
9735       let firstStop = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'stop');
9736       firstStop.setAttributeNS(null, 'stop-color', this.themeManager.getColor(line.getLeftElement()) || this.themeManager.getColor('C'));
9737       firstStop.setAttributeNS(null, 'offset', '20%');
9738       let secondStop = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'stop');
9739       secondStop.setAttributeNS(null, 'stop-color', this.themeManager.getColor(line.getRightElement() || this.themeManager.getColor('C')));
9740       secondStop.setAttributeNS(null, 'offset', '100%');
9741       gradient.appendChild(firstStop);
9742       gradient.appendChild(secondStop);
9743       this.gradients.push(gradient);
9744       return gradientUrl;
9745     }
9746     /**
9747      * Create a tspan element for sub or super scripts that styles the text
9748      * appropriately as one of those text types.
9749      *
9750      * @param {String} text the actual text
9751      * @param {String} shift the type of text, either 'sub', or 'super'
9752      */
9753   
9754   
9755     createSubSuperScripts(text, shift) {
9756       let elem = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'tspan');
9757       elem.setAttributeNS(null, 'baseline-shift', shift);
9758       elem.appendChild(document.createTextNode(text));
9759       elem.setAttributeNS(null, 'class', 'sub');
9760       return elem;
9761     }
9762     /**
9763      * Determine drawing dimensiosn based on vertex positions.
9764      *
9765      * @param {Vertex[]} vertices An array of vertices containing the vertices associated with the current molecule.
9766      */
9767   
9768   
9769     determineDimensions(vertices) {
9770       // Figure out the final size of the image
9771       let maxX = -Number.MAX_VALUE;
9772       let maxY = -Number.MAX_VALUE;
9773       let minX = Number.MAX_VALUE;
9774       let minY = Number.MAX_VALUE;
9775   
9776       for (var i = 0; i < vertices.length; i++) {
9777         if (!vertices[i].value.isDrawn) {
9778           continue;
9779         }
9780   
9781         let p = vertices[i].position;
9782         if (maxX < p.x) maxX = p.x;
9783         if (maxY < p.y) maxY = p.y;
9784         if (minX > p.x) minX = p.x;
9785         if (minY > p.y) minY = p.y;
9786       } // Add padding
9787   
9788   
9789       let padding = this.opts.padding;
9790       maxX += padding;
9791       maxY += padding;
9792       minX -= padding;
9793       minY -= padding;
9794       this.drawingWidth = maxX - minX;
9795       this.drawingHeight = maxY - minY;
9796       let scaleX = this.svg.clientWidth / this.drawingWidth;
9797       let scaleY = this.svg.clientHeight / this.drawingHeight;
9798       let scale = scaleX < scaleY ? scaleX : scaleY;
9799       let viewBoxDim = Math.round(this.drawingWidth > this.drawingHeight ? this.drawingWidth : this.drawingHeight);
9800       this.svg.setAttributeNS(null, 'viewBox', `0 0 ${viewBoxDim} ${viewBoxDim}`);
9801       this.offsetX = -minX;
9802       this.offsetY = -minY; // Center
9803   
9804       if (scaleX < scaleY) {
9805         this.offsetY += this.svg.clientHeight / (2.0 * scale) - this.drawingHeight / 2.0;
9806       } else {
9807         this.offsetX += this.svg.clientWidth / (2.0 * scale) - this.drawingWidth / 2.0;
9808       }
9809     }
9810     /**
9811      * Draw an svg ellipse as a ball.
9812      *
9813      * @param {Number} x The x position of the text.
9814      * @param {Number} y The y position of the text.
9815      * @param {String} elementName The name of the element (single-letter).
9816      */
9817   
9818   
9819     drawBall(x, y, elementName) {
9820       let ball = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'circle');
9821       ball.setAttributeNS(null, 'cx', x + this.offsetX);
9822       ball.setAttributeNS(null, 'cy', y + this.offsetY);
9823       ball.setAttributeNS(null, 'r', this.opts.bondLength / 4.5);
9824       ball.setAttributeNS(null, 'fill', this.themeManager.getColor(elementName));
9825       this.vertices.push(ball);
9826     }
9827     /**
9828      * Draw a dashed wedge on the canvas.
9829      *
9830      * @param {Line} line A line.
9831      */
9832   
9833   
9834     drawDashedWedge(line) {
9835       if (isNaN(line.from.x) || isNaN(line.from.y) || isNaN(line.to.x) || isNaN(line.to.y)) {
9836         return;
9837       }
9838   
9839       let offsetX = this.offsetX,
9840           offsetY = this.offsetY,
9841           l = line.getLeftVector().clone(),
9842           r = line.getRightVector().clone(),
9843           normals = Vector2.normals(l, r);
9844       normals[0].normalize();
9845       normals[1].normalize();
9846       let isRightChiralCenter = line.getRightChiral(),
9847           start,
9848           end;
9849   
9850       if (isRightChiralCenter) {
9851         start = r;
9852         end = l;
9853       } else {
9854         start = l;
9855         end = r;
9856       }
9857   
9858       let dir = Vector2.subtract(end, start).normalize(),
9859           length = line.getLength(),
9860           step = 1.25 / (length / (this.opts.bondThickness * 3.0)),
9861           changed = false;
9862       let gradient = this.createGradient(line);
9863   
9864       for (let t = 0.0; t < 1.0; t += step) {
9865         let to = Vector2.multiplyScalar(dir, t * length),
9866             startDash = Vector2.add(start, to),
9867             width = 1.5 * t,
9868             dashOffset = Vector2.multiplyScalar(normals[0], width);
9869         startDash.subtract(dashOffset);
9870         let endDash = startDash.clone();
9871         endDash.add(Vector2.multiplyScalar(dashOffset, 2.0));
9872         this.drawLine(new Line(startDash, endDash), null, gradient);
9873       }
9874     }
