9976     /**
9977      * Draw a text to the canvas.
9978      *
9979      * @param {Number} x The x position of the text.
9980      * @param {Number} y The y position of the text.
9981      * @param {String} elementName The name of the element (single-letter).
9982      * @param {Number} hydrogens The number of hydrogen atoms.
9983      * @param {String} direction The direction of the text in relation to the associated vertex.
9984      * @param {Boolean} isTerminal A boolean indicating whether or not the vertex is terminal.
9985      * @param {Number} charge The charge of the atom.
9986      * @param {Number} isotope The isotope number.
9987      * @param {Object} attachedPseudoElement A map with containing information for pseudo elements or concatinated elements. The key is comprised of the element symbol and the hydrogen count.
9988      * @param {String} attachedPseudoElement.element The element symbol.
9989      * @param {Number} attachedPseudoElement.count The number of occurences that match the key.
9990      * @param {Number} attachedPseudoElement.hyrogenCount The number of hydrogens attached to each atom matching the key.
9991      */
9992   
9993   
9994     drawText(x, y, elementName, hydrogens, direction, isTerminal, charge, isotope, attachedPseudoElement = {}) {
9995       let offsetX = this.offsetX,
9996           offsetY = this.offsetY,
9997           pos = {
9998         x: x + offsetX,
9999         y: y + offsetY
10000       },
10001           textElem = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'text'),
10002           writingMode = 'horizontal-tb',
10003           letterSpacing = 'normal',
10004           textOrientation = 'mixed',
10005           textDirection = 'direction: ltr;',
10006           xShift = -2,
10007           yShift = 2.5;
10008       let mask = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'circle');
10009       mask.setAttributeNS(null, 'cx', pos.x);
10010       mask.setAttributeNS(null, 'cy', pos.y);
10011       mask.setAttributeNS(null, 'r', '3.5');
10012       mask.setAttributeNS(null, 'fill', 'black');
10013       this.maskElements.push(mask); // determine writing mode
10014   
10015       if (/up|down/.test(direction) && !isTerminal) {
10016         writingMode = 'vertical-rl';
10017         textOrientation = 'upright';
10018         letterSpacing = '-1px';
10019       }
10020   
10021       if (direction === 'down' && !isTerminal) {
10022         xShift = 0;
10023         yShift = -2;
10024       } else if (direction === 'up' && !isTerminal) {
10025         xShift = 0.5;
10026       } else if (direction === 'left') {
10027         xShift = 2;
10028       }
10029   
10030       if (direction === 'left' || direction === 'up' && !isTerminal) {
10031         textDirection = 'direction: rtl; unicode-bidi: bidi-override;';
10032       } // now the text element
10033   
10034   
10035       textElem.setAttributeNS(null, 'x', pos.x + xShift);
10036       textElem.setAttributeNS(null, 'y', pos.y + yShift);
10037       textElem.setAttributeNS(null, 'class', 'element');
10038       textElem.setAttributeNS(null, 'fill', this.themeManager.getColor(elementName));
10039       textElem.setAttributeNS(null, 'style', `
10040                   text-anchor: start;
10041                   writing-mode: ${writingMode};
10042                   text-orientation: ${textOrientation};
10043                   letter-spacing: ${letterSpacing};
10044                   ${textDirection}
10045               `);
10046       let textNode = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'tspan'); // special case for element names that are 2 letters
10047   
10048       if (elementName.length > 1) {
10049         let textAnchor = /up|down/.test(direction) ? 'middle' : 'start';
10050         textNode.setAttributeNS(null, 'style', `
10051                   unicode-bidi: plaintext;
10052                   writing-mode: lr-tb;
10053                   letter-spacing: normal;
10054                   text-anchor: ${textAnchor};
10055               `);
10056       }
10057   
10058       textNode.appendChild(document.createTextNode(elementName));
10059       textElem.appendChild(textNode); // Charge
10060   
10061       if (charge) {
10062         let chargeElem = this.createSubSuperScripts(getChargeText(charge), 'super');
10063         textNode.appendChild(chargeElem);
10064       }
10065   
10066       let isotopeText = '0';
10067   
10068       if (isotope > 0) {
10069         let isotopeElem = this.createSubSuperScripts(isotope.toString(), 'super');
10070         textNode.appendChild(isotopeElem);
10071       } // TODO: Better handle exceptions
10072       // Exception for nitro (draw nitro as NO2 instead of N+O-O)
10073   
10074   
10075       if (charge === 1 && elementName === 'N' && attachedPseudoElement.hasOwnProperty('0O') && attachedPseudoElement.hasOwnProperty('0O-1')) {
10076         attachedPseudoElement = {
10077           '0O': {
10078             element: 'O',
10079             count: 2,
10080             hydrogenCount: 0,
10081             previousElement: 'C',
10082             charge: ''
10083           }
10084         };
10085         charge = 0;
10086       }
10087   
10088       if (hydrogens > 0) {
10089         let hydrogenElem = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'tspan');
10090         hydrogenElem.setAttributeNS(null, 'style', 'unicode-bidi: plaintext;');
10091         hydrogenElem.appendChild(document.createTextNode('H'));
10092         textElem.appendChild(hydrogenElem);
10093   
10094         if (hydrogens > 1) {
10095           let hydrogenCountElem = this.createSubSuperScripts(hydrogens, 'sub');
10096           hydrogenElem.appendChild(hydrogenCountElem);
10097         }
10098       }
10099   
10100       for (let key in attachedPseudoElement) {
10101         if (!attachedPseudoElement.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
10102           continue;
10103         }
10104   
10105         let element = attachedPseudoElement[key].element,
10106             elementCount = attachedPseudoElement[key].count,
10107             hydrogenCount = attachedPseudoElement[key].hydrogenCount,
10108             elementCharge = attachedPseudoElement[key].charge,
10109             pseudoElementElem = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'tspan');
10110         pseudoElementElem.setAttributeNS(null, 'style', 'unicode-bidi: plaintext;');
10111         pseudoElementElem.appendChild(document.createTextNode(element));
10112         pseudoElementElem.setAttributeNS(null, 'fill', this.themeManager.getColor(element));
10113   
10114         if (elementCharge !== 0) {
10115           let elementChargeElem = this.createSubSuperScripts(getChargeText(elementCharge), 'super');
10116           pseudoElementElem.appendChild(elementChargeElem);
10117         }
10118   
10119         if (hydrogenCount > 0) {
10120           let pseudoHydrogenElem = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'tspan');
10121           pseudoHydrogenElem.setAttributeNS(null, 'style', 'unicode-bidi: plaintext;');
10122           pseudoHydrogenElem.appendChild(document.createTextNode('H'));
10123           pseudoElementElem.appendChild(pseudoHydrogenElem);
10124   
10125           if (hydrogenCount > 1) {
10126             let hydrogenCountElem = this.createSubSuperScripts(hydrogenCount, 'sub');
10127             pseudoHydrogenElem.appendChild(hydrogenCountElem);
10128           }
10129         }
10130   
10131         if (elementCount > 1) {
10132           let elementCountElem = this.createSubSuperScripts(elementCount, 'sub');
10133           pseudoElementElem.appendChild(elementCountElem);
10134         }
10135   
10136         textElem.appendChild(pseudoElementElem);
10137       }
10138   
10139       this.vertices.push(textElem);
10140     }
10141     /**
10142      * @param {Line} line the line object to create the wedge from
10143      */
10144   
10145   
10146     drawWedge(line) {
10147       let offsetX = this.offsetX,
10148           offsetY = this.offsetY,
10149           l = line.getLeftVector().clone(),
10150           r = line.getRightVector().clone();
10151       l.x += offsetX;
10152       l.y += offsetY;
10153       r.x += offsetX;
10154       r.y += offsetY;
10155       let normals = Vector2.normals(l, r);
10156       normals[0].normalize();
10157       normals[1].normalize();
10158       let isRightChiralCenter = line.getRightChiral();
10159       let start = l,
10160           end = r;
10161   
10162       if (isRightChiralCenter) {
10163         start = r;
10164         end = l;
10165       }
10166   
10167       let t = Vector2.add(start, Vector2.multiplyScalar(normals[0], this.halfBondThickness)),
10168           u = Vector2.add(end, Vector2.multiplyScalar(normals[0], 1.5 + this.halfBondThickness)),
10169           v = Vector2.add(end, Vector2.multiplyScalar(normals[1], 1.5 + this.halfBondThickness)),
10170           w = Vector2.add(start, Vector2.multiplyScalar(normals[1], this.halfBondThickness));
10171       let polygon = document.createElementNS('http://www.w3.org/2000/svg', 'polygon'),
10172           gradient = this.createGradient(line, l.x, l.y, r.x, r.y);
10173       polygon.setAttributeNS(null, 'points', `${t.x},${t.y} ${u.x},${u.y} ${v.x},${v.y} ${w.x},${w.y}`);
10174       polygon.setAttributeNS(null, 'fill', `url('#${gradient}')`);
10175       this.paths.push(polygon);
10176     }
10177   
10178   }

10190     /**
10191      * Returns the hex code of a color associated with a key from the current theme.
10192      *
10193      * @param {String} key The color key in the theme (e.g. C, N, BACKGROUND, ...).
10194      * @returns {String} A color hex value.
10195      */
10196   
10197   
10198     getColor(key) {
10199       if (key) {

10201   
10202         if (key in this.theme) {

10204         }
10205       }
10206

10208     }
10209     /**
10210      * Sets the theme to the specified string if it exists. If it does not, this
10211      * does nothing.
10212      *
10213      * @param {String} theme the name of the theme to switch to
10214      */
10215   
10216

10269   class Vector2 {

10271      * The constructor of the class Vector2.

10276     constructor(x, y) {
10277       if (arguments.length == 0) {
10278         this.x = 0;
10279         this.y = 0;
10280       } else if (arguments.length == 1) {
10281         this.x = x.x;
10282         this.y = x.y;
10283       } else {
10284         this.x = x;
10285         this.y = y;
10286       }
10287     }

10290      *
10291      * @returns {Vector2} The clone of this vector.

10296       return new Vector2(this.x, this.y);
10297     }

10306       return '(' + this.x + ',' + this.y + ')';
10307     }

10395     /**

10398      * @param {Vector2} vec A vector.
10399      * @returns {Number} The euclidean distance between the two vectors.
10400      */
10401   
10402   
10403     distance(vec) {
10404       return Math.sqrt((vec.x - this.x) * (vec.x - this.x) + (vec.y - this.y) * (vec.y - this.y));
10405     }
10406     /**
10407      * Returns the squared euclidean distance between this vector and another vector. When only the relative distances of a set of vectors are needed, this is is less expensive than using distance(vec).
10408      *
10409      * @param {Vector2} vec Another vector.
10410      * @returns {Number} The squared euclidean distance of the two vectors.
10411      */
10412   
10413   
10414     distanceSq(vec) {
10415       return (vec.x - this.x) * (vec.x - this.x) + (vec.y - this.y) * (vec.y - this.y);
10416     }
10417     /**
10418      * Checks whether or not this vector is in a clockwise or counter-clockwise rotational direction compared to another vector in relation to the coordinate system.
10419      *
10420      * @param {Vector2} vec Another vector.
10421      * @returns {Number} Returns -1, 0 or 1 if the vector supplied as an argument is clockwise, neutral or counter-clockwise respectively to this vector in relation to the coordinate system.
10422      */
10423   
10424   
10425     clockwise(vec) {
10426       let a = this.y * vec.x;
10427       let b = this.x * vec.y;
10428   
10429       if (a > b) {
10430         return -1;
10431       } else if (a === b) {
10432         return 0;
10433       }
10434   
10435       return 1;
10436     }
10437     /**
10438      * Checks whether or not this vector is in a clockwise or counter-clockwise rotational direction compared to another vector in relation to an arbitrary third vector.
10439      *
10440      * @param {Vector2} center The central vector.
10441      * @param {Vector2} vec Another vector.
10442      * @returns {Number} Returns -1, 0 or 1 if the vector supplied as an argument is clockwise, neutral or counter-clockwise respectively to this vector in relation to an arbitrary third vector.
10443      */
10444   
10445   
10446     relativeClockwise(center, vec) {
10447       let a = (this.y - center.y) * (vec.x - center.x);
10448       let b = (this.x - center.x) * (vec.y - center.y);
10449   
10450       if (a > b) {
10451         return -1;
10452       } else if (a === b) {
10453         return 0;
10454       }
10455   
10456       return 1;
10457     }
10458     /**
10459      * Rotates this vector by a given number of radians around the origin of the coordinate system.
10460      *
10461      * @param {Number} angle The angle in radians to rotate the vector.
10462      * @returns {Vector2} Returns itself.
10463      */
10464   
10465   
10466     rotate(angle) {
10467       let tmp = new Vector2(0, 0);
10468       let cosAngle = Math.cos(angle);
10469       let sinAngle = Math.sin(angle);
10470       tmp.x = this.x * cosAngle - this.y * sinAngle;
10471       tmp.y = this.x * sinAngle + this.y * cosAngle;
10472       this.x = tmp.x;
10473       this.y = tmp.y;
10474       return this;
10475     }
10476     /**
10477      * Rotates this vector around another vector.
10478      *
10479      * @param {Number} angle The angle in radians to rotate the vector.
10480      * @param {Vector2} vec The vector which is used as the rotational center.
10481      * @returns {Vector2} Returns itself.
10482      */
10483   
10484   
10485     rotateAround(angle, vec) {
10486       let s = Math.sin(angle);
10487       let c = Math.cos(angle);
10488       this.x -= vec.x;
10489       this.y -= vec.y;
10490       let x = this.x * c - this.y * s;
10491       let y = this.x * s + this.y * c;
10492       this.x = x + vec.x;
10493       this.y = y + vec.y;
10494       return this;
10495     }
10496     /**
10497      * Rotate a vector around a given center to the same angle as another vector (so that the two vectors and the center are in a line, with both vectors on one side of the center), keeps the distance from this vector to the center.
10498      *
10499      * @param {Vector2} vec The vector to rotate this vector to.
10500      * @param {Vector2} center The rotational center.
10501      * @param {Number} [offsetAngle=0.0] An additional amount of radians to rotate the vector.
10502      * @returns {Vector2} Returns itself.
10503      */
10504   
10505   
10506     rotateTo(vec, center, offsetAngle = 0.0) {
10507       // Problem if this is first position
10508       this.x += 0.001;
10509       this.y -= 0.001;

10511       let b = Vector2.subtract(vec, center);
10512       let angle = Vector2.angle(b, a);
10513       this.rotateAround(angle + offsetAngle, center);
10514       return this;

10516     /**
10517      * Rotates the vector away from a specified vector around a center.
10518      * 
10519      * @param {Vector2} vec The vector this one is rotated away from.
10520      * @param {Vector2} center The rotational center.
10521      * @param {Number} angle The angle by which to rotate.
10522      */
10523   
10524   
10525     rotateAwayFrom(vec, center, angle) {
10526       this.rotateAround(angle, center);
10527       let distSqA = this.distanceSq(vec);
10528       this.rotateAround(-2.0 * angle, center);
10529       let distSqB = this.distanceSq(vec); // If it was rotated towards the other vertex, rotate in other direction by same amount.
10530   
10531       if (distSqB < distSqA) {
10532         this.rotateAround(2.0 * angle, center);
10533       }
10534     }
10535     /**

10549       tmp.rotateAround(-2.0 * angle, center);
10550       let distSqB = tmp.distanceSq(vec);
10551

10553         return angle;
10554       } else {
10555         return -angle;

10596     /**
10597      * Checks whether a vector lies within a polygon spanned by a set of vectors.
10598      *
10599      * @param {Vector2[]} polygon An array of vectors spanning the polygon.
10600      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not this vector is within a polygon.
10601      */
10602   
10603   
10604     isInPolygon(polygon) {
10605       let inside = false; // Its not always a given, that the polygon is convex (-> sugars)
10606   
10607       for (let i = 0, j = polygon.length - 1; i < polygon.length; j = i++) {
10608         if (polygon[i].y > this.y != polygon[j].y > this.y && this.x < (polygon[j].x - polygon[i].x) * (this.y - polygon[i].y) / (polygon[j].y - polygon[i].y) + polygon[i].x) {
10609           inside = !inside;
10610         }
10611       }
10612   
10613       return inside;
10614     }

10656     /**

10683     /**

10773       let delta = Vector2.subtract(vecB, vecA);
10774       return [new Vector2(-delta.y, delta.x).normalize(), new Vector2(delta.y, -delta.x).normalize()];

10783      */
10784   
10785

10787       return new Vector2(vecA.x / vecB.x, vecA.y / vecB.y);
10788     }
10789     /**

10791      *

10795      * @returns {Vector2} The fraction of the two vectors.
10796      */
10797

10800       return new Vector2(vecA.x / s, vecA.y / s);

10802     /**
10803      * Returns the dot product of two vectors.
10804      *
10805      * @static
10806      * @param {Vector2} vecA A vector.
10807      * @param {Vector2} vecB A vector.
10808      * @returns {Number} The dot product of two vectors.
10809      */
10810   
10811   
10812     static dot(vecA, vecB) {
10813       return vecA.x * vecB.x + vecA.y * vecB.y;
10814     }
10815     /**
10816      * Returns the angle between two vectors.
10817      *
10818      * @static
10819      * @param {Vector2} vecA A vector.
10820      * @param {Vector2} vecB A vector.
10821      * @returns {Number} The angle between two vectors in radians.
10822      */
10823   
10824   
10825     static angle(vecA, vecB) {
10826       let dot = Vector2.dot(vecA, vecB);
10827       return Math.acos(dot / (vecA.length() * vecB.length()));
10828     }
10829     /**
10830      * Returns the angle between two vectors based on a third vector in between.
10831      *
10832      * @static
10833      * @param {Vector2} vecA A vector.
10834      * @param {Vector2} vecB A (central) vector.
10835      * @param {Vector2} vecC A vector.
10836      * @returns {Number} The angle in radians.
10837      */
10838   
10839   
10840     static threePointangle(vecA, vecB, vecC) {
10841       let ab = Vector2.subtract(vecB, vecA);
10842       let bc = Vector2.subtract(vecC, vecB);
10843       let abLength = vecA.distance(vecB);
10844       let bcLength = vecB.distance(vecC);
10845       return Math.acos(Vector2.dot(ab, bc) / (abLength * bcLength));
10846     }
10847     /**
10848      * Returns the scalar projection of a vector on another vector.
10849      *
10850      * @static
10851      * @param {Vector2} vecA The vector to be projected.
10852      * @param {Vector2} vecB The vector to be projection upon.
10853      * @returns {Number} The scalar component.
10854      */
10855   
10856   
10857     static scalarProjection(vecA, vecB) {
10858       let unit = vecB.normalized();
10859       return Vector2.dot(vecA, unit);
10860     }
10861     /**
10862     * Returns the average vector (normalized) of the input vectors.
10863     *
10864     * @static
10865     * @param {Array} vecs An array containing vectors.
10866     * @returns {Vector2} The resulting vector (normalized).
10867     */
10868   
10869   
10870     static averageDirection(vecs) {
10871       let avg = new Vector2(0.0, 0.0);
10872   
10873       for (var i = 0; i < vecs.length; i++) {
10874         let vec = vecs[i];
10875         avg.add(vec);
10876       }
10877   
10878       return avg.normalize();
10879     }
10880   
10881   }

10889   const MathHelper = require('./MathHelper');
10890   
10891   const ArrayHelper = require('./ArrayHelper');
10892   
10893   const Vector2 = require('./Vector2');
10894   
10895   const Atom = require('./Atom');
10896   /** 
10897    * A class representing a vertex.
10898    * 
10899    * @property {Number} id The id of this vertex.
10900    * @property {Atom} value The atom associated with this vertex.
10901    * @property {Vector2} position The position of this vertex.
10902    * @property {Vector2} previousPosition The position of the previous vertex.
10903    * @property {Number|null} parentVertexId The id of the previous vertex.
10904    * @property {Number[]} children The ids of the children of this vertex.
10905    * @property {Number[]} spanningTreeChildren The ids of the children of this vertex as defined in the spanning tree defined by the SMILES.
10906    * @property {Number[]} edges The ids of edges associated with this vertex.
10907    * @property {Boolean} positioned A boolean indicating whether or not this vertex has been positioned.
10908    * @property {Number} angle The angle of this vertex.
10909    * @property {Number} dir The direction of this vertex.
10910    * @property {Number} neighbourCount The number of neighbouring vertices.
10911    * @property {Number[]} neighbours The vertex ids of neighbouring vertices.
10912    * @property {String[]} neighbouringElements The element symbols associated with neighbouring vertices.
10913    * @property {Boolean} forcePositioned A boolean indicating whether or not this vertex was positioned using a force-based approach.
10914    */
10915   
10916   
10917   class Vertex {
10918     /**
10919      * The constructor for the class Vertex.
10920      *
10921      * @param {Atom} value The value associated with this vertex.
10922      * @param {Number} [x=0] The initial x coordinate of the positional vector of this vertex.
10923      * @param {Number} [y=0] The initial y coordinate of the positional vector of this vertex.
10924      */
10925     constructor(value, x = 0, y = 0) {
10926       this.id = null;
10927       this.value = value;
10928       this.position = new Vector2(x ? x : 0, y ? y : 0);
10929       this.previousPosition = new Vector2(0, 0);
10930       this.parentVertexId = null;
10931       this.children = Array();
10932       this.spanningTreeChildren = Array();
10933       this.edges = Array();
10934       this.positioned = false;
10935       this.angle = null;
10936       this.dir = 1.0;
10937       this.neighbourCount = 0;
10938       this.neighbours = Array();
10939       this.neighbouringElements = Array();
10940       this.forcePositioned = false;
10941     }
10942     /**
10943      * Set the 2D coordinates of the vertex.
10944      * 
10945      * @param {Number} x The x component of the coordinates.
10946      * @param {Number} y The y component of the coordinates.
10947      * 
10948      */
10949   
10950   
10951     setPosition(x, y) {
10952       this.position.x = x;
10953       this.position.y = y;
10954     }
10955     /**
10956      * Set the 2D coordinates of the vertex from a Vector2.
10957      * 
10958      * @param {Vector2} v A 2D vector.
10959      * 
10960      */
10961   
10962   
10963     setPositionFromVector(v) {
10964       this.position.x = v.x;
10965       this.position.y = v.y;
10966     }
10967     /**
10968      * Add a child vertex id to this vertex.
10969      * @param {Number} vertexId The id of a vertex to be added as a child to this vertex.
10970      */
10971   
10972   
10973     addChild(vertexId) {
10974       this.children.push(vertexId);
10975       this.neighbours.push(vertexId);
10976       this.neighbourCount++;
10977     }
10978     /**
10979      * Add a child vertex id to this vertex as the second child of the neighbours array,
10980      * except this vertex is the first vertex of the SMILE string, then it is added as the first.
10981      * This is used to get the correct ordering of neighbours for parity calculations.
10982      * If a hydrogen is implicitly attached to the chiral center, insert as the third child.
10983      * @param {Number} vertexId The id of a vertex to be added as a child to this vertex.
10984      * @param {Number} ringbondIndex The index of the ringbond.
10985      */
10986   
10987   
10988     addRingbondChild(vertexId, ringbondIndex) {
10989       this.children.push(vertexId);
10990   
10991       if (this.value.bracket) {
10992         let index = 1;
10993   
10994         if (this.id === 0 && this.value.bracket.hcount === 0) {
10995           index = 0;
10996         }
10997   
10998         if (this.value.bracket.hcount === 1 && ringbondIndex === 0) {
10999           index = 2;
11000         }
11001   
11002         if (this.value.bracket.hcount === 1 && ringbondIndex === 1) {
11003           if (this.neighbours.length < 3) {
11004             index = 2;
11005           } else {
11006             index = 3;
11007           }
11008         }
11009   
11010         if (this.value.bracket.hcount === null && ringbondIndex === 0) {
11011           index = 1;
11012         }
11013   
11014         if (this.value.bracket.hcount === null && ringbondIndex === 1) {
11015           if (this.neighbours.length < 3) {
11016             index = 1;
11017           } else {
11018             index = 2;
11019           }
11020         }
11021   
11022         this.neighbours.splice(index, 0, vertexId);
11023       } else {
11024         this.neighbours.push(vertexId);
11025       }
11026   
11027       this.neighbourCount++;
11028     }
11029     /**
11030      * Set the vertex id of the parent.
11031      * 
11032      * @param {Number} parentVertexId The parents vertex id.
11033      */
11034   
11035   
11036     setParentVertexId(parentVertexId) {
11037       this.neighbourCount++;
11038       this.parentVertexId = parentVertexId;
11039       this.neighbours.push(parentVertexId);
11040     }
11041     /**
11042      * Returns true if this vertex is terminal (has no parent or child vertices), otherwise returns false. Always returns true if associated value has property hasAttachedPseudoElements set to true.
11043      *
11044      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not this vertex is terminal.
11045      */
11046   
11047   
11048     isTerminal() {
11049       if (this.value.hasAttachedPseudoElements) {
11050         return true;
11051       }
11052   
11053       return this.parentVertexId === null && this.children.length < 2 || this.children.length === 0;
11054     }
11055     /**
11056      * Clones this vertex and returns the clone.
11057      *
11058      * @returns {Vertex} A clone of this vertex.
11059      */
11060   
11061   
11062     clone() {
11063       let clone = new Vertex(this.value, this.position.x, this.position.y);
11064       clone.id = this.id;
11065       clone.previousPosition = new Vector2(this.previousPosition.x, this.previousPosition.y);
11066       clone.parentVertexId = this.parentVertexId;
11067       clone.children = ArrayHelper.clone(this.children);
11068       clone.spanningTreeChildren = ArrayHelper.clone(this.spanningTreeChildren);
11069       clone.edges = ArrayHelper.clone(this.edges);
11070       clone.positioned = this.positioned;
11071       clone.angle = this.angle;
11072       clone.forcePositioned = this.forcePositioned;
11073       return clone;
11074     }
11075     /**
11076      * Returns true if this vertex and the supplied vertex both have the same id, else returns false.
11077      *
11078      * @param {Vertex} vertex The vertex to check.
11079      * @returns {Boolean} A boolean indicating whether or not the two vertices have the same id.
11080      */
11081   
11082   
11083     equals(vertex) {
11084       return this.id === vertex.id;
11085     }
11086     /**
11087      * Returns the angle of this vertexes positional vector. If a reference vector is supplied in relations to this vector, else in relations to the coordinate system.
11088      *
11089      * @param {Vector2} [referenceVector=null] - The reference vector.
11090      * @param {Boolean} [returnAsDegrees=false] - If true, returns angle in degrees, else in radians.
11091      * @returns {Number} The angle of this vertex.
11092      */
11093   
11094   
11095     getAngle(referenceVector = null, returnAsDegrees = false) {
11096       let u = null;
11097   
11098       if (!referenceVector) {
11099         u = Vector2.subtract(this.position, this.previousPosition);
11100       } else {
11101         u = Vector2.subtract(this.position, referenceVector);
11102       }
11103   
11104       if (returnAsDegrees) {
11105         return MathHelper.toDeg(u.angle());
11106       }
11107   
11108       return u.angle();
11109     }
11110     /**
11111      * Returns the suggested text direction when text is added at the position of this vertex.
11112      *
11113      * @param {Vertex[]} vertices The array of vertices for the current molecule.
11114      * @returns {String} The suggested direction of the text.
11115      */
11116   
11117   
11118     getTextDirection(vertices) {
11119       let neighbours = this.getDrawnNeighbours(vertices);
11120       let angles = Array();
11121   
11122       for (let i = 0; i < neighbours.length; i++) {
11123         angles.push(this.getAngle(vertices[neighbours[i]].position));
11124       }
11125   
11126       let textAngle = MathHelper.meanAngle(angles); // Round to 0, 90, 180 or 270 degree
11127   
11128       let halfPi = Math.PI / 2.0;
11129       textAngle = Math.round(Math.round(textAngle / halfPi) * halfPi);
11130   
11131       if (textAngle === 2) {
11132         return 'down';
11133       } else if (textAngle === -2) {
11134         return 'up';
11135       } else if (textAngle === 0 || textAngle === -0) {
11136         return 'right'; // is checking for -0 necessary?
11137       } else if (textAngle === 3 || textAngle === -3) {
11138         return 'left';
11139       } else {
11140         return 'down'; // default to down
11141       }
11142     }
11143     /**
11144      * Returns an array of ids of neighbouring vertices.
11145      *
11146      * @param {Number} [vertexId=null] If a value is supplied, the vertex with this id is excluded from the returned indices.
11147      * @returns {Number[]} An array containing the ids of neighbouring vertices.
11148      */
11149   
11150   
11151     getNeighbours(vertexId = null) {
11152       if (vertexId === null) {
11153         return this.neighbours.slice();
11154       }
11155   
11156       let arr = Array();
11157   
11158       for (let i = 0; i < this.neighbours.length; i++) {
11159         if (this.neighbours[i] !== vertexId) {
11160           arr.push(this.neighbours[i]);
11161         }
11162       }
11163   
11164       return arr;
11165     }
11166     /**
11167      * Returns an array of ids of neighbouring vertices that will be drawn (vertex.value.isDrawn === true).
11168      * 
11169      * @param {Vertex[]} vertices An array containing the vertices associated with the current molecule.
11170      * @returns {Number[]} An array containing the ids of neighbouring vertices that will be drawn.
11171      */
11172   
11173   
11174     getDrawnNeighbours(vertices) {
11175       let arr = Array();
11176   
11177       for (let i = 0; i < this.neighbours.length; i++) {
11178         if (vertices[this.neighbours[i]].value.isDrawn) {
11179           arr.push(this.neighbours[i]);
11180         }
11181       }
11182   
11183       return arr;
11184     }
11185     /**
11186      * Returns the number of neighbours of this vertex.
11187      *
11188      * @returns {Number} The number of neighbours.
11189      */
11190   
11191   
11192     getNeighbourCount() {
11193       return this.neighbourCount;
11194     }
11195     /**
11196      * Returns a list of ids of vertices neighbouring this one in the original spanning tree, excluding the ringbond connections.
11197      *
11198      * @param {Number} [vertexId=null] If supplied, the vertex with this id is excluded from the array returned.
11199      * @returns {Number[]} An array containing the ids of the neighbouring vertices.
11200      */
11201   
11202   
11203     getSpanningTreeNeighbours(vertexId = null) {
11204       let neighbours = Array();
11205   
11206       for (let i = 0; i < this.spanningTreeChildren.length; i++) {
11207         if (vertexId === undefined || vertexId != this.spanningTreeChildren[i]) {
11208           neighbours.push(this.spanningTreeChildren[i]);
11209         }
11210       }
11211   
11212       if (this.parentVertexId != null) {
11213         if (vertexId === undefined || vertexId != this.parentVertexId) {
11214           neighbours.push(this.parentVertexId);
11215         }
11216       }
11217   
11218       return neighbours;
11219     }
11220     /**
11221      * Gets the next vertex in the ring in opposide direction to the supplied vertex id.
11222      *
11223      * @param {Vertex[]} vertices The array of vertices for the current molecule.
11224      * @param {Number} ringId The id of the ring containing this vertex.
11225      * @param {Number} previousVertexId The id of the previous vertex. The next vertex will be opposite from the vertex with this id as seen from this vertex.
11226      * @returns {Number} The id of the next vertex in the ring.
11227      */
11228   
11229   
11230     getNextInRing(vertices, ringId, previousVertexId) {
11231       let neighbours = this.getNeighbours();
11232   
11233       for (let i = 0; i < neighbours.length; i++) {
11234         if (ArrayHelper.contains(vertices[neighbours[i]].value.rings, {
11235           value: ringId
11236         }) && neighbours[i] != previousVertexId) {
11237           return neighbours[i];
11238         }
11239       }
11240   
11241       return null;
11242     }
11243   
11244   }
11245   
11246   module.exports = Vertex;
